{"name":"Mad Brawler","type":"character","img":"modules/savage-eberron-bestiary/assets/bestiary/humanoids/shifter/shifter-warrior-01.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":6,"runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":0,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":0,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>"},"species":{"name":"Shifter (Beasthide)"},"currency":"500","wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":3,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":4,"rank":"Seasoned","details":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Creation:&nbsp;</strong>Barbarian, Vigor d8, Brawny</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>(N) Attribute:</strong>&nbsp;Vigor d8</li>\n<li><strong>(N) Edge:&nbsp;</strong>Brawler</li>\n<li><strong>(N) Edge:</strong>&nbsp;Martial Artist</li>\n<li><strong>(S) Edge:&nbsp;</strong>Bruiser</li>\n<li><strong>(S) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(S) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(S) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n</ol>\n</div>"},"bennies":{"value":3,"max":3},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Barbarian","displayName":0,"img":"modules/savage-eberron-bestiary/assets/bestiary_tokens/humanoids/shifter/shifter-warrior-01.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":"ffE6DnbziNuak5z9","actorLink":true,"disposition":1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"gso7NeJMXpdXlU6X","name":"Untrained","type":"skill","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":600000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skill.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"RMmVU7ormCp2MOqN","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":700000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sAig03GZiFKqBX7p"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/jump-across.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BkQxvPAlZLOJY7OZ","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":800000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.8N1uMThntsjaUPem"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/gift-of-knowledge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GN2DOxOtwyROzNWZ","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":900000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xOmuCR92Ys9jD5vg"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/convince.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8qCrEiZTjPRuJ2Qq","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1000000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.z9FmdFVGOOW2kufm"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/hidden.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"hzQAaO1x5wYjovWb","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.yvw9bMgsrWQXuZN2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ruBTbGRqlMoy2uSz","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/talk.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GQMFWtp6IWJ6kqTY","name":"Crowns (cp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":8,"weight":0.02,"price":0.01,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.fBZcb1EdAbO4EEOl"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-copper.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"6IZsePloV317RsUb","name":"Dragons (pp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":11,"weight":0.02,"price":10,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.33dBhsz0KCjjGHYe"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-platinum.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"HNsCemxmNdyU8oWj","name":"Galifars (gp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":13,"weight":0.02,"price":1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.CbrYbcaa5bTV8Wnd"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-gold.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Mccx8d95umBCcVgu","name":"Sovereigns (sp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":5,"weight":0.02,"price":0.1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EeHD4BJl6bS0eE4D"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-silver.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ZZrY9N4uTnYeHmFJ","name":"Unarmed Strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"+1","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d8","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":1600001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/fist.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"xAGF8XYetavKyYrd","name":"Fast","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Barbarians are fast and durable runners. They increase their base @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} by +2. This doesn&rsquo;t affect their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{running die}, but does stack with Edges like @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Fleet-Footed]{Fleet-Footed} or racial modifiers.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Barbarian"}},"sort":200001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.jHTlt9HcKW8HShHn"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[{"_id":"suEcQ6e8TEBqE58I","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.speed.value","value":"2","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/run.svg","label":"Fast","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"xtP4n7Z1u5Hc4G2M","name":"Brawny","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Your bruiser is very large or very fit. Her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} increases by +1 (and therefore @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} by 1) and she treats her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} as one die type higher when determining <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Gear Notes]{Encumbrance}</strong></span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">&nbsp;</span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">and </span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Minimum Strength]{Minimum Strength} </span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">to use armor, weapons, and equipment without a penalty.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><br />Brawny can&rsquo;t increase a character&rsquo;s Size above +3.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d6+, Vigor d6+"}},"sort":100001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9dc4ijzy8uh","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.7uRlXxxSuEjm20Cc"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[{"_id":"tyD5M9Dy2604siMm","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.size","value":"1","mode":2},{"key":"data.attributes.strength.encumbranceSteps","value":"2","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/muscle-up.svg","label":"Brawny","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"rhLm2dpDLOyOP0TA","name":"Brawler","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">His fists hit like hammers or his talons cut like scythes. His body feels like it&rsquo;s made of stone. Brawlers increase their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} by 1 and roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} +d4 when hitting with their fists or feet (or claws if they have them). If they already have a damage die from&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Claws)]{Claws}</strong>, the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Martial Artist]{Martial Artist} Edge, etc., increase the damage die type by one instead. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The Brawler Edge doesn&rsquo;t make the character&rsquo;s fists </span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons}</span></strong></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d8+, Vigor d8+"}},"sort":200001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bv1geyfk6c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.FbQVS6pOfmOU92Me"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[{"_id":"1rqEHRKUr87Hr1pt","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.size","value":"1","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/high-punch.svg","label":"Brawler","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"1nOszDpDFTZNXKy6","name":"Bruiser","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The fighter increases his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} an additional +1, and the damage caused with his fists or claws another die type.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Brawler"}},"sort":300001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bv1geyfk6c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.SHXBu9qS2LkH66e7"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[{"_id":"97gpsC3sVX7T4ac1","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.value","value":"1","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/muscle-up.svg","label":"Bruiser","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"chPhPSJflf7i5WeT","name":"Rage","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Barbarians can call upon inner reserves of strength and ferocity in desperate circumstances. As a limited @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action}, a barbarian may &ldquo;rage&rdquo; voluntarily. If she&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounded}, she must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} roll or rage whether she wants to or not.</p>\n<p>Rage lasts five rounds. After the barbarian&rsquo;s fifth turn raging, she takes a level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} that can only be recovered with an hour&rsquo;s rest (generally no walking, riding, etc).</p>\n<p>An @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Exhausted} barbarian who rages is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated} afterward.</p>\n<p>While raging, a barbarian gains the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fury:</strong> Her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} increases a die type (ignoring her usual maximum) and every melee attack must be a <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Attack]{Wild Attack}</strong>. She can&rsquo;t use any skill or ability that requires more than a few seconds of concentration (DM&rsquo;s call).</li>\n<li><strong>Enraged:</strong> She ignores two levels of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound penalties} (this stacks with any other abilities that reduce Wound penalties). &nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Reckless Abandon:</strong> If a barbarian rolls a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} check while raging, she hits a random target within range of her attack (not the intended target), friend or foe. If there are no applicable targets, she injures herself and suffers @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bumps and Bruises]{Bumps and Bruises}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Barbarian"}},"sort":100001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9dc4ijzy8uh","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.kTiZWS3MbTd9mQSX"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[{"_id":"b8CMDAnrdO02xnyH","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.attributes.strength.die.sides","value":"2","mode":2},{"key":"data.wounds.ignored","value":"2","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/enrage.svg","label":"Rage","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"9i5g5AKfZ9uBd9KY","name":"Barbarian Armor Restriction (Medium)","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A barbarian&rsquo;s fighting style requires great freedom of movement. They subtract 4 from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility-based} skill rolls when wearing heavy armor or using a heavy shield.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":300001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.jjdnDUEcajDcIjVO"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Nck5a4Lq6kL9Ds48","name":"Barbarian","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>For some, there is only rage. In the ways of their people, in the fury of their passion, in the howl of battle, these brutal souls swear by the creed of conflict. Battle possessed, these savage warriors disdain the life of the professional guard or soldier. They seek to fight for the sake of the act itself.</p>\n<p>Known as barbarians, these warmongers know little of tactics, preparation, or the rules of warfare. For them, only the moment exists. They embrace the possibility that the next battle might hold their death. Within the barbarian&rsquo;s heart beats the primal spirit of struggle. Those who face their rage, beware.</p>\n<p>Barbarians gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Barbarian Armor Restriction (Medium)]{Barbarian Armor Restriction (Medium)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Fast]{Fast}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rage]{Rage}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d6+, Vigor d6+"}},"sort":200001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Pvc2ah5Ut7RNm64p"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"brznsdWNtUC0IGbO","name":"Animal Handling","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Animal Handling allows a hero to calm down an animal whether domestic or wild, intuit an animal's intention, or train an animal new tricks or behavior.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":100001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.vpHzreNDNjMKovUU"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/skills/labrador-head.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GA5k6ZlGEoPBuuZz","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1700001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/punch.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"gyDUJQK4sKbaMyKo","name":"Intimidation","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Intimidation is the art of frightening an opponent so that he backs down, reveals information, or flees.</p>\n<p>Intimidation is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} resisted by the opponent&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. In combat, this is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}. Out of combat, a successful roll means the foe backs down for the most part, reveals some information, or slinks away when the opportunity presents itself.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} might mean he backs down for the remainder of the scene, spills all the beans, or runs away as fast as he can.</p>\n<p>In or out of combat, a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} means the target is immune to this character&rsquo;s Intimidation attempts for the remainder of this encounter!</p>\n<p><strong>Networking:</strong> Intimidation can also be used as a &ldquo;macro&rdquo; skill to simulate several hours of working the streets. See&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}&nbsp;to see how to crack some heads for favors or information.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1800001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.RrgAZp50CgQyyY6w"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/arrest.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"7i34fVqPMTDrEupq","name":"Riding","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p>Riding allows a hero to mount, control, and ride any beast or beast-drawn vehicle common to his setting. This includes horses, camels, dragons, wagons, chariots, and the like. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mounted Combat]{Mounted Combat}.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1900001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.DHKzenDEPdjw3X2u"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/saddle.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"FkPju6ivtubOsrck","name":"Shooting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Shooting covers all attempts to hit a target with a ranged weapon such as a bow, pistol, or rocket launcher (thrown weapons use @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}). See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for details on ranged combat.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2000001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sOHfVvBDhe3Oy3r1"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/crosshair.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"KyP1bGiKbFwEmqCd","name":"Survival","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Survival allows a character to find food, water, or shelter in hostile environments. It can also be used to navigate wilderness environments, figure out which plants are good to eat and which aren&rsquo;t, and so on.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} Survival roll provides enough food and water for one person for one day; or five people with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p>More detailed information on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hunger]{Hunger} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Thirst]{Thirst} can be found under @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hazards]{Hazards} section.</p>\n<p><strong>Tracking: </strong>Survival can also be used to detect and follow tracks. Each roll generally covers following the tracks for one mile, but the GM should adjust this as needed for specific circumstances.</p>\n<p>The Game Master should assign a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{bonus or penalty} based on the target, environment, and time. Tracking a large group that recently passed through a snow-covered area might grant a bonus of +4, while following a single person over rocks and streams after more than a day incurs a &minus;4 penalty.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2100001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.15aEAJjDEjQy4fHF"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/camping-tent.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ZUa67MbJDNfoeBJH","name":"Low Light Vision","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Low Light Vision ignores penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim and Dark Illumination} (but not @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Pitch Darkness}).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.OL3T8otZVCkOoir3"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/angry-eyes.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GmRzNZ7Cip6Rf2Kw","name":"Beasthide","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The skin of beasthide @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Shifter]{shifters} harden, providing @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor} +4.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":400000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Sf5adq3bGzqv5gPJ"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/saber-toothed-cat-head.svg","effects":[{"_id":"JHrC9CfgBCwKbz7Z","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.armor","value":"4","mode":2},{"key":"data.wounds.ignored","value":"1","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/animal-hide.svg","label":"Beasthide Shifting","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Wx1osmG8XWiMKi36","name":"Outfit, Traveler's","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This set of clothes consists of boots, a wool skirt or breeches, a sturdy belt, a shirt (perhaps with a vest or jacket), and an ample cloak with a hood.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":900000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.RyeCbfEjKOWwkLXn"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/shirt.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"DhkR5Bdi2feYQEht","name":"Shifting","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This ability allows a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Shifter]{shifter} to tap into his lycanthropic heritage. At character creation, the player chooses a shifter ability from the list below. Shifting is a free action and lasts 1 minute or until dismissed as a free action. While in this animal-like form, the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Shifter]{shifter}&nbsp;can ignore 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{wound penalty}.</p>\n<p>When the shifting ends, the shifter must wait 4 hours before shifting again or suffer a level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{fatigue} when the second shifting ends. This level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{fatigue} can only be removed after 4 hours of abstaining from shifting. If the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Shifter]{shifter}&nbsp;uses this ability again during the recovery time, it inflicts another level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{fatigue} that requires an additional 4 hours of recovery time.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":400000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.tSbenW5pBnCQwKPx"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/saber-toothed-cat-head.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GYYsSGxhBw0bfSzH","name":"Bow, Composite","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":100,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Shooting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d6","range":"12/24/48","rof":"1","ap":"1","minStr":"d6","shots":"20","currentShots":"20","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":300001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.i05YkvN1RxzyIQ2u"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/bow-arrow.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"IPMHjavKqezUzAEe","name":"Quiver","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Holds 20 arrows/bolts.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":2900000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ipm13FxqvINKhVMz"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/quiver.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"C9gAfQ6IaJotPY79","name":"Arrow","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>These are standard bodkin arrows.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":20,"weight":0.05,"price":0.05,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.INnuPj0DXAMTxlVf"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/arrow-flights.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"eppuzBByxNZQxnA6","name":"Leather Greaves","type":"armor","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":5,"price":10,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"minStr":"d6","armor":2,"isNaturalArmor":false,"locations":{"head":false,"torso":false,"arms":false,"legs":true}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.8tmZCXDGiG5fZEf5"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/armored-pants.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"osidPLyMIyaTSgDL","name":"Axe, Hand","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":10,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{"czf29uz2s1":{"name":"Athletics (throwing)","type":"skill","rof":null,"skillMod":"","skillOverride":"Athletics","shotsUsed":null}}},"damage":"@str+d6","range":"3/6/12","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d6","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":800001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.F2JNgD0SfESTyCZ6"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/fire-axe.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"08FRrHGLWy1MP5Ka","name":"Pouch","type":"gear","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0.5,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":2800000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.uei6rnu2kRmn3n7w"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/knapsack.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"G1TpRlmiIjJsIRyG","name":"Mean","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This curmudgeon is ill-tempered and disagreeable. He has trouble doing anything kind for anyone else, must be paid for his troubles, and doesn&rsquo;t accept awards or favors graciously. Besides the obvious roleplaying issues, Mean characters subtract 1 from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{rolls}.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":3000000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.sNgSwqh2fGyM6i14"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"fzk5giirJYZHqdGB","name":"Poverty","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">It&rsquo;s said a fool and his money are soon parted. Your hero is one of them. He starts with half the usual @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{money} for your @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{setting} and just can&rsquo;t seem to hang on to funds acquired after play begins. In general, the player halves his total funds every game week.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":3100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.mNjWBgjuwM7pX0nL"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"6cNFkA9cpsYtCQqe","name":"Code of Honor","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Honor is very important to your character. He keeps his word, doesn&rsquo;t abuse or kill prisoners, and generally tries to operate within his world&rsquo;s particular notion of proper gentlemanly or ladylike behavior.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"sort":3200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.n7D74dbSRjPwaoue"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"JIxGjJkcMXytpi7a","name":"Martial Artist","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The fighter has trained in basic martial arts. Her fists and feet are weapons (see </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\"><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons}</strong>) </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">so she&rsquo;s always considered armed. She adds +1 when striking with them and causes @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength}+d4 damage. If she already has a Strength damage die from the&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Claws)]{Claws} </strong>racial ability or the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Brawler]{Brawler} Edge, increase the damage a die type. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Martial Artist does </span><em><span class=\"fontstyle3\">not </span></em><span class=\"fontstyle0\">add to damage from other Natural Weapons such as fangs or horns.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Fighting d6+"}},"sort":3300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bv1geyfk6c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.6OBT6Kt7CWBzIsab"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}}],"effects":[{"_id":"0eyALlK31L3JVlXE","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.speed.value","value":"2","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":0},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/run.svg","label":"Fast","origin":"Actor.ffE6DnbziNuak5z9.Item.xAGF8XYetavKyYrd","tint":null,"transfer":true},{"_id":"FJU80yUlajI9MRwe","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.size","value":"1","mode":2},{"key":"data.attributes.strength.encumbranceSteps","value":"2","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":0},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/muscle-up.svg","label":"Brawny","origin":"Actor.ffE6DnbziNuak5z9.Item.xtP4n7Z1u5Hc4G2M","tint":null,"transfer":true},{"_id":"LQCzLYUzPYGxIrJH","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.size","value":"1","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":0},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/high-punch.svg","label":"Brawler","origin":"Actor.ffE6DnbziNuak5z9.Item.rhLm2dpDLOyOP0TA","tint":null,"transfer":true},{"_id":"7F9GaBVG6HY8au5a","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.value","value":"1","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":0},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/muscle-up.svg","label":"Bruiser","origin":"Actor.ffE6DnbziNuak5z9.Item.1nOszDpDFTZNXKy6","tint":null,"transfer":true},{"_id":"Zyee7jYHMAAkhxcs","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.attributes.strength.die.sides","value":"2","mode":2},{"key":"data.wounds.ignored","value":"2","mode":2}],"disabled":true,"duration":{"startTime":0},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/enrage.svg","label":"Rage","origin":"Actor.ffE6DnbziNuak5z9.Item.chPhPSJflf7i5WeT","tint":null,"transfer":true},{"_id":"3rHfXYzWAIknvZhV","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.armor","value":"4","mode":2},{"key":"data.wounds.ignored","value":"1","mode":2}],"disabled":true,"duration":{"startTime":0},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/animal-hide.svg","label":"Beasthide Shifting","origin":"Actor.ffE6DnbziNuak5z9.Item.GmRzNZ7Cip6Rf2Kw","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"gm-notes":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_2mncjgs233x","path":"Savage Eberron Characters#/CF_SEP/Pregens","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"2vecxsYoQNdvdru7"}
{"name":"Rogue and Pickpocket","type":"character","img":"modules/savage-eberron-bestiary/assets/bestiary/humanoids/gnome/gnome-rogue-01.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":10,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":4,"runningMod":0,"value":5},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":1,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":0,"modifier":0},"size":-1},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>"},"species":{"name":"Gnome"},"currency":"500","wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{"value":1,"max":1,"Gnome Magic":{"value":1,"max":1}},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":3,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":4,"rank":"Seasoned","details":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Creation:&nbsp;</strong>Rabble-rouser, Rogue, Thief</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>(N) Edge:&nbsp;</strong>Quick</li>\n<li><strong>(N) Attribute:&nbsp;</strong>Agility d10</li>\n<li><strong>(N) Skills:</strong> Taunt d8, Athletics d8</li>\n<li><strong>(S) Edge:</strong> Trap Sense</li>\n<li><strong>(S) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(S) : </strong></li>\n<li><strong>(S) : </strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) : </strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n</ol>\n</div>"},"bennies":{"value":3,"max":3},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Rogue","displayName":0,"img":"modules/savage-eberron-bestiary/assets/bestiary_tokens/humanoids/gnome/gnome-rogue-01.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":"xtIX0GXhOwYbIcaR","actorLink":true,"disposition":1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"gso7NeJMXpdXlU6X","name":"Untrained","type":"skill","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":600000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skill.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"RMmVU7ormCp2MOqN","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":10,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":700000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sAig03GZiFKqBX7p"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/jump-across.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BkQxvPAlZLOJY7OZ","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":800000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.8N1uMThntsjaUPem"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/gift-of-knowledge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GN2DOxOtwyROzNWZ","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":900000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xOmuCR92Ys9jD5vg"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/convince.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8qCrEiZTjPRuJ2Qq","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1000000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.z9FmdFVGOOW2kufm"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/hidden.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"hzQAaO1x5wYjovWb","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.yvw9bMgsrWQXuZN2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ruBTbGRqlMoy2uSz","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/talk.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"TxNgTcI1DU6IpqsS","name":"Rogue","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Life is an endless adventure for those who live by their wits. Ever just one step ahead of danger, rogues bank on their cunning, skill, and charm to bend fate to their favor. Never knowing what to expect, they tend to prepare for everything. Out of necessity, they become adept manipulators, agile acrobats, or shadowy stalkers. They are thieves and gamblers, fast talkers and diplomats, bandits and bounty hunters, or explorers and investigators.</p>\n<p>Although many rogues favor the opportunities of towns and cities, some embrace life on the road. They wander from place to place, meeting exotic people and facing fantastic danger in pursuit of endless riches. In the end, all rogues desire to shape their fates and live life on their own terms.</p>\n<p>Rogues gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)]{Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sneak Attack]{Sneak Attack}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d6+, Thievery d6+"}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.UBXzgLMsycquNmh2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"PDfwwWLbHDWFeksi","name":"Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rogues are nimble and deadly acrobats. Bulky armor interferes with their abilities, so they subtract 4 from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility-based} skill rolls when wearing medium or heavy armor, or using medium or heavy shields.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":100000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B1jMHG6GDPNV0kYU"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"jq2nNXShbPeNdRhv","name":"Sneak Attack","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rogues add an additional d6 to their damage when they have @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{the Drop} on their victim, or the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable}. This applies to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} attacks.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Rogue"}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.5ggl5Khobnfxq698"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"0E55RPXKpsrAX0jd","name":"Trap Sense","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rogues are adept at spotting and defeating all but the most clever snares and traps. They get a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll anytime a detectable trap is about to be sprung within 5&rdquo; (10 yards). They must have line of sight to the trap and can&rsquo;t be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}. This works generally like @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Danger Sense]{Danger Sense} but applies only to mechanical and magical traps.</p>\n<p>If the trap is detected and may be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evaded}, the rogue and anyone she warns ignores 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evasion} penalties to do so. If the trap can&rsquo;t normally be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evaded}, anyone warned may @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Evasion]{Evade} at the usual &minus;2 penalty.</p>\n<p><strong>Disarming Traps:</strong> Rogues with Trap Sense ignore up 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} penalties when attempting to disarm traps</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Rogue"}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gMhsswekqyI1hslR"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Kc4urAwceZI1QvLz","name":"Crowns (cp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":6,"weight":0.02,"price":0.01,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.fBZcb1EdAbO4EEOl"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-copper.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"kBnwLV74s7sITL5l","name":"Dragons (pp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":22,"weight":0.02,"price":10,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.33dBhsz0KCjjGHYe"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-platinum.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"brg4P66QdAjzCbLb","name":"Galifars (gp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":12,"weight":0.02,"price":1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.CbrYbcaa5bTV8Wnd"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-gold.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"HHZckOHEB2J5m3Rd","name":"Sovereigns (sp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":8,"weight":0.02,"price":0.1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EeHD4BJl6bS0eE4D"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-silver.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"cXibHn74uDVgX2OX","name":"Language (Gnomish)","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.udHxlHKPSrGG5QjZ"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/talk.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"RU5yr2Sa2B2QW7h1","name":"Thief","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Thieves specialize in deceit, treachery, and acrobatics. They can be invaluable where traps must be detected, walls must be climbed, and locks must be picked. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Thieves know how to use protrusions on walls and window ledges to climb the tallest of buildings, scampering through streets and back alleys like cats. They add +1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} rolls made to climb in urban areas. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Thieves also know how to use the dark areas between the streetlights of cities to conceal their movements, and add +1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} rolls when in an urban environment. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Finally, these rogues are&mdash;not surprisingly&mdash; adept at @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} itself, adding +1 to those rolls in all circumstances.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+, Stealth d6+, Thievery d6+"}},"sort":1700001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_4wzuhu4mbqi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.lp2OQZTT3w4NuITR"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ERX2Ug5re24REN9b","name":"Quick","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Quick characters have lightning-fast reflexes and a cool head. Whenever you are dealt an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} of Five or lower, you may discard it and draw again until you get a card higher than Five.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Characters} with both the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Level Headed]{Level Headed} and Quick Edges first draw their additional card and choose which to take. If that card is a Five or less, the Quick Edge may be used to draw a replacement until it&rsquo;s Six or higher.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"sort":1800001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9dc4ijzy8uh","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.XHguf9iQ3N9yHN4Z"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"bdjqlBAv6NRQTQ8b","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1900001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/punch.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"bGUA0AB3nNlylZYx","name":"Taunt","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Taunt attacks a person&rsquo;s pride through ridicule, cruel jests, or oneupmanship.</p>\n<p>Taunt is an opposed roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{resisted} by the opponent&rsquo;s Smarts. In combat, this is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} means the defender backs down, slinks away, or starts a fight. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} might leave the victim cowed for the remainder of the scene, or make her storm out of the area fuming or even in tears, or attack her tormentor recklessly (perhaps with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Attack]{Wild Attack} on the first round of combat).</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} means the target is immune to this character&rsquo;s Taunts for the remainder of the encounter.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2000001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.tjzr8dGPHLLWZdRI"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/confrontation.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"KXhuPQ0xxxBAGZ6d","name":"Thievery","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Lockpicking, safecracking, picking pockets, sleight of hand, setting and disabling traps and similar acts of misdirection, sabotage, subterfuge, and manipulation are called Thievery.</p>\n<p>If used to pick a lock, crack a safe, disable a trap, or perform a simple unopposed action, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} opens or disables the device, and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} does it in less time, without tripping alarms, or whatever else the GM feels is appropriate.</p>\n<p>Sleight of hand, hiding or planting an item, or picking a pocket require a simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}. If foes are actively watching the character, Thievery is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice}.</p>\n<p>The Game Master should assign @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalties} for particularly difficult circumstances. Picking a heavy padlock might have a &minus;4 penalty, while hiding a revolver in bulky winter clothing might grant a +1 bonus. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} typically means the character is spotted or it takes too much time (after which the character can try again). A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} typically sets off the trap, alerts the victim, or jams the device so that it must be opened or interacted with in a different way.</p>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Using Thievery on an electronic device, such as a keypad, is limited by the thief&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Electronics]{Electronics} skill. Use the lowest of the two skills.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2100001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wZbyJkisWIfmcZNt"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/lockpicks.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"LWnLBtt4nX3VfK3h","name":"Performance","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>A good entertainer can lift the spirits, rally a crowd to action, or simply earn a few bucks from the locals. Specifics depend on the situation, setting, and how well the character is known in the area.</p>\n<p>Performance covers singing, acting, playing an instrument, or similar tasks that require an audience to appreciate.</p>\n<p><strong>Raising Funds:</strong> The amount of money a character can raise by performing is extremely subjective, but as a general rule a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} performance raises 20% of the setting's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Starting Funds} with a success and 30% with a raise. The GM can multiply this amount by the performer's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} if she feels it's appropriate. These numbers work for typical performers who might be known in a small establishment or area. Larger performances can greatly boost the performer's fee, but also require more time, energy, and setup.</p>\n<p><strong>Deception: </strong>Performance can be used instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} if the character is attempting to deceive, bluff, or disguise herself and the GM agrees it makes sense in the context of the situation.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2200001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.SJ1nN0CmOHNQhfOQ"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/drama-masks.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"FNMyUzYzaDhYyEXy","name":"Quirk (leaves lead coin with symbol at thefts)","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This individual has some minor foible that is usually humorous but can occasionally cause him real trouble. A swashbuckler may always try to slash his initials on his foes, a dwarf may brag constantly about his culture, or a snobby d&eacute;butante might not eat, drink, or socialize with the lower class, for example.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":2300001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.y0lUBhYHhl2LdjZZ"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"uAVbmkv20M6KyscL","name":"Pacifist","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">(MINOR OR MAJOR)</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Your hero absolutely despises violence. Minor pacifism means he only fights when given no other choice and never allows the killing of prisoners or other defenseless victims.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Major Pacifists won&rsquo;t fight living characters under </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">any </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">circumstances. They may defend themselves, but won&rsquo;t do anything to permanently harm sapient, living creatures. They may use @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Nonlethal Damage]{nonlethal} methods, but only in self-defense or the defense of others. Note that undeniably evil creatures, undead, demons, and the like are fair game even for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Major} Pacifists!</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":2400001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.WcvOUeVNBLe4aDvV"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"JiEurzgf5J0q88Us","name":"Overconfident","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">There&rsquo;s nothing out there your hero can&rsquo;t defeat. At least that&rsquo;s what he thinks. He believes he can do most anything and never wants to retreat from a challenge. He&rsquo;s not suicidal, but he certainly takes on more than common sense dictates.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"sort":2500001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.1qgPyuagmvWDVoHR"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"P4hy6dWb4I6CPCPu","name":"Rabble-Rouser","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This instigator knows how to rile up several enemies at once.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Once per turn, a character with this Edge can make a social </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test} </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} or<br />@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} against all enemies in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. The targets must be able to see and<br />hear the hero clearly. Each defender resists and is affected by the </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Test </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">separately.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Spirit d8+"}},"sort":2600001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1nt716ztwfa","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Social Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.WJdZ5HttGFp7lpEp"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"3X0LcQVP9hjQIquC","name":"Rapier","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} +1</p>\n</div>","notes":"Parry +1","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":25,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":700001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.yPRx9vOmWYL1MgBF"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/stiletto.svg","effects":[{"_id":"2K9kgErsmseqr2AH","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.parry.modifier","value":"1","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/stiletto.svg","label":"Rapier Parry Bonus","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"H3TE1hjnQU3xw6xH","name":"Knife of Throwing","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The dagger carries the following enchantments:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Distance]{Distance}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Returning]{Returning}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Throwing]{Throwing}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":8302,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Athletics","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{"z40wgz5em8":{"name":"Fighting (melee)","type":"skill","rof":null,"skillMod":"","skillOverride":"Fighting","shotsUsed":null}}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"4/8/16","rof":"1","ap":"1","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":800001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ImZOGC5RY4Z3ZxMy"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/weapons/stiletto.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"eOMJ0Zx8INnxBUF3","name":"Leather Armor","type":"armor","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":5,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"minStr":"d4","armor":1,"isNaturalArmor":false,"locations":{"head":false,"torso":true,"arms":true,"legs":false}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PRPRsNmJyfvoy6hH"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/leather-armor.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"1OC3JsBR9pPwNfX5","name":"Leather Pants","type":"armor","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":3,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"minStr":"d4","armor":1,"isNaturalArmor":false,"locations":{"head":false,"torso":false,"arms":false,"legs":true}},"sort":700000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.XWQhf1v5NNWGhX4p"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/armored-pants.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"qgSQbV2lwW8dXN7Y","name":"Thieves' Tools","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This set of tools includes a small file, a set of lock picks, a small mirror mounted on a metal handle, a set of narrow-bladed scissors, and a pair of pliers.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":25,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.bhqKMj8ohGSLzkU3"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/lockpicks.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"K6KznpsK65QYRbik","name":"Climber's Kit","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>You can use the climber's kit as an action to anchor yourself; when you do, you can't fall more than 8\"/24 feet from the point where you anchored yourself, and you can't climb more than 8\"/24 feet away from that point without undoing the anchor.</p>\n<p><strong>Components. </strong>A climber's kit includes special pitons, boot tips, gloves, and a harness.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":5,"price":30,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":1600000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.6oD83M3OYUsmhMKS"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/light-backpack.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Ani0cuKfc7B17Ql8","name":"Low Light Vision","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Low Light Vision ignores penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim and Dark Illumination} (but not @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Pitch Darkness}).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.OL3T8otZVCkOoir3"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/angry-eyes.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"zDZ9yUk0bLhsZ5Q5","name":"Gnome Magic","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Gnomes are inherently magical creatures. They can cast cantrips as if they knew each of the following powers:&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{light}</em>,&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sound/Silence]{sound}</em>,&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Telekinesis]{telekinesis}</em>, and&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Beast Friend]{beast friend}</em>&nbsp;using their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} (or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} if they have one). They have 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} for activating these cantrips, regained as usual. Gnomes with an Arcane Background or Mystic Power&nbsp; or Dragonmark add their bonus @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} to their pool but must still learn the spells if they wish to cast them normally.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":true},"sort":400000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.wgvTOJ8MnESHB6rQ"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/wizard-face.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"uRjN8XvEEUGyythO","name":"Beast Friend (Cantrips only)","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p>This spell allows an individual to speak with and guide the actions of nature&rsquo;s beasts. The cost to cast is equal to the sum of their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} (minimum 1 per creature). Controlling five @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Dog / Wolf]{wolves} (Size &minus;1) costs 5 points (remember the minimum cost of 1), for example. Controlling a rhino (Size 5) costs 5 points.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} means the creatures obey simple commands, like a well-trained dog. They attack foes and endanger their lives for their master. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the arcane skill roll means the beasts are more obedient. They won&rsquo;t kill themselves but overcome their natural fears to follow their orders.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Swarm]{Swarms} can also be controlled. Small Swarms cost 1 point, Medium Swarms cost 2, and Large Swarms cost 3.</p>\n<p><em> Beast friend</em> works only on natural creatures with animal intelligence, not humanoids, and has no effect on conjured, magical, or otherwise &ldquo;unnatural&rdquo; animals.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Bestiarium (+2):</strong> The caster may affect magical and mythical beasts with animal intelligence.</li>\n<li><strong>Duration (+1):</strong> The base Duration increases to 30 minutes per rank.</li>\n<li><strong>Mind Rider (+1):</strong> The caster can communicate and sense through any of the beasts they've befriended.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Smarts","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"0","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"The caster concentrates and gestures with his hands.","arcane":"Gnome Magic","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":100001,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.YL9RGHSkkkLJEF2f"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ftDcM0Gfulh0ojx0","name":"Candle Light (Cantrips only)","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evocation}</p>\n<p><em>Light </em>creates bright @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{illumination} in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}. With a raise, the light can be focused into a 5&Prime; (10 yard) beam as well.</p>\n<p><em>Darkness </em>blocks @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{illumination}&nbsp;in an area the size of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}, making the area Dark, or Pitch Darkness with a raise (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination}).</p>\n<p>If <em>light </em>and <em>darkness </em>overlap, they create a patch of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim light} (&minus;2).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Area Effect (+2): </strong>The <em>light</em> expands to the caster&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} in radius, with a Range of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} &times;2. The light is sunlight and has the same effect on certain creatures (such as vampires) as natural sunlight.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>True Darkness (+2):</strong> The <em>darkness</em> blocks @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Infravision]{Infravision}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Low Light Vision]{Low Light Vision}, and @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Darkvision]{Darkvision}. It has no effect on magical sight such as <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect arcana}</em>.</li>\n<li><strong>Mobile (+1):</strong> The caster can move the area of effect up to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} die type each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{round} after casting, or attach it to an inanimate object when first cast.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Smarts","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"0","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"Illusionary torch, sunlight, darkness, thick fogs","arcane":"Gnome Magic","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":100001,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gEg0cmKVXZN0LEYt"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"xNqpDzmLq33Kcxov","name":"Minor Sound (Cantrips only)","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Illusion}</p>\n<p><em>Sound </em>mimics any known sound or voice, emanating from a point of origin within @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range} at a volume up to the sound of a loud shout. If used as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}, the defender @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposes} the casting roll with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts}.</p>\n<p><em>Silence </em>does the opposite, muting all sound up to a loud shout within a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}. This subtracts 4 from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls made by those inside the area of effect, as well as anyone trying to hear sounds made from within. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} completely mutes all sound inside the template&mdash;such @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls automatically fail.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Greater Sound/Silence</strong><strong> (+1):</strong> The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} roll made to resist a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test} (or Targeted modifier) is made at &minus;2.</li>\n<li><strong>Mobile (+1):</strong> The caster can move the area of effect up to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} die type each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{round}.</li>\n<li><strong>Targeted (+0):</strong> Instead of casting <em>silence </em>in an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{area of effect}, the caster may instead target individuals in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range} for 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each. Unwilling targets resist with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} (at &minus;2 if the caster gets a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Smarts","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"0","damage":"","range":"Smarts ×5 (sound); Smarts (silence)","duration":"Instant (sound); 5 (silence)","trapping":"Magical effects, a brief ripple in the air, a bell or chime that starts or stops ringing","arcane":"Gnome Magic","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":100001,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.2XWZLvwndmibm5gP"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"31IWGXmD1u4F0Kub","name":"Mage Hand (Cantrips only)","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p><em>Telekinesis </em>is the ability to move objects or creatures (including oneself) with arcane will. It has a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} of d10, or d12 with a raise.</p>\n<p>Unwilling opponents resist the caster&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} with an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll when targeted and at the start of each of their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{turns} afterward until they&rsquo;re released. They can be moved up to the caster&rsquo; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} per turn in any direction, and can be bashed into walls, ceilings, or other obstacles for Str+d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{damage}.</p>\n<p>Dropped creatures suffer @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Falling]{falling damage} as usual.</p>\n<p><strong>Telekinetic Tools</strong>: A caster can wield tools (including weapons) with <em>telekinesis </em>as an action. Use the caster&rsquo;s relevant @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{skill} when attacking in this way (not his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill}).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Power (+3): </strong>The Strength of telekinesis is d12, or d12 + 2 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. Objects weighing 1,000 pounds or more automatically deal @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{Damage} when used as weapons.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Smarts","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"0","damage":"","range":"Smarts x2","duration":"5","trapping":"A wave of the hand, magic wand, steely gaze","arcane":"Gnome Magic","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":100001,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.KLsRF4Gf0QBakUZu"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"XPuoyLlrOmR19OO0","name":"Obsessive (Thievery)","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Gnomes start with a d4 in any one Smarts-related skill.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":true},"sort":400000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.5NAJSxm6K1Vya1aZ"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/wizard-face.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"yRlvVU5YPFs8mlQ8","name":"Unarmed Strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":2700001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/fist.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"PK6AGUvNYgFrADcM","name":"Hard To Kill","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This adventurer has more lives than a herd of cats. He may ignore his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} penalties when making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls to avoid <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Bleeding Out}</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"sort":2800001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bv1geyfk6c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.hpC41I3Bd56WPTu2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Z2ayl0CRCP7c1Fbi","name":"Pouch","type":"gear","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0.5,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":2900001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_u6k9894u4jr","path":"Savage Eberron Equipment#/CF_SEP/Adventuring Gear","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.n59EuO7qRH4FoJsk"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/knapsack.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"kAM5jCb6vSds1AV0","name":"Mirror","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This hand-held mirror is about a foot across. Unlike many higher-quality glass mirrors, this one is made out of polished steel and sturdy enough that you can drop it without risk of breakage.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":10,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":3000001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_u6k9894u4jr","path":"Savage Eberron Equipment#/CF_SEP/Adventuring Gear","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.CoPJpPFKpROcmLFs"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/mirror-mirror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"9ND1PWazJ1AxpmDB","name":"Potion of Major Cat's Eyes","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Bottle of transparent liquid with a dragonflies wing in it.</p>\n<p>The potion duplicates the&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost Trait}</em> power with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} limited to the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} skill.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0.25,"price":200,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":3100001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.aG8iLALe5HgIYntc"},"cf":{"id":"temp_ue2l4pwsojl","path":"Savage Eberron Treasure#/CF_SEP/02.4. Boost Potions","color":"#000000"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/square-bottle.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}}],"effects":[{"_id":"nUR5M658tzCJRWTT","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.parry.modifier","value":"1","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":0},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/stiletto.svg","label":"Rapier Parry Bonus","origin":"Actor.xtIX0GXhOwYbIcaR.Item.3X0LcQVP9hjQIquC","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_2mncjgs233x","path":"Savage Eberron Characters#/CF_SEP/Pregens","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"7nvwZXfADi0JLLbV"}
{"name":"Scholar/Priest of Aureon","type":"character","img":"modules/savage-eberron-bestiary/assets/bestiary/humanoids/human/human-caster-04.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":6,"runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":2,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":0,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>"},"species":{"name":"Human"},"currency":"500","wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{"Cleric":{"value":10,"max":10}},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":3,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":4,"rank":"Seasoned","details":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Creation: </strong>Charismatic, Cleric, Smarts d8, Spirit d8</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>(N) Edge:</strong> Common Bond</li>\n<li><strong>(N) Edge:</strong> Calculating</li>\n<li><strong>(N) Edge:</strong> New Powers: <em>blind, sanctuary</em></li>\n<li><strong>(S) Edge:</strong> Work the Room</li>\n<li><strong>(S) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(S) : </strong></li>\n<li><strong>(S) : </strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) : </strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n</ol>\n</div>"},"bennies":{"value":1,"max":3},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Cleric","displayName":0,"img":"modules/savage-eberron-bestiary/assets/bestiary_tokens/humanoids/human/human-caster-04.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":"JxY7W97dZ1Rh7QwD","actorLink":true,"disposition":1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"gso7NeJMXpdXlU6X","name":"Untrained","type":"skill","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":600000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skill.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"RMmVU7ormCp2MOqN","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":700000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sAig03GZiFKqBX7p"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/jump-across.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BkQxvPAlZLOJY7OZ","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":800000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.8N1uMThntsjaUPem"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/gift-of-knowledge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GN2DOxOtwyROzNWZ","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":900000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xOmuCR92Ys9jD5vg"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/convince.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8qCrEiZTjPRuJ2Qq","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1000000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.z9FmdFVGOOW2kufm"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/hidden.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"hzQAaO1x5wYjovWb","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.yvw9bMgsrWQXuZN2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ruBTbGRqlMoy2uSz","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/talk.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GQMFWtp6IWJ6kqTY","name":"Crowns (cp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":7,"weight":0.02,"price":0.01,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.fBZcb1EdAbO4EEOl"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-copper.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"6IZsePloV317RsUb","name":"Dragons (pp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":31,"weight":0.02,"price":10,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.33dBhsz0KCjjGHYe"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-platinum.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"HNsCemxmNdyU8oWj","name":"Galifars (gp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":25,"weight":0.02,"price":1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.CbrYbcaa5bTV8Wnd"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-gold.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Mccx8d95umBCcVgu","name":"Sovereigns (sp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":12,"weight":0.02,"price":0.1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EeHD4BJl6bS0eE4D"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-silver.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ZZrY9N4uTnYeHmFJ","name":"Unarmed Strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":1600001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/fist.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"viVI0A8hOKiphIYf","name":"Hard To Kill","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This adventurer has more lives than a herd of cats. He may ignore his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} penalties when making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls to avoid <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Bleeding Out}</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"sort":1700001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bv1geyfk6c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.hpC41I3Bd56WPTu2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"jrvMZhsMcdhFRduU","name":"Skilled (Common Knowledge and Religion)","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Humans are innovative and adapable. They start with a d4 in any two skills based on their experiences, education, training, or culture. If the chosen skill is a core skill, skill), it starts at d6 and the skill&rsquo;s maximum increases to d12+1.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":100000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1CTGE9yVU7dIWPJN"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/monk-face.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"iygXIDXf272clsMB","name":"Religion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Religion reflects knowledge about ancient religions, mythic history, eccelsiastic tradition, holy symbols, undead, as well as details about all the religions of Eberron.</p>\n<p>A successful Religion roll reveals basic information about a topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1000001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.HdShAatiWIBLgv8z"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/skills/church.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"rUfpBYZyCz68PI9f","name":"Faith","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p>Faith is the arcane skill required for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Background (Miracles)]{Arcane Background (Miracles)}.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1800001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.YI5rxzYzsqXwAo9A"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/prayer.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BTSj5tbVouVujozb","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1900001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/punch.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"NrTM96pJqsvuVh6l","name":"Cosmology","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The planes of Eberron affect every aspect of the material world. This skill covers knowledge of the astral, ethereal, and shadow planes, the thirteen orbiting planes, their properties, planar influences, native inhabitants, and manifest zones connected to them on the material plane.</p>\n<p>For spells and magical effects related to the planes, use the Arcana Skill.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":300001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lZeftp1QnvCFzY8D"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/skills/solar-system.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"DFLpnwGHiR51HCea","name":"Lore","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Lore reflects knowledge and your ability to recall bits of information about history, archaeology, different Ages, legends, other continents, literature, song, poetry, and similar fields. This would also include knowledge about the more common races of the worlds.</p>\n<p>If an explorer wants to remember when the Dhakaani empire collapsed or know when the Qualabrin were destroyed on Xen'drik, this is the skill to have.</p>\n<p>A successful Lore roll reveals basic information about a topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron replaces Academics</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":700001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E0BVumGwbaczoPjD"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/skills/bookshelf.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"YTfpminrlm44ELUA","name":"Riding","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p>Riding allows a hero to mount, control, and ride any beast or beast-drawn vehicle common to his setting. This includes horses, camels, dragons, wagons, chariots, and the like. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mounted Combat]{Mounted Combat}.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2000001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.DHKzenDEPdjw3X2u"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/saddle.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"LR33SUGtELhcsonu","name":"Shooting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Shooting covers all attempts to hit a target with a ranged weapon such as a bow, pistol, or rocket launcher (thrown weapons use @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}). See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for details on ranged combat.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2100001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sOHfVvBDhe3Oy3r1"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/crosshair.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"VMFUkSJqLx4Opodv","name":"Arcana","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Arcana reflects knowledge about spells, artifacts, magic items, eldritch symbols, magical traditions, dragons, forbidden lore, magical beasts, analyzing alchemical compounds and other ritual paraphernalia, translate magical runes, guess what spell was cast based on physical evidence left behind, etc.</p>\n<p>A successful Arcana roll reveals basic information about a magical topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lr6HSv7xgo5Dsp1N"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/skills/spell-book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"H4PoLug1Fi82S3v0","name":"Cleric (Aureon - Knowledge)","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In faith and the miracles of the divine, many find a greater purpose. Called to serve powers beyond most mortal understanding, all priests provide for the spiritual needs of their people. More than mere preachers, clerics serve as emissaries of their gods. These ecclesiastics vow to spread the tenets, knowledge, and truth of their faith.</p>\n<p>While clerics of different faiths may share similar abilities, they prove as different from one another as the divinities they serve. Some offer healing and redemption, others judge law and truth, and still others spread conflict and corruption.</p>\n<p>Clerics gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Cleric)]{Arcane Background (Cleric)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Channel Energy]{Channel Energy}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Vow of Faith]{Vow of Faith}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Faith d4+"}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ouw6W4r3rYVJQIqG"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"J5WkS6PbpXih8yj6","name":"Vow of Faith","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Clerics have a major vow to serve their deity. Those who wish to draw energy from divine sources must uphold the principles of their @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Domains]{Domains}.</p>\n<p>If the cleric violates their deity's trust (DM's call) the cleric subtracts 2 from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Faith]{Faith} rolls for a week. Truly sacrilegious acts might rob her of her powers entirely until she atones in some way.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"sort":700000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.YwWXS95TWbqBIyLE"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"pha2PRx5UyZL3zNT","name":"Channel Energy","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Clerics can cast the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}</em> power at a Range of Spirit rather than Touch. Their&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}</em>&nbsp;power also has the Additional Recipients Power Modifier, allowing them to heal nearby allies at the cost of one extra Power Point each.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Cleric"}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VO5siJEofAatX9Hf"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"l8VHsPcxcbuXEVaW","name":"Arcane Background (Cleric)","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Cleric)]{Arcane Background (Cleric)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"sort":600000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E6yOW6PfzFWgHuPD"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ALti7AB4O36xo2Fl","name":"Hands of the Host","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Healing </em>removes @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} less than an hour old. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} removes one Wound, and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} removes two. The power may be cast additional times to remove additional Wounds within that hour and as long as the healer has enough @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}.</p>\n<p>For @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras}, the GM must first determine if the ally is still alive (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{Aftermath}). If so, a successful arcane skill roll returns the ally to action (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} if it matters).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Greater Healing (+10):</strong> <em>Greater healing</em> can restore any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}, including those more than an hour old.</li>\n<li><strong>Crippling Injuries (+20):</strong> The power can heal a permanent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Injury Table]{Crippling Injury} (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitation}). This requires an hour of preparation and only one casting is permitted per injury. If it @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails}, this caster cannot <em>heal </em>that particular injury (but somoene else may try). If successful, the subject is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Exhausted} for 24 hours.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Mass Healing (+2/+3):</strong> For a +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}, healing affects all allies within a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} centered on the caster (or a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template} for +3).</li>\n<li><strong>Neutralize Poison or Disease (+1):</strong> A successful <em>healing&nbsp;</em>roll negates any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Poison]{poison} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Disease]{disease}. If the poison or disease has a bonus or penalty associated with it, the modifier applies to the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll as well.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Faith","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Touching the victim with a holy symbol","arcane":"Cleric","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":2000000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.L3HoTKUKSXvZNAqa"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"93ZgncVvSlf0bdqV","name":"Blessing of Aureon","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Abjuration}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} with arcane protection means hostile powers suffer a &minus;2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalty} (&minus;4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}) to affect this character.</p>\n<p>If the power causes harm, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{damage} is also reduced a like amount. Arcane Protection stacks with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Arcane Resistance]{Arcane Resistance} should the recipient have both!</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}&nbsp;each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Arcane Protection (+2):&nbsp;</strong> Hostile powers suffer a &minus;4 penalty (&minus;6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Faith","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Words pulled from a book floating around the target","arcane":"Cleric","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":200000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.hDK8ufDJ5YtTLUwf"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"2TeWizIqGWRfckVg","name":"Curse of Aureon","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p><em>Confusion </em>confounds all targets in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, making them either @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted or Vulnerable}, or both with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. The same effect applies to all those affected. These states are removed at the end of the victims&rsquo; next turn as usual.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+0/+1):</strong>The caster can focus the <em>confusion </em>to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Small Blast Template} for no extra cost, or a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template} for +1.</li>\n<li><strong>★ Greater Confusion (+2):</strong> On a success, targets are @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} in addition to being @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} (or both with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}). <em>Confusion </em>is a non-damaging effect and cannot cause a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} on an already @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} target.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Faith","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Scattering of words flying from a book","arcane":"Cleric","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":1000000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.fffVpphTGKxBvT6q"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"eeoZafwznr7CbxdB","name":"Work The Room","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Your hero&rsquo;s words don&rsquo;t just inspire those they&rsquo;re directed at&mdash;they often inspire others as well. Once per turn, you can use Work the Room to roll an additional skill die when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Supporting} with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance}. The additional die Supports any other ally who can see or hear your hero, and applies to their next action, whatever it may be.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"sort":2200001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1nt716ztwfa","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Social Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.U2pALBBG9geRa2S6"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"wxOFBmSUMgcDo84Q","name":"Protection of the Host","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p>Any evil creature attempting a damaging attack that targets or affects the recipient must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll (at &minus;2 if cast with a raise). If the roll fails, the creature loses that action.</p>\n<p>If the caster (or any allies affected by the Area Effect modifier) attempt to harm anyone (evil or otherwise), <em>sanctuary </em>terminates instantly.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Pathfinder</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+2/+3):</strong> For +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Strong (+1):</strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} rolls by the creature are made at &minus;2 (&minus;4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Faith","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"5","trapping":"Presenting holy symbol in prayer","arcane":"Cleric","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":3100000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gDxGCS5pT4gRjwhS"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"86jZstya2KG4hPoN","name":"Blight of Aureon","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>School:&nbsp;@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Necromancy}</p>\n<p>Those affected by this malicious power suffer blurred vision or near-complete blindness with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} means the victim suffers a&nbsp;&minus;2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalty} to all actions requiring sight, or &minus;4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p>The victim automatically tries to shake off the effect with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of his following turns.&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} removes 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalties}, and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} removes the effect entirely.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+2/+3): </strong>For +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}&nbsp;the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (+1): </strong>The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll to shake of the effect is made at &minus;2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Faith","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Bright flash of light from holy symbol","arcane":"Cleric","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":500000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Ps7RDR7CjJWVOVWQ"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"rkKwq2fS3kUK27hl","name":"Common Bond","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Selfless heroes and determined leaders know their greatest strength often comes from their companions, and are willing to give some of their own fortune, fate, or luck to support them.<br />A character with this Edge may freely give her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} to any other character she can communicate with. The player should explan what form this takes, from a quick shout of encouragement to a welcome pat on the back</span> </p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"sort":3200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1nt716ztwfa","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Social Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.8o2F1b4DT8onc9Xt"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"XUV35ELmkg8VKPon","name":"Calculating","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A few seconds to study your foe&rsquo;s actions gives your hero a major advantage. When his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} is a Five or less, he ignores up to 2 points of penalties on one action that turn, which can include @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action}, cover, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range}, and even @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} penalties</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+"}},"sort":3300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bv1geyfk6c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.glTPSIKamM7Kz5ex"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"a6s0nFpxyOdbzKtN","name":"Charismatic","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Your hero is likable for some reason. She may be trustworthy or kind, or might just exude confidence and goodwill. You get one free reroll on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"sort":3400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9dc4ijzy8uh","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.t9CHSlLks9nQ8lIv"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"nmkzF6Nc9r10w38X","name":"Outfit, Scholar's","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Perfect for a scholar, this outfit includes a robe, a belt, a cap, soft shoes, and possibly a cloak.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":5,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":700000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VLjyDDvhoHCfjNa4"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/robe.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"lC0aFQ4MWnxFlrQ1","name":"Leather Greaves","type":"armor","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":5,"price":10,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"minStr":"d6","armor":2,"isNaturalArmor":false,"locations":{"head":false,"torso":false,"arms":false,"legs":true}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.8tmZCXDGiG5fZEf5"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/armored-pants.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"2D4iLFscPHz5PGJp","name":"Studded Leather","type":"armor","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This leather armor is reinforced with metal studs and sometimes small metal plates, providing most of the flexibility of leather armor with more robust protection.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":10,"price":40,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"minStr":"d6","armor":2,"isNaturalArmor":