:</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n</ol>\n</div>"},"bennies":{"value":3,"max":3},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":true},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Monk","displayName":0,"img":"modules/savage-eberron-bestiary/assets/bestiary_tokens/humanoids/warforged/warforged-monk-01.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":"b9WRXx62ihYSWgFM","actorLink":true,"disposition":1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"gso7NeJMXpdXlU6X","name":"Untrained","type":"skill","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":600000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skill.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"RMmVU7ormCp2MOqN","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":700000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sAig03GZiFKqBX7p"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/jump-across.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8qCrEiZTjPRuJ2Qq","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1000000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.z9FmdFVGOOW2kufm"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/hidden.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"hzQAaO1x5wYjovWb","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.yvw9bMgsrWQXuZN2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ruBTbGRqlMoy2uSz","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/talk.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GQMFWtp6IWJ6kqTY","name":"Crowns (cp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":13,"weight":0.02,"price":0.01,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.fBZcb1EdAbO4EEOl"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-copper.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"6IZsePloV317RsUb","name":"Dragons (pp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":25,"weight":0.02,"price":10,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.33dBhsz0KCjjGHYe"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-platinum.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"HNsCemxmNdyU8oWj","name":"Galifars (gp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":24,"weight":0.02,"price":1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.CbrYbcaa5bTV8Wnd"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-gold.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Mccx8d95umBCcVgu","name":"Sovereigns (sp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":26,"weight":0.02,"price":0.1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EeHD4BJl6bS0eE4D"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-silver.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"viVI0A8hOKiphIYf","name":"Hard To Kill","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This adventurer has more lives than a herd of cats. He may ignore his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} penalties when making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls to avoid <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Bleeding Out}</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"sort":1700001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bv1geyfk6c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.hpC41I3Bd56WPTu2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"iRFSZCugYiKcuewF","name":"Living Construct","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Warforged]{Warforged} are living constructs made from organic and inorganic matter and are capable of emotions and conscious thought. They do not need to breathe, eat, or drink, and are immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Poison]{poison} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Disease]{disease}. Wounds must be mended via the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Repair]{repair}</em> power or the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-skills.Repair]{Repair} skill. Each attempt takes one hour per current @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} level and ignores the &ldquo;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{Golden Hour}&rdquo;.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":600000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.DQk7szYIGidEEbGT"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/cyborg-face.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"SoyQs1Dub4dIbwkO","name":"Loyal","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Warforged]{Warforged} are trained to protect their allies in combat, and will always be the first to come to their rescue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":300000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.P0qe44HWyc24Euxt"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/cyborg-face.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"X8AlkKIpu1gfWBn9","name":"Outsider (Warforged)","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>With a history of being dedicated soldiers of war, warforged have difficulty blending into post-war Khorvaire. Most non-warforged strongly dislike the sight of warforged as they stand as living reminders of the horror that was the Last War. As such, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Warforged]{warforged} have &minus;2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls when interacting with non-warforged and are often treated with less rights that others.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"sort":500000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.oZRSCllGl3T8QKRT"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/cyborg-face.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Zg8EC3JUWljG9RAU","name":"Steel Fists","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":null,"weight":null,"price":null,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d6","range":"","rof":"","ap":"","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":800000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GxVNY83rIxMpxCqB"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/mailed-fist.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"OUStAypJLhbaYdvg","name":"Specialize Design(Notice)","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Warforged are typically designed for specific purposes. They start with a d4 in any skill based on their experiences, education, training. If the chosen skill is a core skill, it starts at d6 and the skill's maximum increases to d12+1.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":600000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.pFnuHvubHfLzH3cV"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/cyborg-face.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"fWasjsl7rTkDD9jj","name":"Heroic","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This noble soul never says no to a person in need. She doesn&rsquo;t have to be happy about it,but she always comes to the rescue of those she feels can&rsquo;t help themselves. She&rsquo;s the first </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">one to run into a burning building, usually agrees to hunt monsters for little or no pay, and is generally a pushover for a sob story.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"sort":1800001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.Yv7grUtMJomyg2ek"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Urs4LIBqNimIYCch","name":"Adamantine Body","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The warforged was created from a specially designed line made with adamantine giving him +4 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor}&nbsp;instead of the normal +2 from Composite Plating.</p>\n<p><strong>Special:</strong> This Edge must be taken during character creation.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Warforged"}},"sort":1700000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.QcyEinYFMpf7uquT"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/cyborg-face.svg","effects":[{"_id":"N93Ig1bYA5YgBt7D","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.armor","value":"4","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/breastplate.svg","label":"Adamantine Plating","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"YjqLmnVo33q8hpyY","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1900001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/punch.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Imyix3jEBJsSScJF","name":"Intimidation","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Intimidation is the art of frightening an opponent so that he backs down, reveals information, or flees.</p>\n<p>Intimidation is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} resisted by the opponent&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. In combat, this is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}. Out of combat, a successful roll means the foe backs down for the most part, reveals some information, or slinks away when the opportunity presents itself.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} might mean he backs down for the remainder of the scene, spills all the beans, or runs away as fast as he can.</p>\n<p>In or out of combat, a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} means the target is immune to this character&rsquo;s Intimidation attempts for the remainder of this encounter!</p>\n<p><strong>Networking:</strong> Intimidation can also be used as a &ldquo;macro&rdquo; skill to simulate several hours of working the streets. See&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}&nbsp;to see how to crack some heads for favors or information.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2000001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.RrgAZp50CgQyyY6w"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/arrest.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"4J3Mc4rpxWZ3Ny9C","name":"Repair","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Repair is the ability to craft, take apart and/or fix mechanical gadgets, vehicles, weapons, and constructs including warforged.</p>\n<p>How long a Repair roll takes is up to the DM and the complexity of the task. Success means the item is functional. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the Repair roll halves the time required.</p>\n<p><strong>Constructs: </strong>Repair can be used in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{Healing} of warforged and other constructs @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds}.</p>\n<p><strong>Crafting:&nbsp;</strong>Adventurers sometimes take time to create items from raw materials using appropriate tools. Creating an item requires appropriate raw materials costing half the item's total cost. Making something is usually resolved as an extended skill check, with each skill roll representing roughly a day's work, though this may be smaller for particularly simple jobs.</p>\n<p>The number of successes required and modifiers depend on the complexity, size, and cost of the item to be created, as well as the availability of suitable plans and tools. A critical failure on a skill roll means the work has been ruined and the raw materials wasted.</p>\n<p><strong>Tools:</strong> Characters suffer a minor penalty (&ndash;1 to &ndash;2) to their roll if they don't have access to basic tools, or a major penalty (&ndash;3 to &ndash;4) if the device requires specialized equipment.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Modified for Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VBAYsBHznEUKcaNv"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/skills/anvil-impact.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"71OOkaQZzOPFE47A","name":"Religion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Religion reflects knowledge about ancient religions, mythic history, eccelsiastic tradition, holy symbols, undead, as well as details about all the religions of Eberron.</p>\n<p>A successful Religion roll reveals basic information about a topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1000001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.HdShAatiWIBLgv8z"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/skills/church.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"MtGFq1NmpIWFjg6P","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2100001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.8N1uMThntsjaUPem"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/gift-of-knowledge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"1piUHcWo9TkUh0vl","name":"Survival","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Survival allows a character to find food, water, or shelter in hostile environments. It can also be used to navigate wilderness environments, figure out which plants are good to eat and which aren&rsquo;t, and so on.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} Survival roll provides enough food and water for one person for one day; or five people with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p>More detailed information on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hunger]{Hunger} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Thirst]{Thirst} can be found under @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hazards]{Hazards} section.</p>\n<p><strong>Tracking: </strong>Survival can also be used to detect and follow tracks. Each roll generally covers following the tracks for one mile, but the GM should adjust this as needed for specific circumstances.</p>\n<p>The Game Master should assign a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{bonus or penalty} based on the target, environment, and time. Tracking a large group that recently passed through a snow-covered area might grant a bonus of +4, while following a single person over rocks and streams after more than a day incurs a &minus;4 penalty.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2200001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.15aEAJjDEjQy4fHF"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/camping-tent.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BDXsiiLKT8dA7Fs9","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2300001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xOmuCR92Ys9jD5vg"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/convince.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Y9W5cYGiHvNimHJF","name":"Monk","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>For the truly exemplary, martial prowess transcends the battlefield&mdash;it is a lifestyle, a doctrine, a state of mind. Such warrior-artists search out methods of battle beyond swords and shields, finding weapons within themselves as lethal as any blade.</p>\n<p>These monks (so called since they adhere to ancient philosophies and strict martial disciplines) elevate their bodies to become weapons of war. Monks tread a path of discipline and balance &mdash;in mind, breath, and body.</p>\n<p>Monks gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Monk Armor Restriction (Light)]{Monk Armor Restriction (Light)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Stunning Fist]{Stunning Fist}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Unarmed Strike]{Unarmed Strike}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d6+, Spirit d6+, Fighting d6+"}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.U62vOqX3yBtKGfAC"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"cUCDMa5LUQHO4PVH","name":"Monk Armor Restriction (Light)","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Monks must be&nbsp; unhindered to perform their complex maneuvers. They subtract 4 from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility-based} skill rolls when wearing medium, or heavy armor, or using&nbsp; medium, or heavy shields.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":400000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.udpT3dRwW59mLzPb"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"mEE3qqRmwNV5s4JB","name":"Stunning Fist","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>When a monk hits a target with an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Unarmed Strike]{Unarmed Strike} and scores a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, he may make the foe @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted or Vulnerable}. This occurs even if the victim takes no damage or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soaks} it (the states are applied after the victim attempts to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Soak Rolls]{Soak}).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Monk"}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.hqiESsBHREAShf7l"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"LTSQ3kKSBET2FI28","name":"Unarmed Strike","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Monks cause Str+d4 damage with their hands, feet, or other @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Natural Weapons]{Natural Weapons} (if inhuman and have such appendages).</p>\n<p>If the monk already has a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} damage die from Claws (available to some races), or the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Brawler]{Brawler} Edge, increase the damage a die type for each.</p>\n<p>Monks can apply the benefit of the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Trademark Weapon]{Trademark Weapon} Edge to their unarmed attacks.</p>\n<p>Monks always count as armed. Some use regular weapons in their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Off-Hand Attacks]{off-hand}, but abilities that refer to their Unarmed Strike apply only to unarmed attacks as defined above.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Barbarian"}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.j1AoAS24yKcKAO1e"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"f2YqB5w8oV8PiW29","name":"First Strike","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Once per round, as long as he&rsquo;s not @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned},</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"> the hero gets a free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack against a foe immediately after he moves into @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach}. (See</span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\"> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Free Attacks]{Free Attacks}</span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">)</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"sort":2400001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bv1geyfk6c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.4ue5lRCW1toPyzWO"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"R9xsspWu0CCMW1x0","name":"Quick","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Quick characters have lightning-fast reflexes and a cool head. Whenever you are dealt an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} of Five or lower, you may discard it and draw again until you get a card higher than Five.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Characters} with both the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Level Headed]{Level Headed} and Quick Edges first draw their additional card and choose which to take. If that card is a Five or less, the Quick Edge may be used to draw a replacement until it&rsquo;s Six or higher.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"sort":2500001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9dc4ijzy8uh","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.XHguf9iQ3N9yHN4Z"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"1nDIlVWwQ1DHjfZv","name":"Mystic Powers (Monk)","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action, the monk can invoke one of the following \"ki\" powers: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait}</em> (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Deflection]{deflection}</em>,&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}</em>&nbsp;and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Sloth/Speed]{speed}</em>. All are self only, but the monk gains no benefit from the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Limitation}.</p>\n<p>The monk has 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} that recharge normally. He automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} for an additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}. He may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired.</p>\n<p>Mystic Powers doesn&rsquo;t grant access to Edges requiring an Arcane Background. If the monk also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges, abilities, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} can be used with Mystic Powers (and vice-versa).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Monk"}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1xV7bxE50XIiA8JF"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"1QkbjR43TWi4905h","name":"Focus","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation/Necromancy}</p>\n<p><strong>Limitation:</strong> Boost only (Agility, Athletics, Fighting and Stealth only).</p>\n<p>This power allows a character to increase or decrease a target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} (attribute or skill).</p>\n<p><em>Boosting </em>an ally&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} increases the selected Trait one die type, or two with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, for five rounds.</p>\n<p><em>Lowering </em>an enemy&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} has a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Powers]{Duration} of Instant and lowers the selected attribute or skill a die type with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}, or two with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} (to a minimum of d4). A victim automatically tries to shake off the effect with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of his following turns.&nbsp;Success improves the effect one die type, and a raise removes the effect entirely.</p>\n<p>Additional castings don&rsquo;t stack on a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} (take the highest), but may affect different Traits.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}&nbsp;each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Boost/Lower Trait (+2):&nbsp;</strong> With success, the selected @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} gains a free reroll once per round, or once per action with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. For <em>lower Trait</em> the target applies a &minus;2 penalty to the affected Trait&rsquo;s rolls.</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (+1):</strong> <em>Lower Trait</em> only. The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll to shake off the effect is made at &minus;2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"5","trapping":"Concentration of mind","arcane":"Ki","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":700000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.5p4X7sd96czRfNPc"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"vY7IR19VuWLzQAPt","name":"Deflection","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Abjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Deflection </em>powers work in a variety of ways. Some manifestations actually deflect incoming @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Attacks]{attacks}, others blur the target&rsquo;s form or produce illusionary effects. The end result is always the same, however&mdash;to misdirect incoming melee and missile @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Attacks]{attacks}&nbsp;from the recipient of the power.</p>\n<p>With success, foes must subtract 2 from either melee or ranged attacks (caster&rsquo;s choice). With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the penalty applies to both.</p>\n<p>An attacker who uses a ranged weapon in melee against the recipient suffers the penalty either way.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"5","trapping":"Focus of attention","arcane":"Ki","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":1300000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.MfcTpXsTKk4HRgzb"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"tFWuXSQLFuKIG7wv","name":"Fist of Iron","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p>This power is cast on a weapon of some sort. If it&rsquo;s a ranged weapon, it affects one entire magazine, 20 bolts, shells, or arrows, or one full &ldquo;load&rdquo; of ammunition (the GM determines the exact quantity for unusual weapons). While the power is in effect, the weapon&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{damage} is increased by +2, or +4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p><strong>Limitations:</strong> In the case of smite with a Personal Limitation, &ldquo;Self&rdquo; refers to the specific weapon instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong>&nbsp;The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Smite (+2):</strong> The weapon&rsquo;s damage is increased by +4, or +6 (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{Damage}) with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"5","trapping":"Strengthening of tension in the body","arcane":"Ki","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":3400000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lZnaZ776KQpwRoZq"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"d515cwTPPEADrxjn","name":"Quickness of Body","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p><em>Sloth </em>lessens celerity and coordination while <em>speed </em>increases it. It halves the target&rsquo;s total @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{movement} each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{round} (round up). With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, movement is also an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{action}. The target automatically attempts to shake off the effects of <em>sloth </em>at the end of each of his next turns by making a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} with <em>speed </em>doubles the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{movement} (basic Pace and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{running}). With a&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} the character also ignores the &minus;2 running penalty.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+2/+3):</strong> <em>Sloth</em> only. For +2 points the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li><strong>Quickness (+2):</strong> <em>Speed </em>only. The character's total @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action} penalty each turn is reduced by 2 (she can do two actions at no penalty, or three at &minus;2 each).</li>\n<li><strong>Greater Speed (+2):</strong>&nbsp;<em>Speed&nbsp;</em>only. The recipient&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{running die} isn't rolled&mdash;she gains the maximum result possible.</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (+1):</strong> <em>Sloth</em> only. The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll to shake off <em>sloth's&nbsp;</em>effects is made at &minus;2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"5","trapping":"Blurred motion","arcane":"Ki","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":100001,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GGpr6Jqa61YFJvRd"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"PYhRzeJL4iYplTR1","name":"Backpack","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This leather knapsack has one large pocket that closes with a buckled strap and holds about 2 cubic feet of material. Some may have one or more smaller pockets on the sides.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":5100000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EJwgrkGHCSHskUnO"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/backpack.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"6dFTYYcrdftwk376","name":"Blanket","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This warm, woven blanket has straps so it can be rolled up and tied. Blankets are often used in conjunction with bedrolls to provide additional warmth or a ground cushion.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":0.5,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.pu8kols84h9jj0JF"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/rolled-cloth.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ogP93olQDE8WV2kK","name":"Crowbar","type":"gear","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":800000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.tFYD2qtpz8upwqqy"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/crowbar.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"OsBliJvaXWZggemO","name":"Warforged Repair Kit","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Warforged repair kits contain the same organic and inorganic materials that make up a warforged's body as well specialized tools. The kit has 5 uses and works similarly as a Healer's Kit for healing a Warforged.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":25,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":1300000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.l95Ymz9GM3jsrgy8"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/hand-bag.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"pIymV8vVYocoqWk2","name":"Torch","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>One hour, 4\" radius.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":4,"weight":0.5,"price":0.01,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":4800000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.u95koszLQZ04s69k"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/torch.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"qlicHRUY3bAW4ZUn","name":"Tinderbox","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This small container holds flint, tire steel, and tinder (usually dry cloth soaked in light oil) used to kindle a tire. Using it to light a torch-or anything else with abundant, exposed fuel-takes an action. Lighting any other tire takes 1 minute.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0.5,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":4700000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.oEZYgJYtv6TmTuYZ"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/match-head.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"0Q1xOoUol3iEdZ3E","name":"Rope, Hemp","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>10\"/20 yards.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":5,"price":1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":3000000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.vWxMFq7HkwlyDyYt"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/rope-coil.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"1oMAMun2dw2NPTsM","name":"Code of Honor","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Honor is very important to your character. He keeps his word, doesn&rsquo;t abuse or kill prisoners, and generally tries to operate within his world&rsquo;s particular notion of proper gentlemanly or ladylike behavior.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"sort":5200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.n7D74dbSRjPwaoue"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}}],"effects":[{"_id":"ynhktka7G3xAEQpy","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.armor","value":"4","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":0},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/breastplate.svg","label":"Adamantine Plating","origin":"Actor.b9WRXx62ihYSWgFM.Item.Urs4LIBqNimIYCch","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"gm-notes":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_2mncjgs233x","path":"Savage Eberron Characters#/CF_SEP/Pregens","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"DAmP6IUSRHrfMedP"}
{"name":"Troubadour","type":"character","img":"modules/savage-eberron-bestiary/assets/bestiary/humanoids/changeling/changeling-aristocract-01.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":6,"runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":2,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":0,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>"},"species":{"name":"Changeling"},"currency":"500","wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{"value":null,"max":null,"Bard":{"value":10,"max":10}},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":3,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":4,"rank":"Seasoned","details":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Creation:&nbsp;</strong>Spirit d8, Bard, Humiliate</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>(N) Attribute:</strong> Spirit d10</li>\n<li><strong>(N) Skills:&nbsp;</strong>Performance d10 / Persuasion d8</li>\n<li><strong>(N) Edge:&nbsp;</strong>Work the Room</li>\n<li><strong>(N) Edge:&nbsp;</strong>Inspire Heroics</li>\n<li><strong>(S) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(S) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(S) : </strong></li>\n<li><strong>(S) : </strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) : </strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n</ol>\n</div>"},"bennies":{"value":3,"max":3},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Bad","displayName":0,"img":"modules/savage-eberron-bestiary/assets/bestiary_tokens/humanoids/changeling/changeling-aristocract-01.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":"IxFv8PDouI9xknSJ","actorLink":true,"disposition":1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"gso7NeJMXpdXlU6X","name":"Untrained","type":"skill","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":600000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skill.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"RMmVU7ormCp2MOqN","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":700000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sAig03GZiFKqBX7p"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/jump-across.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BkQxvPAlZLOJY7OZ","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":null},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":800000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.8N1uMThntsjaUPem"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/gift-of-knowledge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GN2DOxOtwyROzNWZ","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":1},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":900000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xOmuCR92Ys9jD5vg"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/convince.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8qCrEiZTjPRuJ2Qq","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1000000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.z9FmdFVGOOW2kufm"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/hidden.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"hzQAaO1x5wYjovWb","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.yvw9bMgsrWQXuZN2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ruBTbGRqlMoy2uSz","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/talk.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GQMFWtp6IWJ6kqTY","name":"Crowns (cp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":11,"weight":0.02,"price":0.01,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.fBZcb1EdAbO4EEOl"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-copper.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"6IZsePloV317RsUb","name":"Dragons (pp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":30,"weight":0.02,"price":10,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.33dBhsz0KCjjGHYe"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-platinum.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"HNsCemxmNdyU8oWj","name":"Galifars (gp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":27,"weight":0.02,"price":1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.CbrYbcaa5bTV8Wnd"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-gold.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Mccx8d95umBCcVgu","name":"Sovereigns (sp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":8,"weight":0.02,"price":0.1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EeHD4BJl6bS0eE4D"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-silver.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"clxF5K33Ai4X2dH3","name":"Change Appearance","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Changeling]{Changelings} can alter physical appearance at will as per the <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Disguise]{disguise}</em> power except it cannot affect clothing or gear. The power has no limit on duration. When they die they return to their natural form.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":400000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.AtT8CgxtLnYYxNSq"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/double-face-mask.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"SZujH4Fy4yzGWThP","name":"Changeling Instinct (Performance, Persuasion)","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Changeling]{Changelings} are socially and psychologically intuitive due to their adoption and understanding of different personas. They add 1 to rolls made with two of the following skills:&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion},&nbsp;</em>or&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}.</em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":500000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.YUYLH7ermvym2fQt"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/double-face-mask.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"p55AfnU6XkGJbxZ5","name":"Outsider (Changeling)","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>If identified as a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-races.Changeling]{changeling}, they have -2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} as other races tend to distrust them.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":300000,"flags":{"journal-links":{"referencedBy":{"JournalEntry":["FLa0Rrc1g8gAvYeu","TGVqpeUJkPHC4La6","ss1fIoGGw4KMULot"]}},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.0D1Cga4cmILKMomO"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/double-face-mask.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"zKdjSwPGQC9FulAm","name":"Bard","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The bards of Eberron bring epic tales of heroism and tragedy to the people. Many are renowned far and wide for their talents, but few realize how crucial they are to parties of brave adventurers. They bolster their allies in dire circumstances, beguile their enemies, and often battle evil with a sword in one hand and a lute in the other.</p>\n<p>Bards cast spells by singing, playing an instrument, reciting poetry, or reciting epic tales. They are usually erudite individuals, traveling the land to learn bawdy songs, great histories, and epic legends.</p>\n<p>Allies must be able to hear the bard to benefit from his various abilities.</p>\n<p>Bards gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Bard)]{Arcane Background (Bard)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bard Armor Interference (Light)]{Bard Armor Interference (Light)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sharp Tongued]{Sharp Tongued}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Performance d4+"}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.zphGBAJ4gdUCFIqa"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"cl5XCf1T7HyXQj2i","name":"Arcane Background (Bard)","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Bard)]{Arcane Background (Bard)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"sort":500000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.zVLHayWmSMnBSupy"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"CdINOq0Z0TAAo0LJ","name":"Bard Armor Interference (Light)","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Bulky armor interferes with a bard&rsquo;s grace and dexterity. They subtract 4 from their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance} rolls and from their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility-based} skill rolls when wearing medium or heavy armor, or using medium or heavy shields.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":200000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.c5ZFUaFkXxNDnOOh"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"UKg0bBRivXzs9jCN","name":"Sharp Tongued","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Bards may use @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance} as @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test} a foe. They may also ignore the Repetition advice given under @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Tests}, as long as they recite different verses, stanzas, lyrics, etc. Bards may also substitute @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance} for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} to meet Edge Requirements.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Bard"}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.pD0DjyWGZctqf2qX"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"1fN3ZFUCYCqMOzJy","name":"Impulsive","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The daredevil almost always leaps before he looks. He rarely thinks things through before taking action.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"sort":1700001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.4JdAnlJCRZvMbpnE"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"su2chLZ73PJm4fFv","name":"Lore","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Lore reflects knowledge and your ability to recall bits of information about history, archaeology, different Ages, legends, other continents, literature, song, poetry, and similar fields. This would also include knowledge about the more common races of the worlds.</p>\n<p>If an explorer wants to remember when the Dhakaani empire collapsed or know when the Qualabrin were destroyed on Xen'drik, this is the skill to have.</p>\n<p>A successful Lore roll reveals basic information about a topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron replaces Academics</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":null},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":700001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E0BVumGwbaczoPjD"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/skills/bookshelf.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ad0dvXBw4Zlz2TP0","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1800001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/punch.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"3BlI5P2nNWxoyjlV","name":"Arcana","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Arcana reflects knowledge about spells, artifacts, magic items, eldritch symbols, magical traditions, dragons, forbidden lore, magical beasts, analyzing alchemical compounds and other ritual paraphernalia, translate magical runes, guess what spell was cast based on physical evidence left behind, etc.</p>\n<p>A successful Arcana roll reveals basic information about a magical topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lr6HSv7xgo5Dsp1N"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/skills/spell-book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"OMB5nyEdq3Djb96T","name":"Performance","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>A good entertainer can lift the spirits, rally a crowd to action, or simply earn a few bucks from the locals. Specifics depend on the situation, setting, and how well the character is known in the area.</p>\n<p>Performance covers singing, acting, playing an instrument, or similar tasks that require an audience to appreciate.</p>\n<p><strong>Raising Funds:</strong> The amount of money a character can raise by performing is extremely subjective, but as a general rule a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} performance raises 20% of the setting's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Starting Funds} with a success and 30% with a raise. The GM can multiply this amount by the performer's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} if she feels it's appropriate. These numbers work for typical performers who might be known in a small establishment or area. Larger performances can greatly boost the performer's fee, but also require more time, energy, and setup.</p>\n<p><strong>Deception: </strong>Performance can be used instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} if the character is attempting to deceive, bluff, or disguise herself and the GM agrees it makes sense in the context of the situation.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":10,"modifier":1},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1900001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.SJ1nN0CmOHNQhfOQ"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/drama-masks.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"CGruaaKqVuOE7srx","name":"Thievery","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Lockpicking, safecracking, picking pockets, sleight of hand, setting and disabling traps and similar acts of misdirection, sabotage, subterfuge, and manipulation are called Thievery.</p>\n<p>If used to pick a lock, crack a safe, disable a trap, or perform a simple unopposed action, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} opens or disables the device, and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} does it in less time, without tripping alarms, or whatever else the GM feels is appropriate.</p>\n<p>Sleight of hand, hiding or planting an item, or picking a pocket require a simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}. If foes are actively watching the character, Thievery is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice}.</p>\n<p>The Game Master should assign @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalties} for particularly difficult circumstances. Picking a heavy padlock might have a &minus;4 penalty, while hiding a revolver in bulky winter clothing might grant a +1 bonus. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} typically means the character is spotted or it takes too much time (after which the character can try again). A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} typically sets off the trap, alerts the victim, or jams the device so that it must be opened or interacted with in a different way.</p>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Using Thievery on an electronic device, such as a keypad, is limited by the thief&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Electronics]{Electronics} skill. Use the lowest of the two skills.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2000001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wZbyJkisWIfmcZNt"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/lockpicks.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Twe2mr94RKwXO5e1","name":"Inspire Heroics","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Bards inspire their comrades with epic tales of valor and bravery. Once during any combat encounter (GM&rsquo;s call), the bard can spend a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} to gain five Inspiration tokens. This is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action}.</p>\n<p>For the remainder of the encounter, the bard may give these tokens to anyone within a Range of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} except himself. This may be done at any time (as long as the bard is conscious). The recipient must use the token immediately&mdash;it cannot be saved.</p>\n<p>Each Inspiration token allows a character to reroll a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} or damage roll. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} or damage roll may only benefit from a single Inspiration Token, even if there are multiple bards present. Further rerolls require spending a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny}&nbsp;or a special ability.</p>\n<p>Inspiration tokens aren&rsquo;t @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies}, don&rsquo;t trigger Edges that use @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} (such as Elan), and can&rsquo;t be used as such in any other way such as drawing new @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Cards} or Soaking Wounds.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Bard"}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ehOjnIxjQBRlFaIZ"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"J8ln6KwlQhjtaRo4","name":"Jealous (His unrivaled skill as a skald)","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>(MINOR OR MAJOR)</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Insecurity leads to envy of others&rsquo; accomplishments or being overly possessive of what this disgruntled soul feels belongs to him. He often complains, pouts, covets others&rsquo; possessions or accolades, claims credit for another&rsquo;s work, disobeys commands, and generally causes problems.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">As a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Minor} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance}, the character&rsquo;s jealousy is focused on one particular subject (such as his &ldquo;unrivaled&rdquo; skill as a pilot or a romantic interest).</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">As a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Major} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance}, the character is jealous of anyone and everyone he feels outshines him. He consistently bad-mouths his rivals, tries to upstage them, or actively plots to discredit those who threaten his ego.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":2100001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.F9LqkZHCqlXatfYK"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"d5h6TjuoNvmkJ0EQ","name":"Phobia (Dogs)","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Phobias are overwhelming and irrational fears that plague a hero&rsquo;s psyche. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Whenever a character is in the presence of his phobia (GM&rsquo;s call, but generally sight), he subtracts 1 from all his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait rolls} if it&rsquo;s a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Minor} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance}, and 2 if it&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Major}.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Phobias shouldn&rsquo;t be too obvious; everyone should be afraid of vampires, for example, so it&rsquo;s not a phobia, it&rsquo;s common sense. Instead, the phobia usually centers on some random element the mind associates with the event. Remember, phobias are </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">irrational </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">fears.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":2200001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.7kILaahVuQHb99nd"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"pM69JIiHkIyGYwUI","name":"Studded Leather","type":"armor","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This leather armor is reinforced with metal studs and sometimes small metal plates, providing most of the flexibility of leather armor with more robust protection.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":10,"price":40,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"minStr":"d6","armor":2,"isNaturalArmor":false,"locations":{"head":false,"torso":true,"arms":true,"legs":false}},"sort":1300000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.kFWq6ziWXi2Hwyk5"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/leather-armor.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"zwcDGyMnel4kSFyb","name":"Leather Pants","type":"armor","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":3,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"minStr":"d4","armor":1,"isNaturalArmor":false,"locations":{"head":false,"torso":false,"arms":false,"legs":true}},"sort":700000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.XWQhf1v5NNWGhX4p"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/armored-pants.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"YuAc4U6Xu72spQMO","name":"Dagger","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":2,"weight":1,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{"oyxuzdjora":{"name":"Athletics (throwing)","type":"skill","rof":null,"skillMod":"","skillOverride":"Athletics","shotsUsed":null}}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"3/6/12","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":400001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GxVNY83rIxMpxCqB"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/stiletto.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Q7LcjhzCpOJ5Sdpr","name":"Sling","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0.1,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Athletics","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"4/8/16","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d4","shots":"20","currentShots":"20","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":900001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.xQVTSzHuEiLKNyzn"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/sling.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ecgRZ3gaEKy5hCL7","name":"Sling Bullets","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>These are metal shaped bullets, typically made from lead.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":20,"weight":0.05,"price":0.01,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":1700000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.iZthAN8lacOVxmZz"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/sling.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"vFnjmZuB7g6AROkl","name":"Disguise Kit","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The perfect tool for anyone who wants to engage in trickery, a disguise kit enables its owner to adopt a false identity.</p>\n<p><strong>Components. </strong>A disguise kit includes cosmetics, hair dye, small props, and a few pieces of clothing.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":25,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":500000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Jg0iZy45yfZtoSQA"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/hand-bag.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"9raaOk6ipkVg6N61","name":"Backpack","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This leather knapsack has one large pocket that closes with a buckled strap and holds about 2 cubic feet of material. Some may have one or more smaller pockets on the sides.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":5100000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EJwgrkGHCSHskUnO"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/backpack.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"IPtqq0yXEKh4oku2","name":"Outfit, Entertainer's","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This set of flashy-perhaps even gaudy- clothes is meant for entertaining. Entertainer's outfits come in a wide range of styles, from scandalous to flattering to absurd. While the outfit looks whimsical, its practical design does nothing to inhibit your ability to tumble, dance, walk a tightrope, or run (if the audience turns ugly).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":3,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":500000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.H2bTnJv74z9kNKqM"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/travel-dress.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"QSlCn0TJiAGtovKu","name":"Mandolin","type":"gear","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":35,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":800001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.XYNQEAyyF6Qwn0Ix"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/musical-notes.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"h81QN3B15Nh0xdl2","name":"Anthem of Heroics","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation/Necromancy}</p>\n<p><strong>Limitation:</strong> Boost only</p>\n<p>This power allows a character to increase or decrease a target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} (attribute or skill).</p>\n<p><em>Boosting </em>an ally&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} increases the selected Trait one die type, or two with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, for five rounds.</p>\n<p><em>Lowering </em>an enemy&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} has a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Powers]{Duration} of Instant and lowers the selected attribute or skill a die type with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}, or two with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} (to a minimum of d4). A victim automatically tries to shake off the effect with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of his following turns.&nbsp;Success improves the effect one die type, and a raise removes the effect entirely.</p>\n<p>Additional castings don&rsquo;t stack on a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} (take the highest), but may affect different Traits.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}&nbsp;each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Boost/Lower Trait (+2):&nbsp;</strong> With success, the selected @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} gains a free reroll once per round, or once per action with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. For <em>lower Trait</em> the target applies a &minus;2 penalty to the affected Trait&rsquo;s rolls.</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (+1):</strong> <em>Lower Trait</em> only. The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll to shake off the effect is made at &minus;2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Performance","skillMod":"+1","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Spirit","duration":"5","trapping":"Heroic song","arcane":"Bard","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":100001,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.5p4X7sd96czRfNPc"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"sCAdO21sVIA5lodW","name":"Song of Friendship","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p>A successful arcane skill vs @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll gives the caster insight into a target's basic emotions. This grants him a +1 bonus (+2 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}) to all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} rolls against the target for the Duration of the power.</p>\n<p><em>Empathy</em> works on animals, adding +1 (+2 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}) to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Riding]{Riding} or other rolls to interact with the creature.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong>&nbsp;@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li><strong>Charm (+2): </strong>If the target is Uncooperative or Neutral, a successful casting makes him Cooperative, or Friendly with a raise. The spell is instantly broken if the caster or her allies attack the victim or her allies.</li>\n<li><strong>Duration (+1):</strong> Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds. If the character Critically Fails any of the affected skill rolls against the target, the effect terminates immediately.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Truth (+2):</strong> The caster knows if the target believes he's telling the truth or not.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Performance","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Spirit","duration":"5","trapping":"Exchanging a lyric conversation","arcane":"Bard","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":100001,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.eAQAHjnqokcoEg0F"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"37msQsg3qKzKci71","name":"Humiliate","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Those with a cruel wit can destroy a rival&rsquo;s ego in a single remark or well-timed gesture.<br />Your hero gets a free reroll on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt Tests}</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Taunt d8+"}},"sort":5200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1nt716ztwfa","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Social Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.NIZkJLu8CZLW5AJZ"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"rjyknLC5fzg8tEko","name":"Work The Room","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Your hero&rsquo;s words don&rsquo;t just inspire those they&rsquo;re directed at&mdash;they often inspire others as well. Once per turn, you can use Work the Room to roll an additional skill die when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Supporting} with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance}. The additional die Supports any other ally who can see or hear your hero, and applies to their next action, whatever it may be.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"sort":5300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1nt716ztwfa","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Social Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.U2pALBBG9geRa2S6"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"lZKwUQ2uIyMAjEfZ","name":"Shout of Terror","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Necromancy}</p>\n<p>This power causes overwhelming dread and horror. The target makes a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear} roll. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras} who fail are @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Fear Table]{Panicked} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards} roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-macros.Fear Table]{Fear Table}. If the power is cast with a raise, the Fear roll is at &minus;2 and Wild Cards add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-macros.Fear Table]{Fear Table} results.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+2/+3):</strong> For +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Small} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Fear (+2): </strong>Fear rolls are made at&minus;2, or &minus;4 if cast with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Performance","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Spirit","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Discordant shout","arcane":"Bard","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":1800000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.RkKW0hhkT9E7bK1C"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"gyRrVlpzNDAmAU4d","name":"Unarmed Strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":5400000,"flags":{},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/fist.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"1sMeHhEB6RxplF5A","name":"Hard To Kill","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This adventurer has more lives than a herd of cats. He may ignore his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} penalties when making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls to avoid <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Bleeding Out}</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"sort":5500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bv1geyfk6c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.hpC41I3Bd56WPTu2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_2mncjgs233x","path":"Savage Eberron Characters#/CF_SEP/Pregens","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"DbzNz2RWuohUYuVc"}
{"name":"Lyrandar Swashbuckler","type":"character","img":"modules/savage-eberron-bestiary/assets/bestiary/humanoids/half-elf/half-elf-caster-01.webp","data":{"attributes":{"agility":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"smarts":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"animal":false},"spirit":{"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"unShakeBonus":0},"strength":{"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6},"encumbranceSteps":0},"vigor":{"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}}},"stats":{"speed":{"runningDie":6,"runningMod":0,"value":6},"toughness":{"value":0,"armor":1,"modifier":0},"parry":{"value":0,"modifier":0},"size":0},"details":{"biography":{"value":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>[swashbuckler] lived from an early age on the seas through the Windwrights Guild. Often one ships that assisted in maintaining the dominance of House Lyrandar, [swashbuckler] has lived a harsh life on the seas. Holding the utmost confidence in their abilities and the luck that seems to surround them. A life of going after competitors for the house has seen a ruthlessness arise within them that always seems to manifest in a fight at sea.</p>\n<p>Of late [swashbuckler] has been feeling the itch to try something else and asked for leave from the House to explore other ventures. This is encouraged within the house so [swashbuckler] has traveled to Stormreach to see what trouble they can get into.</p>\n</div>"},"species":{"name":"Half-elf"},"currency":"500","wealth":{"die":6,"modifier":0,"wild-die":6},"conviction":{"value":0,"active":false},"autoCalcToughness":true,"autoCalcParry":true},"powerPoints":{"value":null,"max":null,"Mark of Storm":{"value":10,"max":10},"Sorcery":{"value":15,"max":15}},"fatigue":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":2},"wounds":{"value":0,"min":0,"max":3,"ignored":0},"advances":{"value":4,"rank":"Seasoned","details":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Creation:&nbsp;</strong>Luck, Mark of Storm, Sorcerer</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>(N) Edge:</strong> New Powers: <em>burst, dispel</em></li>\n<li><strong>(N) Edge:&nbsp;</strong>First Strike</li>\n<li><strong>(N) Skills:</strong> Athletics d6 / Fighting d8</li>\n<li><strong>(S) Edge:</strong> Rogue</li>\n<li><strong>(S) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(S) : </strong></li>\n<li><strong>(S) : </strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) : </strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(V) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(H) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n</ol>\n</div>"},"bennies":{"value":3,"max":3},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Sorcerer","displayName":0,"img":"modules/savage-eberron-bestiary/assets/bestiary_tokens/humanoids/half-elf/half-elf-caster-01.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":"pvtqGSBnGf0hhzYa","actorLink":true,"disposition":1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"gso7NeJMXpdXlU6X","name":"Untrained","type":"skill","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":600000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skill.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"RMmVU7ormCp2MOqN","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":700000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sAig03GZiFKqBX7p"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/jump-across.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BkQxvPAlZLOJY7OZ","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":800000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.8N1uMThntsjaUPem"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/gift-of-knowledge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GN2DOxOtwyROzNWZ","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":900000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xOmuCR92Ys9jD5vg"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/convince.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8qCrEiZTjPRuJ2Qq","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1000000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.z9FmdFVGOOW2kufm"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/hidden.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"hzQAaO1x5wYjovWb","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.yvw9bMgsrWQXuZN2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ruBTbGRqlMoy2uSz","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/talk.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GQMFWtp6IWJ6kqTY","name":"Crowns (cp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":11,"weight":0.02,"price":0.01,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.fBZcb1EdAbO4EEOl"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-copper.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"6IZsePloV317RsUb","name":"Dragons (pp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":28,"weight":0.02,"price":10,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.33dBhsz0KCjjGHYe"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-platinum.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"HNsCemxmNdyU8oWj","name":"Galifars (gp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":31,"weight":0.02,"price":1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.CbrYbcaa5bTV8Wnd"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-gold.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Mccx8d95umBCcVgu","name":"Sovereigns (sp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":12,"weight":0.02,"price":0.1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EeHD4BJl6bS0eE4D"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-silver.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ZZrY9N4uTnYeHmFJ","name":"Unarmed Strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":1600001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/fist.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"viVI0A8hOKiphIYf","name":"Hard To Kill","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This adventurer has more lives than a herd of cats. He may ignore his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} penalties when making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls to avoid <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Bleeding Out}</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"sort":1700001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bv1geyfk6c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.hpC41I3Bd56WPTu2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"JJnRgDF7LH15wNN5","name":"Low Light Vision","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Low Light Vision ignores penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim and Dark Illumination} (but not @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Pitch Darkness}).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.OL3T8otZVCkOoir3"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/angry-eyes.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"MPSOttscqE8G1qDu","name":"Skilled (Boating)","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Sharing the ingenuity of their human relatives as well as having slightly longer life spans, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Half-elf]{half-elves} start with a d4 in any skill based on their experiences, education, training, or culture. If the chosen skill is a core skill, skill), it starts at d6 and the skill's maximum increases to d12+1.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":300000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.nEYWHwMaSPWSHGIq"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/woman-elf-face.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"UVuDofLTLLl2jpiA","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1800001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/punch.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"t1tPWehAhWTS5cUD","name":"Boating","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p>Characters with this skill can handle most any boat or ship common to their setting. They also know how to handle common tasks associated with their vessel such as tying knots, rigging sails, or following currents.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1900001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.WMWgIVDuAW4cHxj2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/sailboat.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"hbJVDtvNKmuGGDQQ","name":"Taunt","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Taunt attacks a person&rsquo;s pride through ridicule, cruel jests, or oneupmanship.</p>\n<p>Taunt is an opposed roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{resisted} by the opponent&rsquo;s Smarts. In combat, this is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} means the defender backs down, slinks away, or starts a fight. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} might leave the victim cowed for the remainder of the scene, or make her storm out of the area fuming or even in tears, or attack her tormentor recklessly (perhaps with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Attack]{Wild Attack} on the first round of combat).</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} means the target is immune to this character&rsquo;s Taunts for the remainder of the encounter.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2000001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.tjzr8dGPHLLWZdRI"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/confrontation.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ht6LjeOVLU2wme9c","name":"Spellcasting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p>Mages, wizards, warlocks, and witches use Spellcasting to cast spells. See the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Background (Magic)]{Arcane Background (Magic)} Edge.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2100001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.MWPNuINyQk9xComt"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/spell-book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"rZGJgIV2yBSDP8u0","name":"Arcana","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Arcana reflects knowledge about spells, artifacts, magic items, eldritch symbols, magical traditions, dragons, forbidden lore, magical beasts, analyzing alchemical compounds and other ritual paraphernalia, translate magical runes, guess what spell was cast based on physical evidence left behind, etc.</p>\n<p>A successful Arcana roll reveals basic information about a magical topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lr6HSv7xgo5Dsp1N"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/skills/spell-book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"qezPCHLtCPw6lR52","name":"Language (Elvish)","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EkUQ1ZBWdYviH0iV"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/talk.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Hdka8abZ6AXCoivM","name":"Water Elemental Bloodline","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The mage&rsquo;s family was touched by a powerful elemental force. Choose one of the elements listed below. Your hero gains @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Enviromental Resistance]{enviromental resistance}&nbsp;to that element and one of the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Air: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Flight]{Flight}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} 6.</li>\n<li><strong>Earth:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Burrow]{Burrowing} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} 6.</li>\n<li><strong>Fire: </strong>+2 damage to damaging Powers with a fire @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Trapping}.</li>\n<li><strong>Water: </strong>Enemies are automatically @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hinder or Hurry (+1)]{Hindered} (per the modifier) when affected by your powers.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":200001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.n4M500Fr8iYKl9Gs"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/ability.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"X14tBh9ztrbNxkDa","name":"Arcane Background (Sorcerer)","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Sorcerer)]{Arcane Background (Sorcerer)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"sort":500000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.BPmOfQyFaixXp9Vj"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"kPEl0SVVmmjFIKx0","name":"Sorcerer","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Scions of magical bloodlines, pawns of fate and destiny, or simply flukes of fickle magic, sorcerers look within themselves for arcane prowess. As they tap into powers few mortals can imagine, these magic-touched souls must learn to harness the power of their birthright. While some seek to control their abilities, others give in to their magic, letting it rule their lives&mdash;often with explosive results.</p>\n<p>Sorcerers live and breathe that which other spellcasters devote their lives to mastering. For them magic is more than a useful tool or a field of study; it is life itself.</p>\n<p>Sorcerers have the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Sorcerer)]{Arcane Background (Sorcerer)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Bloodline]{Bloodline}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sorcerer Armor Interference (Cloth)]{Sorcerer Armor Interference (Cloth)}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+, Spirit d6+, Spellcasting d4+"}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.hWGHnMOWJQpGH1SO"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8yG5aFrRkxA11pad","name":"Rogue/Sorcerer Armor Interference (Light)","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Sorcery requires rapid, intricate, and unhindered somatic movements. Sorcerers subtract 4 from their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} rolls and from their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility-based} skill rolls when wearing medium, or heavy armor, or using medium, or heavy shields.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":400000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.2sn2phCMfhSAObOL"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"VgMjDi6nr0qZfzqf","name":"Bloodline","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The sorcerer must choose a @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Bloodlines]{bloodline}. Beneath each Bloodline description is also the additional special ability one gains when taking the Advanced Bloodline Edge.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Sorcerer"}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.olo05rxG7sk33Bpt"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"tueyKWPCrLLXyu61","name":"Mark of Storm","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the dragonmarked heir can cast one of the following spells:&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Barrier]{Barrier}</em><span style=\"background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);\"> (air and water trapping only), </span><span style=\"background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);\"><em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Light/Darkness]{darkness}</em> (air and water trapping only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Elemental Manipulation]{elemental manipulation}</em> (air and water trappings only, mythic modifiers included), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Havoc]{havoc}</em> (including mythic modifiers), and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Telekinesis]{telekinesis} </em>(air and water trappings only).&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>The heir has 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} that recharge normally. She automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} for an additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}.&nbsp; She may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired.</p>\n<p>The Mark of Storm doesn&rsquo;t grant access to Edges requiring an Arcane Background. If the heir also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges, abilities, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} can be used with the Mark of Storm (and vice-versa).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Half-elf"}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.RFP3pPCEDDKC4pjp"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"fVZeO06cKIqLmPTs","name":"Fog Cloud","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evocation}</p>\n<p><strong>Limitation:&nbsp;</strong>Darkness only</p>\n<p><em>Light </em>creates bright @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{illumination} in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}. With a raise, the light can be focused into a 5&Prime; (10 yard) beam as well.</p>\n<p><em>Darkness </em>blocks @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{illumination}&nbsp;in an area the size of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}, making the area Dark, or Pitch Darkness with a raise (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination}).</p>\n<p>If <em>light </em>and <em>darkness </em>overlap, they create a patch of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim light} (&minus;2).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Area Effect (+2): </strong>The <em>light</em> expands to the caster&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} in radius, with a Range of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} &times;2. The light is sunlight and has the same effect on certain creatures (such as vampires) as natural sunlight.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>True Darkness (+2):</strong> The <em>darkness</em> blocks @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Infravision]{Infravision}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Low Light Vision]{Low Light Vision}, and @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Darkvision]{Darkvision}. It has no effect on magical sight such as <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect arcana}</em>.</li>\n<li><strong>Mobile (+1):</strong> The caster can move the area of effect up to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} die type each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{round} after casting, or attach it to an inanimate object when first cast.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"Think fog","arcane":"Mark of Storm","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":2300000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gEg0cmKVXZN0LEYt"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"67FgUBhe8XA9Z6KI","name":"Elemental Mastery","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p>This power grants basic control over the four traditional elements: air, earth, fire, and water (the elements may vary depending on the setting). The power acts as if it has a d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength}, or d8 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p>Here are some ideas for what each element can do. Each is an action.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Air:</strong> Push someone, blow out a torch, fan a flame, cool someone down (+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} rolls in oppressive heat).</li>\n<li><strong>Earth:</strong> Move a square foot of earth (half that in stone) each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{round}, cover tracks.</li>\n<li><strong>Fire:</strong> Conjure flame about the size of a torch, hurl a small blast of fire at someone (Str damage), spread existing flame (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fire]{Fire}).</li>\n<li><strong>Water:</strong> Conjure a quart of water (not \"inside\" objects or people), purify a gallon of water per casting.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Power (+2):</strong> The volume of air, earth, fire, or water affected is tripled.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Weather (+8): </strong>The caster can summon or dispel storms, bring a cooling rain, scorch the earth with a heatwave, or even bring snow to the hottest climes.\n<p>The caster can bring or disperse rain, snow, sun, and wind in about a five-mile radius. The severity depends on the local environment&mdash;a harsh desert might receive gentle rain while a rain forest gets a driving downpour. The effects take 10 minutes to create and lasts an hour.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"A few simple gestures","arcane":"Mark of Storm","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":1400000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.7kVpgzGDEXhQWeAe"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"S4LRrMsA0uBKPeS2","name":"Whirlwind","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evocation}</p>\n<p>This ability creates chaos and mischief for all those within its area of effect, hurling debris and rivals in all directions.</p>\n<p>With success, the caster places a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template} anywhere within @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{range}, or a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Cone Template} emanating from the caster.</p>\n<p>Anyone touched by the template is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted} and must <em>then </em>make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} roll (at &ndash;2 if the caster got a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}). Those who fail are hurled [[/r 2d6]]&Prime;&mdash;directly away from the caster if using the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Cone Template} or directly away from the center if using a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Blast Template} (the caster chooses for those in the dead center).</p>\n<p>Victims who strike a hard object (such as a wall) take [[/r 2d4]] damage (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Nonlethal Damage]{nonlethal} unless it&rsquo;s a spiked wall or other more dangerous hazard).</p>\n<p><strong>Airborne Targets</strong>: Flying or airborne targets suffer an additional &minus;2 to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} rolls as they have no ground to brace themselves on.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+1):</strong> <em>Havoc </em>affects a&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Havoc (+2):</strong> Targets are knocked back a total of 3d6\" and take 2d6 damage if they strike a hard object.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"12","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Whirlwind","arcane":"Mark of Storm","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":1900000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ImX6NTXegWc0TDg8"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"AIpZGXfGBAcZkwG0","name":"Wind Wall","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Barrier </em>creates a straight wall 5&Prime; (10 yards) long and 1&Prime; (two yards) tall, of immobile material that conforms to the surface it&rsquo;s cast upon. Double the length with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p>Thickness varies depending on what the wall is made of, but is usually a few inches.</p>\n<p>The wall is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{Hardness} 8, and may be destroyed as any other object (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{Breaking Things}). Each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} destroys a 1\" (2 yard) square section of wall (piercing weapons can't damage the barrier).</p>\n<p>When the spell expires or the wall is broken it crumbles to dust or dissipates. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Trappings} are never left behind.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Bridge (+1): </strong>The&nbsp;<em>barrier&nbsp;</em>can be shaped to be flat and act as a bridge or roof.</li>\n<li><strong>Damage (+1): </strong>The <em>barrier </em>causes 2d4 damage to anyone who contacts it.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Deadly (+2): </strong>The <em>barrier </em>causes 2d6 damage.</li>\n<li><strong>Tough (+1): </strong>The wall is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{Hardness} 10.</li>\n<li><strong>Shaped (+1): </strong>The <em>barrier </em>forms a circle, square, or rectangle. It can't have a roof or floor, and can't Bind or Entangle anything within (use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Entangle]{entangle} power for that).</li>\n<li><strong>Size (+1): </strong>The length and height of the <em>barrier </em>doubles.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Wall of strong wind","arcane":"Mark of Storm","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":100001,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.XEfQImAvrlGCMz1O"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Ept7zSLcLKTFfsN3","name":"Gust of Wind","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p><em>Telekinesis </em>is the ability to move objects or creatures (including oneself) with arcane will. It has a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} of d10, or d12 with a raise.</p>\n<p>Unwilling opponents resist the caster&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} with an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll when targeted and at the start of each of their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{turns} afterward until they&rsquo;re released. They can be moved up to the caster&rsquo; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} per turn in any direction, and can be bashed into walls, ceilings, or other obstacles for Str+d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{damage}.</p>\n<p>Dropped creatures suffer @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Falling]{falling damage} as usual.</p>\n<p><strong>Telekinetic Tools</strong>: A caster can wield tools (including weapons) with <em>telekinesis </em>as an action. Use the caster&rsquo;s relevant @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{skill} when attacking in this way (not his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill}).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Power (+3): </strong>The Strength of telekinesis is d12, or d12 + 2 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. Objects weighing 1,000 pounds or more automatically deal @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{Damage} when used as weapons.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts x2","duration":"5","trapping":"Strong wind","arcane":"Mark of Storm","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":100001,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.KLsRF4Gf0QBakUZu"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Z6U8J0Nc7dMw6tUE","name":"Arcane Protection","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Abjuration}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} with arcane protection means hostile powers suffer a &minus;2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalty} (&minus;4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}) to affect this character.</p>\n<p>If the power causes harm, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{damage} is also reduced a like amount. Arcane Protection stacks with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Arcane Resistance]{Arcane Resistance} should the recipient have both!</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}&nbsp;each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Arcane Protection (+2):&nbsp;</strong> Hostile powers suffer a &minus;4 penalty (&minus;6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Spellcasting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Concentration, a dull glow around the protected character, a fetish","arcane":"Sorcery","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":200000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.hDK8ufDJ5YtTLUwf"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ntzeJ4kgMxroWdz2","name":"Elemental Infusions","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation/Necromancy}</p>\n<p>This power allows a character to increase or decrease a target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} (attribute or skill).</p>\n<p><em>Boosting </em>an ally&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} increases the selected Trait one die type, or two with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, for five rounds.</p>\n<p><em>Lowering </em>an enemy&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} has a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Powers]{Duration} of Instant and lowers the selected attribute or skill a die type with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}, or two with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} (to a minimum of d4). A victim automatically tries to shake off the effect with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of his following turns.&nbsp;Success improves the effect one die type, and a raise removes the effect entirely.</p>\n<p>Additional castings don&rsquo;t stack on a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} (take the highest), but may affect different Traits.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}&nbsp;each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Boost/Lower Trait (+2):&nbsp;</strong> With success, the selected @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} gains a free reroll once per round, or once per action with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. For <em>lower Trait</em> the target applies a &minus;2 penalty to the affected Trait&rsquo;s rolls.</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (+1):</strong> <em>Lower Trait</em> only. The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll to shake off the effect is made at &minus;2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Spellcasting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5 (boost); Instant (lower)","trapping":"Shaping of the elementals","arcane":"Sorcery","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":700000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.5p4X7sd96czRfNPc"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"2rtbpECxGG0C3wGJ","name":"Luck","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The adventurer seems to be blessed by fate, karma, the gods, or whatever external forces he believes in (or believe in him!). </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">He draws one extra @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} at the beginning of each game session, allowing him to succeed at important tasks more often than most, and survive incredible dangers.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"sort":2400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9dc4ijzy8uh","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.p00apKW5V2grVRw2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"LrE3PLAoftNleWyp","name":"Lightning Bolt","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evocation}</p>\n<p><em>Burst </em>produces a large fan of energy that bathes its targets in red-hot fire, a cone of cold, or other damaging matter or energy.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} creates a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Cone Template} or Steam Tempalte starting at the caster and extending outward. Everything within suffers 2d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage]{damage} (or 3d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Damage (+2):</strong> The <em>burst</em> causes 3d6 damage, or 4d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Burst (+4):</strong>&nbsp;The&nbsp;<em>burst</em>&nbsp;causes 4d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{Damage} (5d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Spellcasting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"2d6","range":"Cone Template","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Bolt of lightning","arcane":"Sorcery","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":900000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.5wAd94cMftDi6fN8"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"FEfyAagvSdedqF7v","name":"Dispel","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Abjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Dispel </em>allows a hero to negate enemy powers. It has no effect on permanent enchantments or innate abilities such as a dragon&rsquo;s breath or a banshee&rsquo;s scream. <em>Dispel </em>affects @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Devices]{arcane devices} normally.</p>\n<p><em>Dispel </em>can be used on a power already in effect or to counter an enemy power as it&rsquo;s being used. The latter requires the countering mage to be on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hold]{Hold} and interrupt his foe&rsquo;s action.</p>\n<p>In either case, <em>dispelling </em>an opponent&rsquo;s power is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} of arcane skills (with a &minus;2 modifier if the rival&rsquo;s power is of another type such as magic vs. miracles, psionics vs. weird science, etc.).</p>\n<p>If the <em>dispelling </em>character wins, the targeted power ends immediately (or fails if it was countered with the usual results of failure). With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the recipient of the <em>dispelled </em>power is also @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted}.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Anti-magic Field (&minus;3): </strong>Instead of affecting a power at Range, this modifier creates a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} centered on the caster with a Duration of 1 minute per @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{rank}. Magic items, effects, and powers have no effect within the field. Summoned creatures that enter the field must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll each round or take a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}. Anti-Magic Field can't be combined with any other modifiers.</li>\n<li><strong>Area Effect (&minus;1/&minus;2/&minus;3): </strong>The effect covers an area: &minus;1 @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier} uses a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Small Blast Template}, &minus;2 uses @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium}, or &minus;3 uses @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large}. The caster makes one @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll, then each affected target makes an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll to oppose it. This affects all powers in the target area unless the caster also uses the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Selective Targets]{Selective} Power Modifier.</li>\n<li><strong>Multiple Powers (&minus;1): </strong>If successful, the caster <em>dispels</em> all the target&rsquo;s currently activated powers.</li>\n<li><strong>Power (&minus;1):</strong> The caster can target a magical item rather than an individual or a power. This is a standard @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll, not an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll}, at &minus;2 penalty (&minus;4 for artifacts, GM&rsquo;s call). If successful, all the item&rsquo;s magical abilities are negated for one round, or two with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Spellcasting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Sm","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Waving hands, whispered words","arcane":"Sorcery","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":2500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_smjokcv2f6d","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.s6ATQGZEUGwobHE4"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"91Opa4umDbboE3HT","name":"First Strike","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Once per round, as long as he&rsquo;s not @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned},</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"> the hero gets a free @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} attack against a foe immediately after he moves into @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach}. (See</span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\"> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Free Attacks]{Free Attacks}</span></strong><span class=\"fontstyle0\">)</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d8+"}},"sort":2700000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bv1geyfk6c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.4ue5lRCW1toPyzWO"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"x9XwxDidJutNunQI","name":"Leather Armor","type":"armor","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":5,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"minStr":"d4","armor":1,"isNaturalArmor":false,"locations":{"head":false,"torso":true,"arms":true,"legs":false}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PRPRsNmJyfvoy6hH"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/leather-armor.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"OxrpfiVPc2f4nQaV","name":"Leather Pants","type":"armor","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":3,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"minStr":"d4","armor":1,"isNaturalArmor":false,"locations":{"head":false,"torso":false,"arms":false,"legs":true}},"sort":700000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.XWQhf1v5NNWGhX4p"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/armored-pants.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"jiHYzWwkQEyf2cZ1","name":"Rapier","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Parry]{Parry} +1</p>\n</div>","notes":"Parry +1","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":25,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":700001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.yPRx9vOmWYL1MgBF"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/stiletto.svg","effects":[{"_id":"2K9kgErsmseqr2AH","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.parry.modifier","value":"1","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/stiletto.svg","label":"Rapier Parry Bonus","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"VajMeDEr4T5edVrn","name":"Dagger","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{"oyxuzdjora":{"name":"Athletics (throwing)","type":"skill","rof":null,"skillMod":"","skillOverride":"Athletics","shotsUsed":null}}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"3/6/12","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":400001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GxVNY83rIxMpxCqB"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/stiletto.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"WqZLf8tOidnHAr8G","name":"Rogue","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Life is an endless adventure for those who live by their wits. Ever just one step ahead of danger, rogues bank on their cunning, skill, and charm to bend fate to their favor. Never knowing what to expect, they tend to prepare for everything. Out of necessity, they become adept manipulators, agile acrobats, or shadowy stalkers. They are thieves and gamblers, fast talkers and diplomats, bandits and bounty hunters, or explorers and investigators.</p>\n<p>Although many rogues favor the opportunities of towns and cities, some embrace life on the road. They wander from place to place, meeting exotic people and facing fantastic danger in pursuit of endless riches. In the end, all rogues desire to shape their fates and live life on their own terms.</p>\n<p>Rogues gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)]{Rogue Armor Restriction (Light)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Sneak Attack]{Sneak Attack}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Agility d6+, Thievery d6+"}},"sort":500000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.UBXzgLMsycquNmh2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"uGuvvDtaWEQD4ml9","name":"Sneak Attack","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rogues add an additional d6 to their damage when they have @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{the Drop} on their victim, or the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable}. This applies to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} attacks.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Rogue"}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.5ggl5Khobnfxq698"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"kRha4LXslnd3rIEX","name":"Thievery","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Lockpicking, safecracking, picking pockets, sleight of hand, setting and disabling traps and similar acts of misdirection, sabotage, subterfuge, and manipulation are called Thievery.</p>\n<p>If used to pick a lock, crack a safe, disable a trap, or perform a simple unopposed action, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} opens or disables the device, and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} does it in less time, without tripping alarms, or whatever else the GM feels is appropriate.</p>\n<p>Sleight of hand, hiding or planting an item, or picking a pocket require a simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}. If foes are actively watching the character, Thievery is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice}.</p>\n<p>The Game Master should assign @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalties} for particularly difficult circumstances. Picking a heavy padlock might have a &minus;4 penalty, while hiding a revolver in bulky winter clothing might grant a +1 bonus. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} typically means the character is spotted or it takes too much time (after which the character can try again). A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} typically sets off the trap, alerts the victim, or jams the device so that it must be opened or interacted with in a different way.</p>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Using Thievery on an electronic device, such as a keypad, is limited by the thief&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Electronics]{Electronics} skill. Use the lowest of the two skills.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2800000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wZbyJkisWIfmcZNt"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/lockpicks.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"IDCqx8NBcZrR95eM","name":"Buckler Shield","type":"shield","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>Hardness:</strong> 8</p>\n<p>While worn a buckler can be used to bash for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} damage.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":5,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"minStr":"d4","parry":1,"cover":0},"sort":100000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.m1b8jpwKU2orRCCr"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/round-shield.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"oNWi2MMl3LA1rfkD","name":"Quirk (Smokes pipe)","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This individual has some minor foible that is usually humorous but can occasionally cause him real trouble. A swashbuckler may always try to slash his initials on his foes, a dwarf may brag constantly about his culture, or a snobby d&eacute;butante might not eat, drink, or socialize with the lower class, for example.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":2900000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.y0lUBhYHhl2LdjZZ"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"JWTxHFyf4SDhLl3J","name":"Arrogant","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Your hero doesn&rsquo;t think he&rsquo;s the best&mdash;he knows he is. Whether it&rsquo;s swordsmanship, kung fu, or painting, few compare to his skills and he flaunts it every chance he gets. Winning isn&rsquo;t enough for this champion. He wants to dominate his opponent and prove there&rsquo;s no one better. He&rsquo;s the kind of fighter who disarms an opponent in a duel just to pick the sword up and hand it back with a smirk. Arrogant individuals look for the greatest threat in battle, hacking their way through lesser minions only because they&rsquo;re in the way.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"sort":3000000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.YpLBVlqcaIEy8oYq"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"HdazvIs0MTfvvhSs","name":"Ruthless","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>(MINOR OR MAJOR)</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The fanatic will do most anything to accomplish her goals. As a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Major} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance}, she harms anyone and everyone who gets in her way. As a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Minor} Hindrance, she stops short of true harm to anyone except those who directly oppose her.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":3100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.PEvzfcOWbwstmhTy"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"sdTUwQM5CqyskCAD","name":"Manacles","type":"gear","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":3300000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_u6k9894u4jr","path":"Savage Eberron Equipment#/CF_SEP/Adventuring Gear","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.xzovDGSMDlfzJyHR"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/handcuffs.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"RWd0ZXKKdVbCt3lu","name":"Pouch","type":"gear","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0.5,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":3400000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_u6k9894u4jr","path":"Savage Eberron Equipment#/CF_SEP/Adventuring Gear","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.n59EuO7qRH4FoJsk"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/knapsack.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"eUcUQQd4Z2hluL5i","name":"Outfit, Traveler's","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This set of clothes consists of boots, a wool skirt or breeches, a sturdy belt, a shirt (perhaps with a vest or jacket), and an ample cloak with a hood.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":3500000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_elr2lzdtc3","path":"Savage Eberron Equipment#/CF_SEP/Clothing","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.Fiz2e4iqdHDZH7Cd"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/shirt.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"4wfpfHJSn9OJMyUC","name":"Identification Papers, with Portrait","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Most people of the middle and upper classes, at least in the most civilized areas of Khorvaire (Aundair, Breland, Karrnath, Thrane, Zilargo, and the Mror Holds) carry identification papers with them at all times. Issued by national governments and notarized by House Sivis, these papers present a detailed physical description of a person (the wealthy sometimes commission small portraits of themselves), the person's name and residence, and in some cases additional information about the person's affiliations (particularly including any connection to a dragonmarked house, royalty, or a large institution).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":5,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":3600000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.CltANbj5AXQowpPj"},"cf":{"id":"temp_l1quzzxujvp","path":"Savage Eberron Equipment#/CF_SEP/Documents & Identification","color":"#000000"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/scroll-quill.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"YG9lyZkpFhFynX6k","name":"Navigator's Tools","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Navigator's tools helps you determine a true course based on observing the stars. It also grants you insight into charts and maps while developing your sense of direction. This gives a person +1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Survival] checks to read charts, maps and determine sense of direction.</p>\n<p><strong>Components. </strong>Navigator's tools include a sextant, a compass, calipers, a ruler, parchment, ink, and a quill.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":25,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":3700000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_hwsgmy31vii","path":"Savage Eberron Equipment#/CF_SEP/Tools & Tool Kits","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-equipment.tmeeQvIVQ4ooqlqf"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/sextant.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}}],"effects":[{"_id":"8YMSCnhwkhLVH7P5","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.parry.modifier","value":"1","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":0},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/stiletto.svg","label":"Rapier Parry Bonus","origin":"Actor.pvtqGSBnGf0hhzYa.Item.jiHYzWwkQEyf2cZ1","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"gm-notes":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_2mncjgs233x","path":"Savage Eberron Characters#/CF_SEP/Pregens","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"EanicSC2WD6GGRjg"}
