li>\n</ol>\n</div>"},"bennies":{"value":3,"max":3},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Ranger","displayName":0,"img":"modules/savage-eberron-bestiary/assets/bestiary_tokens/humanoids/orc/orc-warrior-01.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":"7xBpcfnKRmiZfXmt","actorLink":true,"disposition":1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"gso7NeJMXpdXlU6X","name":"Untrained","type":"skill","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":600000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skill.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"RMmVU7ormCp2MOqN","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"strength","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":700000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sAig03GZiFKqBX7p"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/jump-across.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BkQxvPAlZLOJY7OZ","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":800000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.8N1uMThntsjaUPem"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/gift-of-knowledge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GN2DOxOtwyROzNWZ","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":900000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xOmuCR92Ys9jD5vg"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/convince.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8qCrEiZTjPRuJ2Qq","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1000000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.z9FmdFVGOOW2kufm"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/hidden.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"hzQAaO1x5wYjovWb","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.yvw9bMgsrWQXuZN2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ruBTbGRqlMoy2uSz","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/talk.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GQMFWtp6IWJ6kqTY","name":"Crowns (cp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":8,"weight":0.02,"price":0.01,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.fBZcb1EdAbO4EEOl"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-copper.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"6IZsePloV317RsUb","name":"Dragons (pp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":31,"weight":0.02,"price":10,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.33dBhsz0KCjjGHYe"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-platinum.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"HNsCemxmNdyU8oWj","name":"Galifars (gp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":18,"weight":0.02,"price":1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.CbrYbcaa5bTV8Wnd"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-gold.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Mccx8d95umBCcVgu","name":"Sovereigns (sp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":13,"weight":0.02,"price":0.1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EeHD4BJl6bS0eE4D"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-silver.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ZZrY9N4uTnYeHmFJ","name":"Unarmed Strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":1600001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/fist.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"viVI0A8hOKiphIYf","name":"Hard To Kill","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This adventurer has more lives than a herd of cats. He may ignore his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} penalties when making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls to avoid <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Bleeding Out}</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"sort":1700001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bv1geyfk6c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.hpC41I3Bd56WPTu2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"OxOTu3tVXhC7SuOR","name":"Language (Goblin)","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.l2excT5ME0JSHPlt"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/talk.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Ztr1Bk75mYSxdGBk","name":"Language (Orcish)","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.B8Z0BJ0B2ULcZFmw"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/talk.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"OjClOI9rUxpGZzAk","name":"Primal Brute","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Orc]{Orcs} focus on core strength and fitness over coordination and flexibility. They treat @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} as linked to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} for purposes of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Advancement}. The character may also resist @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Tests} with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} if she chooses.</p>\n<p>Finally, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Orc]{orcs} increase the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Short Range} of any thrown item by +1. Double that for the adjusted @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Medium Range} , and double again for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Long Range}. If a thrown item&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range} is 3/6/12, for example, an @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Orc]{orc's} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range}&nbsp;is 4/8/16.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":500000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NvIGTQvwpA2rek6y"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/orc-head.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"rH80hW5tO49T5w2e","name":"Primal Passion","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Orc]{Orcs} are reactive and driven by a primal passion. They often take action without thinking things through.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":300000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lTwGLJJQ4OHToNdH"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/orc-head.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"OPVs1YgdIAhfCDb8","name":"Low Light Vision","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Low Light Vision ignores penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim and Dark Illumination} (but not @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Pitch Darkness}).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.OL3T8otZVCkOoir3"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/angry-eyes.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"XTcEpotbqRd3eOqI","name":"Ranger","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>For those who relish the thrill of the hunt, there are only predators and prey. From scouts, to trackers, or bounty hunters, all rangers share the predator&rsquo;s perspective. They value skill with weapons. They excel at stalking even the most elusive game. They train relentlessly to defeat a wide range of quarries.</p>\n<p>Knowledgeable, patient, and skilled hunters, rangers pursue man, beast, and monster alike. While some track dangerous creatures to protect the frontier, others pursue more cunning game&mdash;even fugitives&mdash;into and through the dangerous wilds.</p>\n<p>Rangers gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Enemy]{Favored Enemy}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Favored Terrain]{Favored Terrain}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wilderness Stride (Ranger)]{Wilderness Stride}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Shooting d6+, Survival d6+"}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Bg4PlFNiRBcMLnV1"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"l5usA29QJ3uAsSVe","name":"Favored Enemy (Humanoid)","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rangers study their foes, learning their ways, how to find them, and how to defeat them. Choose a type of enemy (Aberration, Animal, Construct, Dragon, Elemental, Fey, Giant, Humanoid (two), Monstrosity, Ooze, Outsider, Plant, Undead, or Vermin). The ranger gets one free reroll when failing to track (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Survival]{Survival}) or attack (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}) that type of being.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Ranger"}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.PkbIGXl469hlrShV"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"2e4fyPeOypPWtCHj","name":"Favored Terrain (Urban)","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Choose a terrain type (Arctic, Desert, Forest, Jungle, Plains, Hills/ Mountains, Rivers/Seas, Swamp, Urban, or Underground). The ranger draws an additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} for initiative when in his Favored Terrain.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Ranger"}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.dMaDYf9oH0K5SJC2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"3XKJzerOeipNTYGO","name":"Wilderness Stride (Ranger)","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Rangers pass through rough terrain such as dense forest, rocky hills, or desert sands with ease. They ignore movement penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Difficult Ground} through these types of terrain.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Ranger"}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.aHAnRkhc92Pm6ZFf"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"3ILvhC7Mep7qfrUM","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2200000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/punch.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"KmWspTGfFOMnQCQh","name":"Healing","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Healing has multiple uses, from treating @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} to diagnosing diseases and analyzing certain kinds of forensic evidence.</p>\n<p>See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{Healing} for rules on mending and treating @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds}, and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hazards]{Hazards} for treatment of disease or poison.</p>\n<p><strong>Forensics: </strong> Healing can also be used to analyze evidence that relates to anatomical trauma, including cause and time of death, angle of attack, and similar matters. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} provides basic information and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} increases the details uncovered.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Dc50EUXxlsJl7sph"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/medical-pack.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"C3gWjpos0SLoTR16","name":"Intimidation","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Intimidation is the art of frightening an opponent so that he backs down, reveals information, or flees.</p>\n<p>Intimidation is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} resisted by the opponent&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. In combat, this is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}. Out of combat, a successful roll means the foe backs down for the most part, reveals some information, or slinks away when the opportunity presents itself.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} might mean he backs down for the remainder of the scene, spills all the beans, or runs away as fast as he can.</p>\n<p>In or out of combat, a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} means the target is immune to this character&rsquo;s Intimidation attempts for the remainder of this encounter!</p>\n<p><strong>Networking:</strong> Intimidation can also be used as a &ldquo;macro&rdquo; skill to simulate several hours of working the streets. See&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}&nbsp;to see how to crack some heads for favors or information.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.RrgAZp50CgQyyY6w"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/arrest.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"auMDgPKIhzlLLaqQ","name":"Survival","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Survival allows a character to find food, water, or shelter in hostile environments. It can also be used to navigate wilderness environments, figure out which plants are good to eat and which aren&rsquo;t, and so on.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} Survival roll provides enough food and water for one person for one day; or five people with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p>More detailed information on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hunger]{Hunger} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Thirst]{Thirst} can be found under @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hazards]{Hazards} section.</p>\n<p><strong>Tracking: </strong>Survival can also be used to detect and follow tracks. Each roll generally covers following the tracks for one mile, but the GM should adjust this as needed for specific circumstances.</p>\n<p>The Game Master should assign a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{bonus or penalty} based on the target, environment, and time. Tracking a large group that recently passed through a snow-covered area might grant a bonus of +4, while following a single person over rocks and streams after more than a day incurs a &minus;4 penalty.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.15aEAJjDEjQy4fHF"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/camping-tent.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"08qhZlu1CplZZU5f","name":"Arcana","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Arcana reflects knowledge about spells, artifacts, magic items, eldritch symbols, magical traditions, dragons, forbidden lore, magical beasts, analyzing alchemical compounds and other ritual paraphernalia, translate magical runes, guess what spell was cast based on physical evidence left behind, etc.</p>\n<p>A successful Arcana roll reveals basic information about a magical topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lr6HSv7xgo5Dsp1N"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/skills/spell-book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"gkbd9tPeaIOKwehv","name":"Menacing","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Being a brutish lout isn&rsquo;t always a drawback if you know how to use it. Menacing allows a character to put her bad looks or worse attitude to good use. The goon adds +2 to her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} rolls.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, any one of Bloodthirsty, Mean, Ruthless, or Ugly"}},"sort":2600000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1nt716ztwfa","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Social Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.WRpK5JTq57sLcfOq"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"VajIz6xF07u3qkuf","name":"Streetwise","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Streetwise characters know how to find the local black market, fence stolen goods, avoid the local law (or criminal element!), lay low when the heat&rsquo;s on, obtain illegal weapons, find out which &ldquo;boss&rdquo; is hiring muscle, or similar shady activities.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Streetwise characters add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} rolls made to </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">&nbsp;with shady or criminal elements.<br /></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">They also add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls pertaining to the types of disreputable activities listed above</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+"}},"sort":2700000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1nt716ztwfa","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Social Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.9dkUUjYdfSoYx10K"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"qULrQTVV58u9OeIV","name":"Inquisitive","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Investigators spend a great deal of time researching ancient legends, working the streets, or deducing devilish mysteries. Some of these heroes are actual inquiisitives while others are sleuthing mages in a fantasy world or inquisitive college professors stumbling upon Things Man Was Not Meant to Know.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Investigators add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Lore]{Lore} rolls and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls made to search through desks for important papers, sift through stacks of junk mail for something of note, or spy obscured items from piles of junk or debris</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d8+, Lore d8+"}},"sort":2000000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_4wzuhu4mbqi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.U1BHSc8oduMJ8HXf"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Q7E4RSzJs81tQgHr","name":"Leather Pants","type":"armor","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":3,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"minStr":"d4","armor":1,"isNaturalArmor":false,"locations":{"head":false,"torso":false,"arms":false,"legs":true}},"sort":700000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.XWQhf1v5NNWGhX4p"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/armored-pants.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"CsdRp2td1Ym76FZC","name":"Chain Mail Hauberk","type":"armor","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":25,"price":75,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"minStr":"d8","armor":3,"isNaturalArmor":false,"locations":{"head":false,"torso":true,"arms":true,"legs":false}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.X3b7JulU9PXYrUp6"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/chain-mail.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"CMU5TuD8NhnvGgWg","name":"Axe, Throwing","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":2,"weight":2,"price":5,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Athletics","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{"1ylr63s5au":{"name":"Fighting (melee)","type":"skill","rof":null,"skillMod":"","skillOverride":"Fighting","shotsUsed":null}}},"damage":"@str+d6","range":"3/6/12","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d6","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":100001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.7Ha6aPi228030yKu"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/fire-axe.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"F3vFtzrxCBiG9BqM","name":"Sword, Bastard","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>May be used @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Two Hands]{Two hands} (if so, it may Sweep and causes +1 damage)</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":6,"price":35,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{"h47pgxzbvy":{"name":"Sweep","type":"damage","rof":null,"skillMod":"","skillOverride":"","shotsUsed":null,"dmgOverride":"","dmgMod":"1"}}},"damage":"@str+d8","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"1","minStr":"d8","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":900001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.r8pPlPu74Xuf1f8d"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/two-handed-sword.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"KoVkiOY5OsOiIrfz","name":"Thievery","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Lockpicking, safecracking, picking pockets, sleight of hand, setting and disabling traps and similar acts of misdirection, sabotage, subterfuge, and manipulation are called Thievery.</p>\n<p>If used to pick a lock, crack a safe, disable a trap, or perform a simple unopposed action, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} opens or disables the device, and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} does it in less time, without tripping alarms, or whatever else the GM feels is appropriate.</p>\n<p>Sleight of hand, hiding or planting an item, or picking a pocket require a simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}. If foes are actively watching the character, Thievery is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice}.</p>\n<p>The Game Master should assign @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalties} for particularly difficult circumstances. Picking a heavy padlock might have a &minus;4 penalty, while hiding a revolver in bulky winter clothing might grant a +1 bonus. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} typically means the character is spotted or it takes too much time (after which the character can try again). A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} typically sets off the trap, alerts the victim, or jams the device so that it must be opened or interacted with in a different way.</p>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Using Thievery on an electronic device, such as a keypad, is limited by the thief&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Electronics]{Electronics} skill. Use the lowest of the two skills.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2800000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wZbyJkisWIfmcZNt"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/lockpicks.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"oRJBprz9Rwev0aW0","name":"Inquisitive's Kit","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Made popular by freelance inquisitives, this kit contains some of the most often-used tools of the investigation trade. This kit provides a +1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research] rolls made to investigate the scene of a crime or other mystery.</p>\n<p><strong>Components.</strong> An Inquisitive's Kit includes containers of various shapes and sizes made of glass, metal, and wood; fine silk gloves; mundane dusts and brushes; tweezers, picks, and probes; a magnifying lens; ink and quills; chalk and charcoal; parchment sheets; and a small journal for recording notes.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":300,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":700000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.cDnoy1i8tZCIgiGa"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/light-backpack.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"1Cy9OgR1dVK1gQoR","name":"Thieves' Tools","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This set of tools includes a small file, a set of lock picks, a small mirror mounted on a metal handle, a set of narrow-bladed scissors, and a pair of pliers.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":25,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.bhqKMj8ohGSLzkU3"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/lockpicks.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"wYe83re4k6zi1mqZ","name":"Backpack","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This leather knapsack has one large pocket that closes with a buckled strap and holds about 2 cubic feet of material. Some may have one or more smaller pockets on the sides.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":5100000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EJwgrkGHCSHskUnO"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/backpack.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"iJhSxJcbZzBQkerN","name":"Ballbearings","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Bag of 1,000.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":5200000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.U1XLH5b9Rq9pAeju"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/striking-balls.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"jdWM8kGSHU9mKzj7","name":"Bedroll","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This consists of two woolen sheets sewn together along the bottom and one side to create a bag for sleeping in. Some have cloth straps along the open side so the bedroll can be tied closed while you are sleeping. It can be rolled and tied into a tight coil for storage or transport. Most people use a blanket with the bedroll to stay warm or provide a ground cushion.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":5300000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.u4QC3ltQoRK2ucM7"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/duffel-bag.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"nozeLM1ctnrfeC7J","name":"Candle","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>One hour, 2\" radius. A candle dimly illuminates a small area.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":5,"weight":0,"price":0.01,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":300000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.cbchY2qIVWn80f8T"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/candle-light.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"DrIWz2c7aFMkojfc","name":"Crowbar","type":"gear","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":800000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.tFYD2qtpz8upwqqy"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/crowbar.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"84qHWouqXFYUN3cc","name":"Healer's Kit","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This is a leather pouch containing bandages, salves, and splints. Five uses, see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{Healing}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":5,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Hj0l7X9YL5sEaGpW"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/first-aid-kit.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"bPX9d7qDNJEW1nCN","name":"Ink","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This vial contains 1 ounce of ink. Ink in colors other than black costs twice as much.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":8,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":1300000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.SL5djuvy1ajzLILp"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/quill-ink.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"4MUVZNX1simyeAJm","name":"Inkpen","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This is a wooden stylus with a metal tip that retains a small amount of ink after you dip it in a vial of ink.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0.1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":1400000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.K9ejgX2dnb8jAsQM"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/quill-ink.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"hpmrcNr8DK5MEBaB","name":"Manacles","type":"gear","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":1900000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.LMK3iTpNMaY41r16"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/handcuffs.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"7pzCTnWLq6fmlTFH","name":"Mirror","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This hand-held mirror is about a foot across. Unlike many higher-quality glass mirrors, this one is made out of polished steel and sturdy enough that you can drop it without risk of breakage.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":10,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":2100000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.QaJD9VBa6lwEKoCJ"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/mirror-mirror.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"XNrxHLZDYZ0h3xrS","name":"Tinderbox","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This small container holds flint, tire steel, and tinder (usually dry cloth soaked in light oil) used to kindle a tire. Using it to light a torch-or anything else with abundant, exposed fuel-takes an action. Lighting any other tire takes 1 minute.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0.5,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":4700000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.oEZYgJYtv6TmTuYZ"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/match-head.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Ek32FNnf2iCiTDj1","name":"String","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>4 yards.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0.1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":4100000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.tnQ8YB7peihKRNoi"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/sewing-string.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Xf8hYo2ysUHPwM2P","name":"Whistle","type":"gear","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0.05,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":5000000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.qBsPNCBjGFCtfej4"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/whistle.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"RLxfQKps2esEpIEO","name":"Trouble Magnet","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Things never go smoothly for this hero. As a Minor Hindrance, whenever the character rolls a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} the consequences are subtly worse in some way, as determined by the Dungeon Master. A hero isn't just spotted trying to infiltrate a a Brelish Camp, someone recognizes her face. A would be savior doesn't just fail at Intimidation, the target also has friends. Or a botched attack roll results in the adventurer's weapon busting too.</p>\n<p>The Major Hindrance has a different effect. Anytime the Dungeon Master must choose a \"random character\" to be hit, attacked, or otherwise negatively affected by something&mdash;it&rsquo;s this poor devil.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Deadlands Wierd West</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":1400000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.9ewPq88hGY0TZvT9"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"m40fmzjHdcOZxrFZ","name":"Habit (chews swamp weed)","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">(MINOR OR MAJOR)</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Your warrior has an annoying or dangerous compulsion. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Minor} Habit irritates those around her but isn&rsquo;t dangerous. Maybe she picks her nose, can&rsquo;t stop fiddling with her phone, says &ldquo;y&rsquo;know&rdquo; in the middle of every sentence, or chews and smacks her gum loudly and often. Allies avoid her if possible.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Major} </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Habit</span> is a physical or mental addiction of some sort that is debilitating or possibly even deadly. This includes drug use, chronic drinking, or perhaps even an addiction to virtual reality in a hightech setting.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">An addict who doesn&rsquo;t get his fix must make a</span> <span class=\"fontstyle0\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor}&nbsp;roll every 24 hours he goes without or take a level of </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Once every 24 hours, a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Healing]{Healing} roll with some sort of appropriate medicine removes one level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}&nbsp;for four hours. After that the Fatigue returns and can only be recovered with the addicting substance.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":5400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.DvgwzTd4xsaPE77h"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"zDBZJjftE5YXxAKt","name":"Arrogant","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Your hero doesn&rsquo;t think he&rsquo;s the best&mdash;he knows he is. Whether it&rsquo;s swordsmanship, kung fu, or painting, few compare to his skills and he flaunts it every chance he gets. Winning isn&rsquo;t enough for this champion. He wants to dominate his opponent and prove there&rsquo;s no one better. He&rsquo;s the kind of fighter who disarms an opponent in a duel just to pick the sword up and hand it back with a smirk. Arrogant individuals look for the greatest threat in battle, hacking their way through lesser minions only because they&rsquo;re in the way.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"sort":5500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.YpLBVlqcaIEy8oYq"}},"img":"