<strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n</ol>\n</div>"},"bennies":{"value":3,"max":4},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Druid","displayName":0,"img":"modules/savage-eberron-bestiary/assets/bestiary_tokens/humanoids/halfling/halfling-woodsman-01.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":"QTFndjGRCn3qCvLa","actorLink":true,"disposition":1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"gso7NeJMXpdXlU6X","name":"Untrained","type":"skill","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":600000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skill.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"RMmVU7ormCp2MOqN","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":700000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sAig03GZiFKqBX7p"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/jump-across.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BkQxvPAlZLOJY7OZ","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":800000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.8N1uMThntsjaUPem"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/gift-of-knowledge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GN2DOxOtwyROzNWZ","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":900000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xOmuCR92Ys9jD5vg"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/convince.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8qCrEiZTjPRuJ2Qq","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1000000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.z9FmdFVGOOW2kufm"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/hidden.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"hzQAaO1x5wYjovWb","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.yvw9bMgsrWQXuZN2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ruBTbGRqlMoy2uSz","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/talk.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GQMFWtp6IWJ6kqTY","name":"Crowns (cp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0.02,"price":0.01,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.fBZcb1EdAbO4EEOl"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-copper.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"6IZsePloV317RsUb","name":"Dragons (pp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0.02,"price":10,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.33dBhsz0KCjjGHYe"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-platinum.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"HNsCemxmNdyU8oWj","name":"Galifars (gp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0.02,"price":1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.CbrYbcaa5bTV8Wnd"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-gold.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Mccx8d95umBCcVgu","name":"Sovereigns (sp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0.02,"price":0.1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EeHD4BJl6bS0eE4D"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-silver.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ZZrY9N4uTnYeHmFJ","name":"Unarmed Strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":1600001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/fist.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"viVI0A8hOKiphIYf","name":"Hard To Kill","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This adventurer has more lives than a herd of cats. He may ignore his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} penalties when making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls to avoid <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Bleeding Out}</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"sort":1700001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bv1geyfk6c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.hpC41I3Bd56WPTu2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"4y9M6J6vJMzDnmQa","name":"Druid Armor Interference (Light)","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Bulky armor interferes with a druid&rsquo;s ability to sense and commune with nature. They subtract 4 from their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Faith]{Faith} rolls and from their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility-based} skill rolls when wearing medium or heavy armor, or using medium or heavy shields.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":300000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.KJFnSBzNgEYOTDJO"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"aivR718lWzCMB5gM","name":"Druidic Vow","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Druids have a major vow to serve and protect nature. Those who wish to draw energy from natural sources must uphold these principles.</p>\n<p>If the druid violates Eberron's trust (DM's call) the druid subtracts 2 from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Faith]{Faith} rolls for a week. Truly sacrilegious acts might rob her of her powers entirely until she atones in some way.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"sort":600000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ytlByHH2iyB7cpfX"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"capNBWrS7rboA3N7","name":"Arcane Background (Druid)","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Druid)]{Arcane Background (Druid)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"sort":500000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.AiuViCNsPg67wXyk"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"sT5tqy1MCZIFYbcN","name":"Druid","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Within the purity of the elements and the order of the wilds lingers a power beyond the marvels of civilization. Furtive yet undeniable, these primal magics are guarded by servants of philosophical balance known as druids. Allies to beasts and manipulators of nature, these protectors of the wild strive to shield their lands from all who would threaten them.</p>\n<p>Rewarded for their devotion with incredible powers, druids gain unparalleled shapeshifting abilities, the companionship of mighty beasts, and the power to call upon nature&rsquo;s wrath. The mightiest temper powers akin to storms, earthquakes, and volcanoes with wisdom long forgotten by civilization.</p>\n<p>Druids gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Druid)]{Arcane Background (Druid)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Druid Armor Interference (Light)]{Druid Armor Interference (Light)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Druidic Vow]{Druidic Vow}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Nature Bond]{Nature Bond}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Nature Sense]{Nature Sense}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wilderness Stride (Druid)]{Wilderness Stride}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Survival d6+, Faith d4+"}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.W4GxKShGuagr8Yb0"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"myQNp80SJsbjITzY","name":"Nature Bond (Attuned)","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A druid may attune herself to nature or a special animal companion.</p>\n<p>The bonds druids form with nature are deep and powerful. Choose one of these abilities:</p>\n<p><strong>Attuned:</strong> The druid gets one free reroll anytime she fails a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Faith]{Faith} roll to activate a spell.</p>\n<p><strong>Beast Master:</strong> The druid gains the Beast Master Edge. When subsequently taking the Edge, she can ignore the Rank requirement to make her companion a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Druid"}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.NISz9chZiTGrQ8WJ"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"7tGNxdtyuvWs3Bnv","name":"Nature Sense","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Druids commune with nature and its spirits. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Survival]{Survival} is linked to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} rather than @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Druid"}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.uqXSQRBuEBpOQzmO"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"kyPOuMbR5Fh45y1z","name":"Wilderness Stride (Druid)","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Druids pass through rough terrain such as dense forest, rocky hills, or desert sands with ease. They ignore movement penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Difficult Ground} in these kinds of terrain.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Druid"}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.mPxlxw1dG1CGKbel"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Qtz3xT5GQ0XvJpyb","name":"Healing","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Healing has multiple uses, from treating @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} to diagnosing diseases and analyzing certain kinds of forensic evidence.</p>\n<p>See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{Healing} for rules on mending and treating @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds}, and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hazards]{Hazards} for treatment of disease or poison.</p>\n<p><strong>Forensics: </strong> Healing can also be used to analyze evidence that relates to anatomical trauma, including cause and time of death, angle of attack, and similar matters. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} provides basic information and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} increases the details uncovered.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1800001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Dc50EUXxlsJl7sph"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/medical-pack.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"vFJwnVIJeMMzv0QE","name":"Woodsman","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Woodsmen are rangers, scouts, and hunters who are more at home in the wilderness than in urban areas. They are skilled trackers and scouts, and know how to live off the land for months at a time.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Woodsmen add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Survival]{Survival} rolls, and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} rolls made in the wild (not towns, ruins, or underground).</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+, Survival d8+"}},"sort":2100001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_4wzuhu4mbqi","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Professional Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.mTY5axyUKXjsEmmx"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"oGOrF19ybfgGEGtK","name":"Luck","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The adventurer seems to be blessed by fate, karma, the gods, or whatever external forces he believes in (or believe in him!). </span></p>\n<p>He draws one extra @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Benny} at the beginning of each game session, allowing him to succeed at important tasks more often than most, and survive incredible dangers.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9dc4ijzy8uh","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.a5BHUWx93nGoO2mo"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/woman-elf-face.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"OejPwYl1zwVao9Qu","name":"Brave","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Those with this Edge have learned to master their fear, or have dealt with so many horrors they&rsquo;ve become jaded. These valiant explorers add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear} checks and subtract 2 from </span><strong><span class=\"fontstyle2\">@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Fear Table]{Fear Table} </span></strong>results.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d6+"}},"sort":500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9dc4ijzy8uh","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.WJbfV0MEvQBjHEaE"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/woman-elf-face.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"NmBi6DeYUH2B1rkp","name":"Language (Halfling)","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EYk5HsLk3sstMnmu"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/talk.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"I1kdgw0LMBGL9Ilw","name":"Cosmology","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The planes of Eberron affect every aspect of the material world. This skill covers knowledge of the astral, ethereal, and shadow planes, the thirteen orbiting planes, their properties, planar influences, native inhabitants, and manifest zones connected to them on the material plane.</p>\n<p>For spells and magical effects related to the planes, use the Arcana Skill.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":300001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lZeftp1QnvCFzY8D"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/skills/solar-system.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"oJDcu6OnQX2ZYND1","name":"Animal Handling","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Animal Handling allows a hero to calm down an animal whether domestic or wild, intuit an animal's intention, or train an animal new tricks or behavior.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":100001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.vpHzreNDNjMKovUU"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/skills/labrador-head.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"qXM3B1iRA7PyzOvb","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2200001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/punch.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"oWoP61il4hfl8wrN","name":"Shooting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Shooting covers all attempts to hit a target with a ranged weapon such as a bow, pistol, or rocket launcher (thrown weapons use @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}). See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for details on ranged combat.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2300001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sOHfVvBDhe3Oy3r1"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/crosshair.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BKGIYcXKmOTADpwK","name":"Riding","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p>Riding allows a hero to mount, control, and ride any beast or beast-drawn vehicle common to his setting. This includes horses, camels, dragons, wagons, chariots, and the like. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mounted Combat]{Mounted Combat}.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2400001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.DHKzenDEPdjw3X2u"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/saddle.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"YthttKhuRR1kAWry","name":"Wild Shape","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The druid gains the <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Shape Change]{shape change}</em> spell, if she doesn&rsquo;t already have it. The Duration is one hour for her, and she casts as if she were one @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} higher than her actual @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} on the&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Shape Change]{shape change}</em>&nbsp;table.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Druid"}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.rVU86Ao0mN6MvGSt"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ueMjEcgdFkobRBOw","name":"Common Bond","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Selfless heroes and determined leaders know their greatest strength often comes from their companions, and are willing to give some of their own fortune, fate, or luck to support them.<br />A character with this Edge may freely give her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} to any other character she can communicate with. The player should explan what form this takes, from a quick shout of encouragement to a welcome pat on the back</span> </p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wild Card, Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"sort":2500001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_1nt716ztwfa","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Social Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.8o2F1b4DT8onc9Xt"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"RtgHYzf2BXSCYUuI","name":"Bones of the Ancestors","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Divination}</p>\n<p>By casting gem-inlaid sticks, rolling dragon bones, laying out ornate cards, or employing some other divining tool, you receive an omen from an otherworldly entity about the results of a specific course of action that you plan to take within the next 30 minutes, The DM chooses from the following possible omens:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Weal</em>, for good results</li>\n<li><em>Woe</em>, for bad results</li>\n<li><em>Weal and woe</em>, for both good and bad results</li>\n<li><em>Nothing</em>, for results that aren't especially good or bad</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The spell doesn't take into account any possible circumstances that might change the outcome, such as the casting of additional spells or the loss or gain of a companion.</p>\n<p>If you cast the spell two or more times before 24 hours pass, there is a cumulative 25 percent chance for each casting after the first that you get a random reading. The DM makes this roll in secret.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Faith","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Casting of dinosaur bones","arcane":"Druid","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":300000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Item.wEY9tJSSjazIL3fd"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"3ft5eyl1kMQY1szy","name":"Protection of the Ancients","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p>Adventurers sometimes travel beneath the waves, through planes of fire, or other hazardous environments. This power protects them from crushing depths, scathing heat, intense cold, and even radiation.</p>\n<p>Environmental protection allows the target to breathe, speak, and move at his normal @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} in an otherwise fatal environment. It protects him from intense heat, cold, radiation, pressure, and lack of oxygen.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} increases the Duration to eight hours.</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li><strong>Enviromental Resistance (+1):</strong> The power now offers environmental resistance, reducing damage from one energy source (fire, cold, electricity, etc.) by 4 (6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Faith","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"One hour","trapping":"Symbol of ash marked on forehead","arcane":"Druid","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":1700000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lUxJHMkJaDYzMAMz"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"6y450SiRKEI0p8ux","name":"Summon Spirts of Nature","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p>Animals have long been associated with wizards, whether it be the familiars of witches or the fetish beasts of shamans. <em>Summon Beast</em> allows a user to summon mundane animals.</p>\n<p>A character may learn this spell while a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Novice}, but cannot summon any larger creatures until he attains the appropriate @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank}. It materializes anywhere in Range, and with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll, it&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Resilient]{Resilient} as well.</p>\n<p>The beast acts on its creator's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} and follows her basic commands to the best of its ability.</p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Summon Beast</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Rank</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Cost</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Servant</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Novice</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1 small animal</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Seasoned</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>1 medium animal or swarm of rats, birds, insects, or other vermin, or 2 small animals</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Veteran</td>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>1 large, 2 medium or swarms, or 4 small animals</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Heroic</td>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>1 huge, 2 large, 4 medium or swarms, or 6 small animals</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Legendary</td>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>2 huge, 4 large, 6 medium or swarms, or 8 small animals</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Small creatures have a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} less than zero. Medium creatures are Size +0 to Size +3. Large covers Size +4 to +7, and Huge is +8 or larger. Swarms share a similar set of statistics and fill a Medium Burst Template.</p>\n<p>The beast is under the total control of the summoner for the Duration of the spell.</p>\n<p>Animals can only be summoned in their natural terrain. So while a wizard may be able to summon a swarm of rats in Sharn, only on the open plains can he call a lion to his side.</p>\n<p>Summoned creatures appear from the nearest appropriate terrain. For instance, rats swarm out of sewers, a lion emerges from jungle or grass on the savannah, and a swarm of birds descends from the clouds or erupts from the trees. If in doubt, assume the beasts \"appear\" 1d10 x 2 yards away from the caster. When the Duration expires, the animal leaves of its own accord.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><strong><em>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</em></strong></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Duration (+1):</strong>&nbsp;<em>Summon beast's </em>Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds.</li>\n<li><strong>Increased Trait (+1):&nbsp;</strong> The caster can increase a Trait one die type for 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}. She may do this for as many Traits as she likes, but only once per Trait.</li>\n<li><strong>Mind Rider (+1):</strong>&nbsp;The caster can communicate and sense through the beast.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Faith","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Chanting to the spirits","arcane":"Druid","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":3900000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Item.t665pEYOCFywfEOb"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"qUOCJOIhmIZPwYWU","name":"Gift of the Spirits","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p>Many cultures have legends of shamans or wizards who take on the shape of animals. This power does just that, allowing the caster to take the form of any animal (including fantastic creatures such as dragons and hippogriffs, but not humanoids, undead, etc).</p>\n<p>What a character can change into depends on his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank}:</p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Shape Change</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Cost</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Rank</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Size</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>Novice</td>\n<td>Size &minus;4 to Size &minus;1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>Seasoned</td>\n<td>Size 0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>Veteran</td>\n<td>Size 1 to 2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>11</td>\n<td>Heroic</td>\n<td>Size 3 to 4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>15</td>\n<td>Legendary</td>\n<td>Size 5 to 10</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>With a&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}&nbsp;on the roll, the character transforms into a&nbsp; particularly large version of its type&mdash;increase its @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} by one die type each.</p>\n<p>Weapons and other personal effects are assumed into the animal&rsquo;s form and reappear when the power ends, but other objects are dropped.</p>\n<p>While transformed, the character retains his own&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges}, and linked @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{skills} (though he may not be able to use some or all of them depending on the form -- GM&rsquo;s call). He gains the animal&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor}, and linked @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{skills} and cannot use devices that require humanoid form. He has no capacity for speech and cannot activate @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Powers]{powers}, though he may continue to maintain powers previously active.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bestiary]{creature&rsquo;s} natural abilities inherent to its form are conferred, but magical ones aren&rsquo;t. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Dragon]{dragon}&nbsp;can fly and breathe fire in a traditional fantasy setting, for example, so a character who <em>shape changes </em>into one may do so as well. If dragons also cast spells in that world, however, <em>shape change </em>would not grant that ability because it&rsquo;s not inherent to the physical form.</p>\n<p><strong>Size</strong>: The caster does not inherit extra @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wounds} when transforming into creatures of Large or Huge @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Duration (+1):</strong> <em>Shape change's </em>Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds.</li>\n<li><strong>Speech (+1):</strong> The recipient retains the power of speech (but still cannot activate @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Powers]{powers}).</li>\n<li><strong>Transform (+2/+3</strong>): The power may affect others at a Range of Touch for +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} or Smarts for +3 (the Range Modifier may increase this further). Unwilling targets resist with an opposed @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll and if transformed, may make another @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll at the end of each of their turns to shake off the effect (at &ndash;2 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}). Otherwise, the power lasts for the normal Duration.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Faith","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"One hour","trapping":"Tattoos of animals on body.","arcane":"Druid","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":3300000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.6bHPHZLb8QvoDhzU"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"kof6xvotfwkkvIBk","name":"Faith","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p>Faith is the arcane skill required for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Background (Miracles)]{Arcane Background (Miracles)}.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":4000000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.YI5rxzYzsqXwAo9A"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/prayer.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"gm-notes":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_2mncjgs233x","path":"Savage Eberron Characters#/CF_SEP/Pregens","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Pc5KhyWMjcRiMosU"}
