.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} penalties when making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls to avoid <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Bleeding Out}</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"sort":1700001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bv1geyfk6c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.hpC41I3Bd56WPTu2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"dfNfw4jKMIvNLg5N","name":"Slender (Elf)","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Elf]{Elves} are graceful but more frail than other races. Their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} is reduced by 1 and they have a &minus;1 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} checks.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"sort":700000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.6HeXl41e1tDzQbk6"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/woman-elf-face.svg","effects":[{"_id":"M2EYP15qrztQlsu1","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.value","value":"-1","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/woman-elf-face.svg","label":"Slender","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"jUPwATZYih39tBwL","name":"Elven Magical Nature","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Elf]{Elves} were born of ancient giant magic and have an inherent connection to arcane energies. @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Elf]{Elves}&nbsp;get a free reroll when rolling to resist enemy powers.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":600000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.mp7hX4aqPghrxsv2"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/woman-elf-face.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Rl51ys8EJX4EfASk","name":"Language (Elvish)","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.WgSQwh3EwSnLYsVD"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/talk.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"WVTFq3UG6EjfX9hY","name":"Low Light Vision","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Low Light Vision ignores penalties for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim and Dark Illumination} (but not @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Pitch Darkness}).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.OL3T8otZVCkOoir3"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/angry-eyes.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"QHd70fwDBu801Gv3","name":"Wizard","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Beyond the veil of the mundane hide the secrets of absolute power. Legends, mysteries, and wonders of arcane realms call to those with the ambition&mdash;and the intellect&mdash;to rise above the common folk to grasp true might. Such is the path of the wizard.</p>\n<p>These shrewd magic-users research, collect, and covet esoteric knowledge. Some choose to become a master of a particular field of magical study. Others embrace versatility, reveling in the unbounded wonders of all magic. In either case, wizards prove a cunning and potent lot, capable of smiting their foes, empowering their allies, and shaping the world to their every desire.</p>\n<p>Wizards have the following abilities.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Wizard)]{Arcane Background (Wizard)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Arcane Bond]{Arcane Bond}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Schools]{Schools}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Spellbooks]{Spellbooks}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Wizard Armor Interference&nbsp;(Cloth)]{Wizard Armor Interference (Cloth)}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Smarts d6+, Arcana d6+"}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.8BOd0526OKnzdoU4"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"YlpZtH7RU1LUTuu1","name":"Wizard Armor Interference (Cloth)","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Like sorcerers, wizards must gesticulate in precise patterns. They subtract 4 from their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} rolls&nbsp;and from their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility-based} skill rolls&nbsp;when wearing light, medium, or heavy armor, or using light, medium, or heavy shields.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":100000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ZWL8WB1oXG9OVkOY"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"EvY0UtHRnOPUo0R6","name":"Spellbooks","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Wizard spells are strange, complex things that fade quickly from the minds of even the most accomplished casters. For this reason, each wizard maintains a spellbook with the spells he&rsquo;s translated and acquired. He studies them daily, transcribing their mystical patterns onto his mind.</p>\n<p>The link to the book is far more than rote memorization&mdash;it is an arcane bond with the power and patterns within. If a wizard doesn&rsquo;t have access to his spellbook, he may continue to cast normally until the next sunset or sunrise (whichever comes first). After that, the magical imprint on his mind fades and he can no longer cast them.</p>\n<p>Wizards may only carry one active spellbook at a time. The mountains of scrolls, magical notations, and research needed to prepare another cannot be carried with the wizard and must be stored safely somewhere. It takes a week of work and 500 gp to create a replacement spellbook once the wizard has access to his magical notes.</p>\n<p>When a wizard finds a new spellbook or scroll, the spells it contains become available as choices to the wizard when he next chooses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.New Powers]{New Powers} Edge. Moreover, a wizard taking the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.New Powers]{New Powers}&nbsp;Edge can learn a third new power, if all the new powers are learned from scrolls and spellbooks.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wizard"}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.YPX017alaLikmNOO"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"yCBsEp8py55nVg8H","name":"Arcane Bond (Bonded Object)","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Wizards form an intense magical bond with an object or creature.</p>\n<p>Wizards immerse themselves in the study of eldritch lore and arcane theories. During these long hours they form a bond with a dependable item or friendly creature (a &ldquo;@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Familiars]{familiar}&rdquo;). Choose one of the following options for your wizard:</p>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Bonded Object: </strong>The spellcaster possesses an amulet, ring, staff, wand, or weapon that adds +1 to all his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} totals when worn or in hand. If the object is lost or destroyed, the mage can replace it with a new object worth at least 500 gp.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Familiars]{Familiar}:</strong> The mage has a magical pet.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wizard"}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.cc9G5TuUayqBVXnX"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"gK6NoquXSIOZtINS","name":"Arcana","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Arcana reflects knowledge about spells, artifacts, magic items, eldritch symbols, magical traditions, dragons, forbidden lore, magical beasts, analyzing alchemical compounds and other ritual paraphernalia, translate magical runes, guess what spell was cast based on physical evidence left behind, etc.</p>\n<p>A successful Arcana roll reveals basic information about a magical topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1800001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lr6HSv7xgo5Dsp1N"},"cf":{"id":"temp_v8ypmxc2q0l","path":"Skills","color":"#008000"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/skills/spell-book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8F1oFJkhz5mvvsDg","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1900001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/punch.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"9KWSvyv7vWCaUnDD","name":"Spellcasting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p>Mages, wizards, warlocks, and witches use Spellcasting to cast spells. See the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Background (Magic)]{Arcane Background (Magic)} Edge.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":10,"modifier":null},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2000001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.MWPNuINyQk9xComt"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/spell-book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"lUuDk5EZrQ5PTRYz","name":"Lore","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Lore reflects knowledge and your ability to recall bits of information about history, archaeology, different Ages, legends, other continents, literature, song, poetry, and similar fields. This would also include knowledge about the more common races of the worlds.</p>\n<p>If an explorer wants to remember when the Dhakaani empire collapsed or know when the Qualabrin were destroyed on Xen'drik, this is the skill to have.</p>\n<p>A successful Lore roll reveals basic information about a topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron replaces Academics</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":700001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.E0BVumGwbaczoPjD"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/skills/bookshelf.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"0E8rYBQLyFD8js0m","name":"Shooting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Shooting covers all attempts to hit a target with a ranged weapon such as a bow, pistol, or rocket launcher (thrown weapons use @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}). See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for details on ranged combat.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2100001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sOHfVvBDhe3Oy3r1"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/crosshair.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"kZFqiXSbDgXCxQ3R","name":"Cosmology","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The planes of Eberron affect every aspect of the material world. This skill covers knowledge of the astral, ethereal, and shadow planes, the thirteen orbiting planes, their properties, planar influences, native inhabitants, and manifest zones connected to them on the material plane.</p>\n<p>For spells and magical effects related to the planes, use the Arcana Skill.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":300001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lZeftp1QnvCFzY8D"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/skills/solar-system.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Zenus0l3Gg5JzRUP","name":"Arrogant","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Your hero doesn&rsquo;t think he&rsquo;s the best&mdash;he knows he is. Whether it&rsquo;s swordsmanship, kung fu, or painting, few compare to his skills and he flaunts it every chance he gets. Winning isn&rsquo;t enough for this champion. He wants to dominate his opponent and prove there&rsquo;s no one better. He&rsquo;s the kind of fighter who disarms an opponent in a duel just to pick the sword up and hand it back with a smirk. Arrogant individuals look for the greatest threat in battle, hacking their way through lesser minions only because they&rsquo;re in the way.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"sort":2300001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.YpLBVlqcaIEy8oYq"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"pUIQqsS0kdG9kXN1","name":"Hesitant","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Your hero hesitates in stressful situations. Draw two @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Cards} in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{combat} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{act} on the lowest. If you draw a Joker, use it normally and ignore the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance} for the round (hence this being a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Minor} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance}, it actually increases your chances of drawing a Joker!)</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\"> Hesitant characters cannot take the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Quick]{Quick} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Level Headed]{Level Headed} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges}.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":2400001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.aLzHhQGScJ7XzywT"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"OwaaAxKysgpzsbJ2","name":"Quirk (Constantly reading)","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This individual has some minor foible that is usually humorous but can occasionally cause him real trouble. A swashbuckler may always try to slash his initials on his foes, a dwarf may brag constantly about his culture, or a snobby d&eacute;butante might not eat, drink, or socialize with the lower class, for example.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":2500001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.y0lUBhYHhl2LdjZZ"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"MbR2SrkG2TJJvnK0","name":"Arcane Background (Wizard)","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Arcane Background (Wizard)]{Arcane Background (Wizard)}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"sort":400000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.0cILksGLzuFqCSxP"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"JECNzd0a1kY0IF9H","name":"Ice Bolt","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evocation}</p>\n<p><em>Bolt</em>&nbsp;sends damaging bursts of energy, streaks of holy light, or shards of matter toward one&rsquo;s foes.</p>\n<p>There are no @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Attacks]{Range} penalties, but the&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{arcane skill roll} is affected by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{Cover}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination}, and all other usual @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalties}.</p>\n<p>The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{damage} of the <em>bolt </em>is 2d6, or 3d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Damage (+2):</strong> The <em>bolt</em> causes 3d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{damage} (4d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Disintegrate (+2):</strong> If the <em>bolt </em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitates} a creature, it immediately dies and its body disintegrates. If the target is an object, everything in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Small Blast Template} disintegrates.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Bolt (+4):</strong> The <em>bolt</em> causes 4d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{Damage} (5d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Rate of Fire (+2):</strong> The <em>bolt </em>attack is made at @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Rate of Fire]{Rate of Fire} 2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Spellcasting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"2d6","range":"Smarts x 2","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Shard of ice from the wand","arcane":"Wizard","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":600000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VJEfX52o7ArBwWei"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"NKIwcu5vHMu2ve5c","name":"Schools (Universalist)","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A wizard&rsquo;s intense studies lead him down two paths&mdash;a &ldquo;universalist&rdquo; who dabbles in all the various &ldquo;@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{schools}&rdquo; of magic, or a &ldquo;specialist&rdquo; who focuses on one @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{school}&nbsp;at the expense of some others.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Specialists</strong></em> designate one favored @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{school} and two opposition @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{schools} from the list below. They gain one free reroll when casting spells from their favored @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{school}, but spells cast from their opposition @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{school} cost one additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} and suffer a &minus;2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} penalty.</p>\n<p>Opposition spells should be marked with an asterisk in a character&rsquo;s power lists, like this: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Banish]{banish}*</em>.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Universalists</strong></em> have no favored or opposed @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{schools}, and thus gain none of the advantages or disadvantages of specialists.</p>\n<p>Here are the various schools</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Abjuration}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Divination}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evocation}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Illusion}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Necromancy}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Wizard"}},"sort":300000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.7NeqieVUj6AdPeT0"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"THKCmJa96v7gUmeD","name":"Detect/Conceal Arcana","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Divination}</p>\n<p><em>Detect arcana </em>allows the recipient of the power to see and detect all supernatural persons, objects, or effects in sight for five rounds. This includes <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{invisible}</em> foes, enchantments on people or items, weird science devices, and so on. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the caster knows the type of enchantment as well.</p>\n<p>When used on a supernatural creature, the caster learns its active powers and arcane abilities. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, he knows @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Weakness]{Weaknesses} common to that creature type. This doesn&rsquo;t reveal @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Weakness]{Weaknesses} of unique individuals, if any. Those must usually be discovered through research or trial and error.</p>\n<p><strong>Invisible Creatures:</strong> <em>Detect arcana </em>also allows a character to ignore up to 4 points of penalties when attacking foes hidden by magical darkness, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{invisibility}, or similar abilities (or all penalties with a raise).</p>\n<p><em>Conceal arcana</em> obscures one being or item of Normal Scale or smaller from the detect magic ability for one hour (see Detect Magic on page 169 and the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size Table]{Size Table}). For larger creatures, increase the cost based on the Scale Modifier (+2 PPs for Large, +4 PPs for Huge, or +6 PPs for Gargantuan).</p>\n<p>With a success, attempts to <em>detect arcana</em> on the being or item suffer a &ndash;2 penalty or &ndash;4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. If <em>detect arcana</em> fails, the character cannot see through the ruse with this casting and is not aware it is concealed unless presented with obvious evidence of such (for example, the attack of an invisible foe).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one viewer for <em>detect</em>, or item for <em>conceal</em>, for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li><strong>Alignment Sense (+1):</strong> The caster can sense the presence and exact location of supernatural good or evil within range. Detect arcana activated with Alignment Sense no longer requires line of sight to locate creatures.</li>\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+1/+2):</strong> <em>Conceal&nbsp;</em>only. The power affects everything in a sphere the size of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template} for +1 points, or a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template} for +2.</li>\n<li><strong>Identify (+1):</strong> The caster can identify a magic item's powers and how they work.</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (+1):</strong> <em>Conceal </em>only. <em>Detection </em>rolls to see through the <em>concealment </em>are made at &minus;2. This stacks with the additional penalty for casting with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Spellcasting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5 (detect); one hour (conceal)","trapping":"Waving hands, whispered words.","arcane":"Wizard","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":4300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_eu5zd8ame7m","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.wKQFjlig5q7Q2OXn"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"UzUoDpLmMmxudBMs","name":"Aura of Siberys","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Abjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Protection</em> creates a field of energy or armor around a character, giving him 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor}. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the bonus is applied to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} instead (and therefore immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{Armor Piercing} modifiers).</p>\n<p>Whether the protection is visible or not depends on the Trapping&mdash;this is entirely up to the caster.</p>\n<p><em>Protection</em> stacks with all other armor, natural or worn.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Spellcasting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"5","trapping":"A mystical light glow","arcane":"Wizard","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":2900000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.XZyjBh2300ebhcYI"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"LDnHJhdRSRjLOfJ1","name":"Conjure Item","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p>The caster can create an object weighing up to one pound for every 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} spent. The item must be a simple, mundane object made of a common material (GM&rsquo;s call) such as a 10-foot pole, blanket, shield, etc. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll produces an more durable version of the conjured item.</p>\n<p>Conjured items appear in the hands of the caster or on the ground nearby. Once the Duration expires, the item fades from reality. This can cause issues, for example, if the conjured item holds a door open or was given as a gift.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Pathfinder</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Complexity (+2):&nbsp;</strong>The item conjured cab have modest artistry and modest complex moving parts.</li>\n<li><strong>Complete (+1): </strong>The object is a complete set, such as a chess set or a quiver of arrows. The set must fit under the weight limit.</li>\n<li><strong>Create Food and Water (Special):</strong> Instead of an object, every 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} creates enough food and water to sustain a Size 0 humanoid for one day. The nourishing food is permanent (doesn&rsquo;t disappear after you eat it), although it decays and becomes inedible after 24 hours if not consumed. The water is just like clean rainwater and does not spoil.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Creation (+4): </strong>For +4 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}, the object created can have the volume of 1 cubic foot per 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} spent rather than one pound.</li>\n<li><strong>Durable (+1 per pound):</strong> The object&rsquo;s Duration becomes &ldquo;permanent&rdquo; until dispelled. The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} are &ldquo;invested&rdquo; and unavailable until it&rsquo;s destroyed, dispelled, or dismissed by the caster. The conjurer may dismiss the object at any time, regardless of sight, distance, or other factors. His Power Points then begin recharging normally.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Spellcasting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"One hour","trapping":"Energy shaped from the wand tip","arcane":"Wizard","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":null,"core":{"sourceId":"Item.k40oRcXSOqofazsY"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"NJMouDru6ztYG1JE","name":"Anti-Magic Aura","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Abjuration}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} with arcane protection means hostile powers suffer a &minus;2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalty} (&minus;4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}) to affect this character.</p>\n<p>If the power causes harm, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{damage} is also reduced a like amount. Arcane Protection stacks with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Arcane Resistance]{Arcane Resistance} should the recipient have both!</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}&nbsp;each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Arcane Protection (+2):&nbsp;</strong> Hostile powers suffer a &minus;4 penalty (&minus;6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Spellcasting","skillMod":"+1","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"5","trapping":"Glow of deflective energy","arcane":"Wizard","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":200000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.hDK8ufDJ5YtTLUwf"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"iyIwXujgimUtx0Vq","name":"Summon Ally","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p>This power allows the character to summon a magical servant from nothing. The ally typically takes the form of a basic humanoid of the appropriate Size but can appear differently based on the caster&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Trappings}. It materializes anywhere in Range, and with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll, it&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Resilient]{Resilient} as well.</p>\n<p>The ally acts on its creator&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card}&nbsp;and follows her commands to the best of its ability. It has no personality, creativity, or emotions. When the power ends or the ally is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated}, it fades into nothingness, leaving no trace behind.</p>\n<p>The type of servant that can be summoned depends on the caster&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank}. With the GM&rsquo;s approval, the player may swap abilities. If a hero wants an attendant in the form of a wolf, for example, the caster might exchange the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} skill for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Survival]{Survival} so that the &ldquo;animal&rdquo; can track its foes.</p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Summon Ally</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Rank</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Cost</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Servant</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Novice</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>Attendant</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Seasoned</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>Bodyguard</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Veteran</td>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>Mirror Self*</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Heroic</td>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>Sentinel</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>*<em>Mirror Self incurs a&nbsp;</em><em>&minus;1 </em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}<em>&nbsp;per </em><em>Rank above Veteran to a maximum of&nbsp;</em><em>&minus;6&nbsp;at Legendary</em></p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Allies (Varies):&nbsp;</strong> Additional allies of the same type may be summoned at the same time for half the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} cost of the original summons (total cost including modifiers, rounded up).</li>\n<li><strong>Bite/Claw (+1):&nbsp;</strong> The ally can bite or claw at Str+d6.</li>\n<li><strong>Combat Edge (+1):&nbsp;</strong> The ally has a Combat Edge (it must meet the Requirements as usual). You may take this modifier up to three times per ally.</li>\n<li><strong>Duration (+1):</strong>&nbsp;<em>Summon ally's&nbsp;</em>Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds.</li>\n<li><strong>Flight (+2):</strong> The ally can fly at @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} 12</li>\n<li><strong>Increased Trait (+1):&nbsp;</strong> The caster can increase a Trait one die type for 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}. She may do this for as many Traits as she likes, but only once per Trait.</li>\n<li><strong>Mind Rider (+1):</strong> The caster can communicate and sense through the ally.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\n<h2>STATBLOCKS</h2>\n<p><strong>Attendant</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Attributes: </strong>Agility d4, Smarts d4, Spirit d4, Strength d4, Vigor d4<br /><strong>Skills:</strong>&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d4, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d4, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} d4, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d4, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d6<br /><strong>Pace: </strong>4; <strong>Parry: </strong>4; <strong>Toughness: </strong>4<br /><strong>Special Abilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Claw: </strong>Str+d4.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Construct)]{Construct}: </strong>+2 to recover from being @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}; ignore 1 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound penalties}; doesn&rsquo;t breathe, immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Poison]{poison} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Disease]{disease}.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Fearless)]{Fearless}: </strong>Immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{fear} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Bodyguard</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Attributes: </strong>Agility d6, Smarts d4, Spirit d6, Strength d6, Vigor d6<br /><strong>Skills:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d6, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d6, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} d6, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} d4, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d4, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d4<br /><strong>Pace: </strong>6; <strong>Parry: </strong>5; <strong>Toughness: </strong>7 (2)<br /><strong>Edges: </strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.First Strike]{First Strike}<br /><strong>Gear: </strong>Melee attack (Str+d6).<br /><strong>Special Abilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Armor +2: </strong>Hardened skin.</li>\n<li><strong><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Construct)]{Construct}:</strong> </strong>See Attendant.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Fearless)]{Fearless}: </strong>Immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{fear} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Mirror Self<br /></strong>The ally is a clone of the caster except: it&rsquo;s an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras}; it has the same number of current @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} as the caster after subtracting for this casting; it cannot use the <em>summon ally </em>power; its @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{skills} (but not @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{attributes}) are one die type less (minimum d4) than the original; it has identical mundane equipment (no magical qualities, disappears when the power expires); has the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Construct)]{Construct} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Fearless)]{Fearless} abilities.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Sentinel<br />Attributes: </strong>Agility d6, Smarts d6, Spirit d8, Strength d12+2, Vigor d10<br /><strong>Skills:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d6, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d10, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} d10, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} d8<br /><strong>Pace: </strong>6; <strong>Parry: </strong>7; <strong>Toughness: </strong>13 (4)<br /><strong>Edges: </strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Arcane Resistance]{Arcane Resistance}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Improved Sweep]{Sweep (Improved)}.<br /><strong>Gear: </strong>Melee attack (Str+d8).<br /><strong>Special Abilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Armor +4: </strong>Stone skin.</li>\n<li><strong><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Construct)]{Construct}:</strong> </strong>See Attendant.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Fearless)]{Fearless}: </strong>Immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{fear} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} 2: </strong>Sentinels are 8' tall and very dense.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Spellcasting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Clay figure that grows into a servant","arcane":"Wizard","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":3900000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.8bPAvCSxx3oSvfZx"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"vFChiHkCTNeh38Rf","name":"Light of Siberys/Darkness of Khyber","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evocation}</p>\n<p><em>Light </em>creates bright @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{illumination} in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}. With a raise, the light can be focused into a 5&Prime; (10 yard) beam as well.</p>\n<p><em>Darkness </em>blocks @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{illumination}&nbsp;in an area the size of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}, making the area Dark, or Pitch Darkness with a raise (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination}).</p>\n<p>If <em>light </em>and <em>darkness </em>overlap, they create a patch of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim light} (&minus;2).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Area Effect (+2): </strong>The <em>light</em> expands to the caster&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} in radius, with a Range of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} &times;2. The light is sunlight and has the same effect on certain creatures (such as vampires) as natural sunlight.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>True Darkness (+2):</strong> The <em>darkness</em> blocks @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Infravision]{Infravision}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Low Light Vision]{Low Light Vision}, and @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Darkvision]{Darkvision}. It has no effect on magical sight such as <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect arcana}</em>.</li>\n<li><strong>Mobile (+1):</strong> The caster can move the area of effect up to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} die type each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{round} after casting, or attach it to an inanimate object when first cast.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Spellcasting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"Bright sunbeam or shadows that pull from the ground","arcane":"Wizard","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":2300000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gEg0cmKVXZN0LEYt"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"YqIIyHjgF4cx0xvY","name":"Illusion","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Illusion}</p>\n<p><em>Illusion </em>can be used to create a visual scene or replica of most anything the caster can imagine, but it is silent, intangible, and incapable of affecting the real world. For example, illusionary weapons pass through foes, one cannot sit in an illusionary chair, and an illusionary dog has no audible bark.</p>\n<p>Those who contact an <em>illusion </em>or doubt it&rsquo;s real make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} (at &ndash;2 if the power was activated with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}). If @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful}, that individual is no longer subject to this casting.</p>\n<p>The GM should make @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group rolls} for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras} as they point out the <em>illusion&rsquo;s </em>inconsistencies to each other.</p>\n<p>The volume of the <em>illusion </em>must fit within a sphere the size of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}&nbsp;(4&Prime; or eight yards in diameter).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area Effect (+1):</strong> The illusion&rsquo;s area of effect is increased to the size of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Deadly Illusion (+3):</strong> The <em>illusion</em> may attack or otherwise cause harm. Once per turn, the caster may use an action to &ldquo;attack&rdquo; an individual. This is an opposed roll of the caster&rsquo;s arcane skill versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} (at &minus;2 if the power was activated with a raise).\n<p>If the caster wins, the target is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} (this cannot cause Incapacitation). With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the target suffers a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} (this can cause Incapacitation). The caster may attack additional foes as @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Actions}. She may not use other combat maneuvers, such as @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Called Shots]{Called Shots} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Attack]{Wild Attacks} (though it may look that way!)</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Duration (+1):</strong> The Duration is measured in minutes.</li>\n<li><strong>Mobility (+1/+2):</strong> For a +1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}, the <em>illusion</em> can move (and fly) at a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} of 12, or 24 for +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}. This is a limited @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action}.</li>\n<li><strong>Sound (+1):</strong> The power generates sound appropriate to the <em>illusion</em>. Illusionary allies may talk, illusionary crows caw, and so on. It may not mask or mute existing sound, however.&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (+2):</strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} rolls to disbelieve the <em>illusion </em>are made at &minus;2.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Spellcasting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Shaping windy with wand","arcane":"Wizard","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":4100000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Z847ioI1J7kcXYBP"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"6sqEABjoWg6Xn9P2","name":"Friends","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p>A successful arcane skill vs @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll gives the caster insight into a target's basic emotions. This grants him a +1 bonus (+2 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}) to all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} rolls against the target for the Duration of the power.</p>\n<p><em>Empathy</em> works on animals, adding +1 (+2 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}) to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Riding]{Riding} or other rolls to interact with the creature.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong>&nbsp;@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li><strong>Charm (+2): </strong>If the target is Uncooperative or Neutral, a successful casting makes him Cooperative, or Friendly with a raise. The spell is instantly broken if the caster or her allies attack the victim or her allies.</li>\n<li><strong>Duration (+1):</strong> Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds. If the character Critically Fails any of the affected skill rolls against the target, the effect terminates immediately.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Truth (+2):</strong> The caster knows if the target believes he's telling the truth or not.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"Spellcasting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Concentration on a target","arcane":"Wizard","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":1500000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.eAQAHjnqokcoEg0F"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"CDim5gqD4xkrwjIY","name":"Crossbow, Light","type":"weapon","data":{"description":null,"notes":"Hand-drawn","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":5,"price":25,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Shooting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"2d6","range":"10/20/40","rof":"1","ap":"2","minStr":"d6","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":600001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.cXYnSp8h1A8bQn7H"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/crossbow.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"B7VemQ686LNEpzQl","name":"Outfit, Scholar's","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Perfect for a scholar, this outfit includes a robe, a belt, a cap, soft shoes, and possibly a cloak.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":5,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":700000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VLjyDDvhoHCfjNa4"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/robe.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"G1LtIasyuAwe7DXY","name":"Bolt","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>All crossbows use these kinds of crossbow bolts, which are sometimes called \"quarrels.\"</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":20,"weight":0.05,"price":0.05,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":500000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.S1MrclfpqaebDGMj"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/arrow-flights.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"gXb9fwKaMV7UXFHY","name":"Backpack","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This leather knapsack has one large pocket that closes with a buckled strap and holds about 2 cubic feet of material. Some may have one or more smaller pockets on the sides.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":5100000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EJwgrkGHCSHskUnO"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/backpack.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"UJrDlPq6jA5BJx6B","name":"Ink","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This vial contains 1 ounce of ink. Ink in colors other than black costs twice as much.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":8,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":1300000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.SL5djuvy1ajzLILp"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/quill-ink.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"wX1PbY4a0IO7rsxX","name":"Inkpen","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This is a wooden stylus with a metal tip that retains a small amount of ink after you dip it in a vial of ink.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0.1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":1400000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.K9ejgX2dnb8jAsQM"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/quill-ink.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"w72EtNKdY99aGMxB","name":"Pouch","type":"gear","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0.5,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":2800000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.uei6rnu2kRmn3n7w"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/knapsack.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"w2IEx34KJQsvx1lh","name":"Quiver","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Holds 20 arrows/bolts.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":2900000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ipm13FxqvINKhVMz"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/quiver.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Kc6mVA20yg9SKH50","name":"Scroll Case","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>A leather or wooden scroll case easily holds four scrolls; you can cram more inside, but retrieving any of them becomes a full action rather than a free action. You must destroy the scroll case to damage its contents. A scroll case is not watertight, and must still be protected from the elements.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":3700000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.dog1ogE8gOY7uyJB"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/tied-scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Wh3pu1iVPkkTBBB3","name":"Journal","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This is a blank, lightweight book with an oilskin cover. It has 50 paper pages.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":10,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":700000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.UWruaYQei4yYUJfV"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/white-book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"bFUFuZxREqjAhOlg","name":"Sealing Wax","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This stick of red (or another color) wax is used to seal envelopes, often using an impression from a signet ring as proof they were sent by you.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":300000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.gXXUkiTr94IEhgFh"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/swap-bag.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"axNDStIDRBJNMufC","name":"Bag of Sand","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This bag of sand is used for soaking up wet ink to dry out the writting on a parchment.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0.1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.mpYzIw09Vx43SNlf"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/swap-bag.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"AQZQ8mlRO2uEBERq","name":"Perfume","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Most perfumes and colognes are derived from the essential oils of flowers. Perfume or cologne may (at the GM's discretion) provide a +1 bonus on several certain @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} checks.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":5,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":2400000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.k9EgXXXZDoe3WqWX"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/perfume-bottle.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"em6davup4EOMaFhF","name":"Channeling","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">When the character gets a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise }on her arcane skill roll (or roll to activate or use an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Devices]{arcane device}), she reduces its @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">&nbsp;cost by 1. This </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">can </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">take it to 0</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Arcane Background (any)"}},"sort":5300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6i9cxyc2ng8","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Power Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Z5thwi3zWWr2HXC1"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"QiZNnOSVra29ZVGl","name":"Rich","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Whether the individual was born with a silver spoon in his mouth or earned it through hard work, he&rsquo;s got more money than most.</p>\n<p>Rich heroes start with 900 gold galifars instead of the usual 300. The hero also receives (1d6+6) x 100 gp per week, perhaps from family holdings, a profitable business, or an inheritance. Whether he can get to it or not is another matter. It might simply build up in an account, or more likely, as a collection of assets such as a manor or estate. Of course that kind of wealth usually comes with obligations to spend it, pay taxes, or take care of retainers, employees, caretakers, and grounds.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"sort":1300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_9dc4ijzy8uh","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Background Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.jvLa3GcF1ihS9NNb"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BIjJ9nQt7JltVp3N","name":"Spell Components","type":"gear","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0.05,"price":1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":500001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.0DAFyobPr0accnyN"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/knapsack.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"xGzJkEUd8seYaZFi","name":"Bedroll","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This consists of two woolen sheets sewn together along the bottom and one side to create a bag for sleeping in. Some have cloth straps along the open side so the bedroll can be tied closed while you are sleeping. It can be rolled and tied into a tight coil for storage or transport. Most people use a blanket with the bedroll to stay warm or provide a ground cushion.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":3,"price":1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":5300000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.u4QC3ltQoRK2ucM7"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/duffel-bag.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"vZpW2k6BrAB1Tg52","name":"Mess Kit","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This tin box contains a cup and simple cutlery. The box clamps together, and one side can be used as a cooking pan and the other as a plate or shallow bowl.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":0.2,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":2000000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.kAwVnG5ld7QBujNB"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/cooking-pot.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"oQ7pnZGnOH0dz6cm","name":"Rope, Silk","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>10\"/20 yards.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":2,"price":10,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":3100000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.Grlo5VrazMEpRu7i"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/rope-coil.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"XHVA9nszUyqRsjv7","name":"Dagger","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":2,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{"oyxuzdjora":{"name":"Athletics (throwing)","type":"skill","rof":null,"skillMod":"","skillOverride":"Athletics","shotsUsed":null}}},"damage":"@str+d4","range":"3/6/12","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"d4","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":400001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.GxVNY83rIxMpxCqB"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/stiletto.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"L1L00meDejRG2EBZ","name":"Letter of Credit (1000 gp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":1000,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.RTyfIimlzKPiSezD"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/scroll-quill.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"xUqykGeENbcUomxT","name":"Arcane Wand","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The counts for a Wizard's Bonded Object.</p>\n<p>The spellcaster possesses an amulet, ring, staff, wand, or weapon that adds +1 to all his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Spellcasting]{Spellcasting} totals when worn or in hand. If the object is lost or destroyed, the mage can replace it with a new object worth at least 500 gp.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":500,"equippable":true,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":700001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.JCKSq3i0xBRtth7E"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/orb-wand.svg","effects":[{"_id":"8h4NWdC7x66TwLcQ","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.attributes.spellcasting.die.modifier","value":"1","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/orb-wand.svg","label":"Arcane Focus","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Bt9Bw9ZmesSHoaz5","name":"Aristocrat","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>This individual was born into privilege or came into it later in life. She may or may not have money (the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rich]{Rich} or @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Filthy Rich]{Filthy Rich}&nbsp;Edge), but she still walks in the elite social circles of the setting.</p>\n<p>This character will likely be able to place ir' before their last name to denote being a member of the nobility.</p>\n<p>Aristocrats add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} when @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking} with the local elite, captains of industry, nobles, or other aristocrats. They also add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls made to know the etiquette of the upper class, recognize family trees or heraldry, or recall gossip concerning others of their station.</p>\n<p>Typically, a character with this edge has the lowest noble title (his father being one or two steps higher up the social ladder). The character also rules a small manor, small village, or hamlet. Only with the GM's permission may the character begin at a higher social status.</p>\n<p>Further social promotions require family members to move aside (or die) to allow the character to assume a new title, and this should be worked into the campaign.</p>\n<h2>Other Form of \"Nobility\"</h2>\n<p>While the Noble Edge typically covers those born to high station, this is not a firm dictate. The Edge can also be used to represent other character types. A player who wants to use the Noble Edge in an atypical way should always consult with his GM first.</p>\n<p>For instance, a cleric with the Edge may be the head of a small temple. A hero may also be a guildmaster. Normally this should be a legitimate guild, but with the GM's permission, the hero may run a small thieves' guild. A hero may be a guildmaster for a craft guild or perhaps run a way station for one of the dragonmarked houses. The hero must handle labor disputes, raids by the thieves' guild, and so on.</p>\n<p>Although a merchant can be represented by the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Rich]{Rich} Edge, one taking the Aristocract Edge might be a well-known merchant or have a sizable business. In return for the +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking} bonus, he also has the hassle of balancing the books, negotiating contracts, fighting off competitors, and such like.</p>\n<p>Characters using Artistocract in an alternate way do not gain the titles listed elsewhere. GMs and players should work together to create suitable honorifics.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Modified from Savage Worlds Adventure Edition</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice"}},"sort":500000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EodaX1WBgR36f4bq"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"jyENu8ZWzsWhFuS5","name":"Cloak of Minor Protection","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The cloak is made from a strange material that has been made in manifest zone to @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-lore.Shavarath]{Shavarath}. It surrounds the wearer with an invisible but tangible field of force. It grants an armor bonus of +2, which does not stack with worn armor (use the highest value)</p>\n<p><strong>Craft:</strong>&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Protection]{Protection}</em>; 2,000 gp</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":1,"price":4000,"equippable":true,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":5400000,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.VpLp24aWHGyVEXPA"},"cf":{"id":"temp_4ybla1pnsyl","path":"Savage Eberron Treasure#/CF_SEP/11. Wondrous Items","color":"#000000"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/wondrous/cloak.svg","effects":[{"_id":"lcCWgDFvBgdt6wYe","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.armor","value":"2","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/wondrous/cloak.svg","label":"Cloak of Protection","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"mUFxTBzRns3uxolo","name":"Scroll of Dispel Magic","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Scroll of <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{dispel}</em> with the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} <strong>Area Effect</strong> and <strong>Multiple Powers</strong> modifiers.</p>\n<p><strong>Craft:</strong>&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{Dispel}</em>; 600 gp</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":1200,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":5500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3q1cfbt6zbp","path":"Savage Eberron Treasure#/CF_SEP/01. Treasure","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-treasure.CDX7LZvpHbWtnxOW"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/tied-scroll.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}}],"effects":[{"_id":"O9YTGSfB0PRJpyyL","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.value","value":"-1","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":0},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/woman-elf-face.svg","label":"Slender","origin":"Actor.T4EcJwaaLrp49WDF.Item.dfNfw4jKMIvNLg5N","tint":null,"transfer":true},{"_id":"a46Nz4EvbBX3supx","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.attributes.spellcasting.die.modifier","value":"1","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":0},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/orb-wand.svg","label":"Arcane Focus","origin":"Actor.T4EcJwaaLrp49WDF.Item.xUqykGeENbcUomxT","tint":null,"transfer":true},{"_id":"Eg6gVLj80asIGOqM","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.stats.toughness.armor","value":"2","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":0,"startRound":2,"startTurn":0},"icon":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/wondrous/cloak.svg","label":"Cloak of Protection","origin":"Actor.T4EcJwaaLrp49WDF.Item.jyENu8ZWzsWhFuS5","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"gm-notes":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_2mncjgs233x","path":"Savage Eberron Characters#/CF_SEP/Pregens","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Rf1xkRsOsupXvEvW"}
