<strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n<li><strong>(L) :</strong></li>\n</ol>\n</div>"},"bennies":{"value":3,"max":3},"status":{"isShaken":false,"isDistracted":false,"isVulnerable":false,"isStunned":false,"isEntangled":false,"isBound":false},"initiative":{"hasHesitant":false,"hasLevelHeaded":false,"hasImpLevelHeaded":false,"hasQuick":false},"additionalStats":{},"wildcard":true},"token":{"flags":{},"name":"Paladin","displayName":0,"img":"modules/savage-eberron-bestiary/assets/bestiary_tokens/humanoids/dwarf/dwarf-warrior-01.png","tint":null,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"vision":true,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"dimLight":0,"brightLight":0,"sightAngle":0,"lightAngle":0,"lightColor":null,"lightAlpha":1,"lightAnimation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5},"actorId":"4a0dCu7d9Pysuszw","actorLink":true,"disposition":1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":""},"bar2":{"attribute":""},"randomImg":false,"alpha":1},"items":[{"_id":"gso7NeJMXpdXlU6X","name":"Untrained","type":"skill","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":-2},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":600000,"flags":{},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skill.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"RMmVU7ormCp2MOqN","name":"Athletics","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Athletics combines an individual&rsquo;s coordin&shy;ation with learned skills such as climbing, jumping, balancing, biking, wrestling, skiing, swimming, throwing, or catching. Characters who rely on physical power more than coordination can take the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Brute]{Brute} Edge to link this skill to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} instead of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":700000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sAig03GZiFKqBX7p"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/jump-across.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BkQxvPAlZLOJY7OZ","name":"Common Knowledge","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p>Characters roll Common Knowledge to know people, places, and things of their world, including etiquette, geography, culture, popular technology, contacts, and customs.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":800000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.8N1uMThntsjaUPem"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/gift-of-knowledge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GN2DOxOtwyROzNWZ","name":"Persuasion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Persuasion is the ability to convince others to do what you want through reason, cajoling, deception, rewards, or other friendly means. Persuasion isn&rsquo;t mind control. It can change someone&rsquo;s attitude but not their goals. A bandit may let you keep a sentimental piece of jewelry with a good Persuasion roll but still takes all your other goods.</p>\n<p>When used to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Support]{Support} allies it&rsquo;s an unopposed roll. If the target is resistant, it&rsquo;s an @JournalEntry[JBxsGv2wAoAmoCDe]{opposed} roll vs. the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. The GM should modify the roll as she sees fit based on roleplaying, any pertinent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} that affect the conversation, and the circumstances.</p>\n<p><strong>Reaction Level:</strong> How much a person is willing to cooperate depends largely on their attitude toward whoever&rsquo;s talking to them. The Game Master can decide how nonplayer characters feel based on the setting, or roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Reaction Table]{Reaction Table} if she has no preconceived notions.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} improves the target&rsquo;s attitude one level and a raise improves it two. Further increases aren&rsquo;t generally possible in the same encounter&mdash;it takes individuals a little time to adjust their biases.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Failure} means the target won&rsquo;t change his mind this scene or until the situation changes in some important way. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} also <em>reduces</em> the target&rsquo;s attitude two levels.</p>\n<p>Only one roll should generally be allowed per interaction unless new information is revealed, a substantial reward is offered, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Networking: </strong>Characters can also use Persuasion as a &ldquo;macro skill,&rdquo; simulating a few hours or an evening&rsquo;s time hobnobbing and socializing to gain favors or information. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":900000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.xOmuCR92Ys9jD5vg"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/convince.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"8qCrEiZTjPRuJ2Qq","name":"Stealth","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Stealth is the ability to hide and move quietly. A simple @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} on a Stealth roll means the character avoids detection if enemies aren&rsquo;t particularly alert. If the character @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails} the roll, the enemy realizes something is amiss and begins actively searching for whatever roused them.</p>\n<p>Once foes are alerted and active, Stealth is opposed by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} (a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{group roll} if there are many foes.</p>\n<p>The GM should apply any circumstantial penalties to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{darkness}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{cover}, noise, distractions, and any difference in the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale} (just like when attacking). Sneaking through dry leaves might subtract 2 from the Stealth roll, for example, while spotting someone in the dark uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination} penalty (&minus;4). Don&rsquo;t apply the same modifier to both rolls, however. If Stealth is at &minus;2 for the leaves, don&rsquo;t give Notice a +2 for them as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Sneak Attack: </strong> Sneaking up close enough to make a melee attack <em>always</em> requires an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} Stealth roll versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice}, whether the guard is actively looking for trouble or not. If successful, the victim is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to the attacker, but only until the attacker&rsquo;s turn ends. With a raise, the attacker has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop} instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Movement:</strong> In combat, characters roll Stealth each turn as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of their move or any action the GM thinks might draw attention.</p>\n<p>Out of combat, the distance moved depends entirely on the situation. The GM might want a roll every minute if the group is sneaking around the perimeter of a defensive position, or every few miles if they&rsquo;re trying to quietly walk the path through a dark forest without alerting the creatures that live there.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1000000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.z9FmdFVGOOW2kufm"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/hidden.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"hzQAaO1x5wYjovWb","name":"Notice","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Notice is a hero&rsquo;s general awareness and alertness. It&rsquo;s used to sense sights, sounds, tastes, and smells, spot clues, detect ambushes, spot hidden weapons on a foe, or tell if a rival is lying, frightened, happy, etc.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} conveys basic information&mdash;the character hears movement in the forest, smells distant smoke, or senses someone isn&rsquo;t being completely truthful.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants more detail, such as the direction of a sound or odor or what topic a person is avoiding or lying about.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1100000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.yvw9bMgsrWQXuZN2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/psychic-waves.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ruBTbGRqlMoy2uSz","name":"Language (Common)","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1500001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.XIuR2IyQtewm5BZP"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/talk.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"GQMFWtp6IWJ6kqTY","name":"Crowns (cp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":6,"weight":0.02,"price":0.01,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.fBZcb1EdAbO4EEOl"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-copper.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"6IZsePloV317RsUb","name":"Dragons (pp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":23,"weight":0.02,"price":10,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.33dBhsz0KCjjGHYe"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-platinum.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"HNsCemxmNdyU8oWj","name":"Galifars (gp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":25,"weight":0.02,"price":1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.CbrYbcaa5bTV8Wnd"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-gold.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Mccx8d95umBCcVgu","name":"Sovereigns (sp)","type":"gear","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":12,"weight":0.02,"price":0.1,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.EeHD4BJl6bS0eE4D"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/coin-silver.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ZZrY9N4uTnYeHmFJ","name":"Unarmed Strike","type":"weapon","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"Fighting","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"@str","range":"","rof":"1","ap":"0","minStr":"","shots":"0","currentShots":"0","ammo":"","autoReload":false},"sort":1600001,"flags":{},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/blackbackground/fist.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"viVI0A8hOKiphIYf","name":"Hard To Kill","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">This adventurer has more lives than a herd of cats. He may ignore his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} penalties when making @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls to avoid <strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Bleeding Out}</strong></span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+"}},"sort":1700001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_bv1geyfk6c","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Combat Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.hpC41I3Bd56WPTu2"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ciV1ZIUUHMoBxhTV","name":"Stability","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Dwarf]{Dwarves} have a low center of gravity. They recieve a +2 bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} rolls for performing and resisting @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Push]{Push} attacks.</p>\n<p>This also gives them a +2 bonus for to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} rolls for to resist being knocked @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Prone]{Prone} from a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Push]{Push} attack,&nbsp; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Grappling]{Grappling} attacks or other @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} based @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Tests}.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":800000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.1H3LVT4Iwgc1Bt4U"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/dwarf-face.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"tK6MvIMu8SkfCAhp","name":"Stonecunning","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Dwarf]{Dwarves} grow up in halls and caverns of worked stone, and get a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll at +2 as a free action within 10 feet of unusual stonework such as traps and hidden doors. Success means they know something is off, and a raise gives them more specific information such as how to trigger the trap or open the door. They also add 2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Common Knowledge]{Common Knowledge} rolls also related to stonework or mechanical work.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":900000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.oKUfbirZZMjg6bU9"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/dwarf-face.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"BITQdy4sO25onYpD","name":"Dwarven Resilience","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Dwarf]{Dwarves} are hardy and resistanct to toxins. They gain a +4 bonus to resist the effects of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Poison]{poison}. Damage from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Poison]{poison} is also reduced by 4.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":700000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.9vf1AJvQXGdej9Sc"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/dwarf-face.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ikSEcN5z5Ccuo94f","name":"Language (Dwarvish)","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>In some settings, such as those that focus on pulp action or &ldquo;planetary romance&rdquo; (where characters frequently travel among many strange civilizations), speaking various languages can simply be roleplayed with halting dialogue and campy accents that start out a little difficult and are quickly forgotten. The GM may ignore this skill altogether in these settings, or use the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multiple Languages]{Multiple Languages}&nbsp;&shy;option in the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Setting Rules]{Setting Rules}.</p>\n<p>In more realistic settings, communication can be a major barrier that requires characters to put skill points into additional languages. In a 1980s World War Three game, for example, a group of United Nations paratroopers won&rsquo;t be able to speak with their foes unless they take Russian, Polish, or other languages common to the Warsaw Pact.</p>\n<p>If the Language skill is in use, it should be listed as Language (Spanish), Language (American Sign Language), etc. A character&rsquo;s die type also notes how fluent he is in it. (Characters start with a d8 in their own Language.)</p>\n<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Language Proficiency</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Skill</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Ability</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>d4</td>\n<td>The character can read, write and speak common words and phrases.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d6</td>\n<td>The speaker can carry on a prolonged but occasionally halting conversation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d8</td>\n<td>The character can speak fluently.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d10</td>\n<td>The hero can mimic other dialects within the language.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>d12</td>\n<td>The speaker can masterfully recite important literary or oral works.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Limited: </strong>Use whichever skill is lowest when performing an action that requires knowledge of a foreign language. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} (if verbal), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Research]{Research}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt}, etc., are all limited by the character&rsquo;s Language skill.</p>\n<p>This limitation never applies to a character&rsquo;s native tongue.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":600000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_nsugutrpau","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.6h3o5AH7UNmgPjdJ"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/talk.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"ArT32Y7S8uWpjPen","name":"Darkvision","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>The creature can see normally up to 10\" in areas of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim or Dark illumination} and treat @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Pitch Darkness} as @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim illumination}. They treat anything beyond that distance as @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim illumination} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dark illumination} respectively. Such vision is in black and white only.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":100001,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.ySnD6BzrINJi0bnJ"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/angry-eyes.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"41iR440CbDfiaS3K","name":"Intimidation","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Intimidation is the art of frightening an opponent so that he backs down, reveals information, or flees.</p>\n<p>Intimidation is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} resisted by the opponent&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. In combat, this is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}. Out of combat, a successful roll means the foe backs down for the most part, reveals some information, or slinks away when the opportunity presents itself.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} might mean he backs down for the remainder of the scene, spills all the beans, or runs away as fast as he can.</p>\n<p>In or out of combat, a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} means the target is immune to this character&rsquo;s Intimidation attempts for the remainder of this encounter!</p>\n<p><strong>Networking:</strong> Intimidation can also be used as a &ldquo;macro&rdquo; skill to simulate several hours of working the streets. See&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Networking]{Networking}&nbsp;to see how to crack some heads for favors or information.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"spirit","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1800001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.RrgAZp50CgQyyY6w"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/arrest.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"pXZy8BwGuZCBnMy0","name":"Shooting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Shooting covers all attempts to hit a target with a ranged weapon such as a bow, pistol, or rocket launcher (thrown weapons use @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}). See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for details on ranged combat.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1900001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.sOHfVvBDhe3Oy3r1"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/crosshair.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"UuCLY3Kphs9uOj54","name":"Riding","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p>Riding allows a hero to mount, control, and ride any beast or beast-drawn vehicle common to his setting. This includes horses, camels, dragons, wagons, chariots, and the like. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Mounted Combat]{Mounted Combat}.</p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2000001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.DHKzenDEPdjw3X2u"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/saddle.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"c3lQR5t40tR4YjjD","name":"Fighting","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Fighting covers all hand-to-hand (melee) attacks, whether it&rsquo;s with fists, axes, laser swords, or martial arts. See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Combat]{Chapter Three} for the combat rules and the various maneuvers a warrior might attempt.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"agility","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":8,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":2100001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.wWiwjPlzAQU3TN9l"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/punch.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"5CZGhFXiAmrkvaDm","name":"Religion","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Religion reflects knowledge about ancient religions, mythic history, eccelsiastic tradition, holy symbols, undead, as well as details about all the religions of Eberron.</p>\n<p>A successful Religion roll reveals basic information about a topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":1000001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.HdShAatiWIBLgv8z"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/skills/church.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"DOymbSZ4M5iHdDmU","name":"Paladin","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Through a worthy few shines the power of the divine. Called paladins, these noble souls dedicate their swords and lives to the battle against evil. Knights, crusaders, and lawbringers, paladins seek not just to spread righteous justice but to embody the teachings of the virtuous deities they serve. In pursuit of their lofty goals, they adhere to ironclad laws of morality and discipline.</p>\n<p>As a reward for their service, these holy champions are blessed with boons to aid them in their quests. They gain abilities to battle evil opponents, heal allies, and inspire the faithful. Their conviction leads them into conflict with the very souls they would save. Paladins weather endless challenges of faith and temptation. They risk their lives to do right and ensure justice.</p>\n<p>Paladins gain the following abilities:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Aura of Courage]{Aura of Courage}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Code of Honor]{Code of Honor}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Detect Evil (or Good)]{Detect Evil (or Good)}</li>\n<li>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-edges.Smite Evil (or Good)]{Smite Evil (or Good)}</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Strength d6+, Spirit d6+, Vow (Minor—serve their deity or order)"}},"sort":100000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.v0X1hSTjhREkiuLf"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"Ilk1eVhE7nrRDcsC","name":"Aura of Courage","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>As long as the paladin is conscious, all allies within 10&rdquo; (20 yards) add +1 to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear} tests.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Paladin"}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.dYfVIshMEbxQFBsE"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"6DJUMbZgS7iKuGJq","name":"Code of Honor","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>All paladins have the Code of Honor Hindrance, even evil ones though it might be different.</p>\n<p>Honor is very important to your character. He keeps his word, doesn&rsquo;t abuse or kill prisoners, and generally tries to operate within his world&rsquo;s particular notion of proper gentlemanly or ladylike behavior.</p>\n<p>This is in addition to their other Hindrances.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"sort":300000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.kssBhJb3FTVyosko"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"oET9mNX7KCGazGh0","name":"Detect Evil (or Good)","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>As an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{action}, the Paladin can concentrate on any one object or individual within @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} range to determine whether it&rsquo;s Evil (or Good) in nature.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Paladin"}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.BEKZNxav4YubrQ97"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"3SXfW4m2KOORRa8E","name":"Smite Evil (or Good)","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>As a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action}, a paladin can choose an enemy. If that enemy is evil (or good), she gets a free reroll on any failed @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} rolls against that target for the remainder of the encounter. She may use this ability once per @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} per encounter.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Paladin"}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.kyZPP0PTkA9dXLtC"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"HtsxVTMjxt2mL4bq","name":"Champion","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Champions are holy (or unholy) men and women chosen to fight for a particular deity or religion. Most are pious souls ready and willing to lay down their lives for a greater cause, but some may have been born into the role and follow their path with some reluctance.</p>\n<p>Champions fight the forces of darkness (or good), adding +2 damage when attacking supernaturally evil (or good if they&rsquo;re evil) creatures. The bonus applies to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{area effect damage}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Attacks]{ranged attacks}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Powers]{powers}, etc.</p>\n<p>The GM must decide which foes this bonus applies to, but generally it&rsquo;s any evil (or good!) creature born of magic or with any supernatural abilities.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Novice, Spirit d8+, Fighting d6+"}},"sort":2200001,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_cap9ep7u7q","path":"Edges#/CF_SEP/Weird Edges","color":"#000000"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-edges.pajf2NwAkxt7TCbY"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"1FA2Qi8bH7cGredU","name":"Mystic Powers (Paladin)","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the paladin can invoke one of the following miracles: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait}</em> (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength}, and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Relief]{relief}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}</em>.&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost Trait}</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}</em> are self only, but the paladin gains no benefit from the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Limitation}.</p>\n<p>The paladin has 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} that recharge normally. She automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} for an additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}. He may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired.</p>\n<p>Mystic Powers doesn&rsquo;t grant access to Edges that require an Arcane Background. If the paladin also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges, abilities, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} can be used with Mystic Powers (and vice-versa).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":false,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Paladin"}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.xuvMmtl4nldn0CBO"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"opaBc5JKBDfeL0NN","name":"Mystic Powers (Paladin)","type":"edge","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>As a limited free action the paladin can invoke one of the following miracles: <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{boost Trait}</em> (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength}, and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} only), <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Healing]{healing}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Relief]{relief}</em>, and <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}</em>.&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Boost/Lower Trait]{Boost Trait}</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Smite]{smite}</em> are self only, but the paladin gains no benefit from the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Limitation}.</p>\n<p>The paladin has 10 dedicated @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} that recharge normally. She automatically activates the power with success for its regular cost, or with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} for an additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}. He may use applicable Power Modifiers if desired.</p>\n<p>Mystic Powers doesn&rsquo;t grant access to Edges that require an Arcane Background. If the paladin also has an Arcane Background, none of its Edges, abilities, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} can be used with Mystic Powers (and vice-versa).</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"isArcaneBackground":true,"requirements":{"value":"Seasoned, Paladin"}},"sort":200000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.xuvMmtl4nldn0CBO"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/edge.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"3JkiVbV2jcnjLU84","name":"Blessing of the Flame","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation/Necromancy}</p>\n<p><strong>Limitation:</strong> Boost only (Fighting, Strength and Vigor only)</p>\n<p>This power allows a character to increase or decrease a target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} (attribute or skill).</p>\n<p><em>Boosting </em>an ally&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} increases the selected Trait one die type, or two with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, for five rounds.</p>\n<p><em>Lowering </em>an enemy&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} has a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Powers]{Duration} of Instant and lowers the selected attribute or skill a die type with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}, or two with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} (to a minimum of d4). A victim automatically tries to shake off the effect with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of his following turns.&nbsp;Success improves the effect one die type, and a raise removes the effect entirely.</p>\n<p>Additional castings don&rsquo;t stack on a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} (take the highest), but may affect different Traits.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}&nbsp;each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Boost/Lower Trait (+2):&nbsp;</strong> With success, the selected @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} gains a free reroll once per round, or once per action with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. For <em>lower Trait</em> the target applies a &minus;2 penalty to the affected Trait&rsquo;s rolls.</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (+1):</strong> <em>Lower Trait</em> only. The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll to shake off the effect is made at &minus;2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"5","trapping":"Physical change, glowing aura, potions","arcane":"Paladin","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":700000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.5p4X7sd96czRfNPc"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"mee4ryizu5BsEPw0","name":"Lay on Hands","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Healing </em>removes @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} less than an hour old. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} removes one Wound, and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} removes two. The power may be cast additional times to remove additional Wounds within that hour and as long as the healer has enough @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}.</p>\n<p>For @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras}, the GM must first determine if the ally is still alive (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{Aftermath}). If so, a successful arcane skill roll returns the ally to action (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} if it matters).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Greater Healing (+10):</strong> <em>Greater healing</em> can restore any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}, including those more than an hour old.</li>\n<li><strong>Crippling Injuries (+20):</strong> The power can heal a permanent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Injury Table]{Crippling Injury} (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitation}). This requires an hour of preparation and only one casting is permitted per injury. If it @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails}, this caster cannot <em>heal </em>that particular injury (but somoene else may try). If successful, the subject is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Exhausted} for 24 hours.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Mass Healing (+2/+3):</strong> For a +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}, healing affects all allies within a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} centered on the caster (or a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template} for +3).</li>\n<li><strong>Neutralize Poison or Disease (+1):</strong> A successful <em>healing&nbsp;</em>roll negates any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Poison]{poison} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Disease]{disease}. If the poison or disease has a bonus or penalty associated with it, the modifier applies to the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll as well.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Laying on hands, touching the victim with a holy symbol, prayer","arcane":"Paladin","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":2000000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.L3HoTKUKSXvZNAqa"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"yxFQocQOVB0gnbG5","name":"Light of the Flame","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Relief</em> allows the caster to recover from a negative condition or the effects of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}.</p>\n<p><strong>Recover: </strong>The caster removes one of the following negative conditions: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable}. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll removes two conditions. If affecting more than one target (via the Additional Recipients modifier), the caster may choose which condition(s) to remove for each ally.</p>\n<p><em>Relief</em> can&rsquo;t remove negative conditions caused by ongoing effects (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bound and Entangled]{Bound or Entangled}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}, etc.) unless the source of the effect is removed.</p>\n<p><strong>Numb: </strong>Reduces the recipient&rsquo;s total penalties from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} by one with success, or two with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. An Exhausted (&minus;2) hero with three @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} (&minus;3), for example, reduces her total &minus;5 penalty to &minus;4 with success, and &minus;3 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p>This effect lasts one hour. It doesn&rsquo;t actually remove the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} or the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}, it just allows the recipient to ignore the penalties. If the target would be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated} by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}, she&rsquo;s still @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated}&nbsp;as usual.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Restoration (+3): </strong>The caster can restore one die type from an energy draining effect with a success, two with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</li>\n<li><strong>Stunned (+1): </strong>If using the Recover option, the caster may also affect the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned} condition. This completely removes the effects of being @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant/One Hour","trapping":"Prayer, tonics","arcane":"Paladin","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":2900000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.tptlmWZOYPnRsBh3"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"RHdsnHwG1kXHwa56","name":"Smite","type":"power","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p>This power is cast on a weapon of some sort. If it&rsquo;s a ranged weapon, it affects one entire magazine, 20 bolts, shells, or arrows, or one full &ldquo;load&rdquo; of ammunition (the GM determines the exact quantity for unusual weapons). While the power is in effect, the weapon&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{damage} is increased by +2, or +4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p><strong>Limitations:</strong> In the case of smite with a Personal Limitation, &ldquo;Self&rdquo; refers to the specific weapon instead.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong>&nbsp;The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Smite (+2):</strong> The weapon&rsquo;s damage is increased by +4, or +6 (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{Damage}) with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":true,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"5","trapping":"Silver flame on the weapon","arcane":"Paladin","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"sort":3400000,"flags":{"cf":null,"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lZnaZ776KQpwRoZq"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"aRJEaarP2SqhhKnj","name":"Arcana","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Arcana reflects knowledge about spells, artifacts, magic items, eldritch symbols, magical traditions, dragons, forbidden lore, magical beasts, analyzing alchemical compounds and other ritual paraphernalia, translate magical runes, guess what spell was cast based on physical evidence left behind, etc.</p>\n<p>A successful Arcana roll reveals basic information about a magical topic, and a raise grants more details.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":6,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":200001,"flags":{"journal-links":{},"core":{"sourceId":"Item.lr6HSv7xgo5Dsp1N"}},"img":"modules/savage-eberron-artwork/assets/icons/skills/spell-book.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"DXxjUHkZGmmkztWK","name":"Healing","type":"skill","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>Healing has multiple uses, from treating @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} to diagnosing diseases and analyzing certain kinds of forensic evidence.</p>\n<p>See @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{Healing} for rules on mending and treating @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds}, and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hazards]{Hazards} for treatment of disease or poison.</p>\n<p><strong>Forensics: </strong> Healing can also be used to analyze evidence that relates to anatomical trauma, including cause and time of death, angle of attack, and similar matters. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} provides basic information and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} increases the details uncovered.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"attribute":"smarts","isCoreSkill":false,"die":{"sides":4,"modifier":0},"wild-die":{"sides":6}},"sort":3500000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qals24wpyph","path":"Skills","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Dc50EUXxlsJl7sph"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/skills/medical-pack.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"qLfgoyZTLap0r9yp","name":"Vow (Serve the Silver Flame)","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\">\n<p>(MINOR OR MAJOR)</p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The character has sworn an oath to someone or something he believes in.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">The danger in fulfilling the Vow and how often it might occur determines the level of the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrance}. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Minor} </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Vow</span> might be to serve an order with a broad mandate that rarely conflicts with the party&rsquo;s goals.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Major} </span><span class=\"fontstyle0\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Vow</span> makes long-term and frequent demands on the servant&rsquo;s time and results in great risks to his life.</span></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":3600000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.pdv7W2JX8IiVuqZT"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"laDGVyr45SEFZZvw","name":"Death Wish","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Having a death wish doesn&rsquo;t mean your adventurer is suicidal&mdash;he might just think his life is worth less than some noble but clearly deadly goal. Those with a Death Wish don&rsquo;t throw their lives away for no reason, but when there&rsquo;s a chance to complete a goal they do anything&mdash;and take any risk&mdash;to achieve it.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":false},"sort":3700000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.u8qpImKHd19jXXiu"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"2pYiDAidHZJF2ZdQ","name":"Overconfident","type":"hindrance","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core\"><p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">There&rsquo;s nothing out there your hero can&rsquo;t defeat. At least that&rsquo;s what he thinks. He believes he can do most anything and never wants to retreat from a challenge. He&rsquo;s not suicidal, but he certainly takes on more than common sense dictates.</span></p></div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"major":true},"sort":3800000,"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_paujlrjlvl","path":"Hindrances","color":"#8c160f"},"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.swade-core-rules.swade-hindrances.1qgPyuagmvWDVoHR"}},"img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/hindrance.svg","effects":[],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"69OH6tdtVdH4NNDg","name":"Tough","type":"ability","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>Dwarves are stout and tough. Their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} is considered one die type higher for armor and worn gear (not weapons) and when determining Encumbrance.</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"subtype":"special","grantsPowers":false},"sort":800000,"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.tuS6pSP7BlFI5hC1"}},"img":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/dwarf-face.svg","effects":[{"_id":"bhmy8Oxej0h2Il8d","flags":{},"changes":[{"key":"data.attributes.strength.encumbranceSteps","value":"1","mode":2}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"modules/game-icons-net/whitebackground/dwarf-face.svg","label":"Tough","tint":null,"transfer":true}],"folder":null,"permission":{"default":0}},{"_id":"vqFah2PSnDLQm2rB","name":"Plate Armor","type":"armor","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":30,"price":750,"equippable":false,"equipp